title: fudge
directions: Mix milk and chips in pyrex dish.
Microwave on high 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and stir.
Return to microwave and cook high for 1 1/2 minutes more.
Stir thoroughly.
Add vanilla and nuts stirring well.
Line 8 or 9 inch pan with foil.
Spread mixture in pan and chill for 2 hours.
Remove from pan and cut into squares. Store in plastic container with lid ajar until firm.

title: cheddar apple bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined eggs, milk and margarine; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes; remove from pan.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix ingredients with tap water to form a stiff dough.
Place in covered bowl and allow to set 4 to 5 hours.
Pinch off small pieces of dough and pat into 5-inch circles.
Fry in deep, hot fat until golden brown.
Serve hot with butter and honey or meat and vegetables.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine meal and onion in bowl.
Add egg and milk; stir.
Drop by teaspoons into hot fat (375°).
Fry only a few at a time until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: ziti garden salad
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on package; drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Combine pasta and dressing with remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss; chill 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together; spread on tortillas and roll up. Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and walnuts.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Form into rolls on wax paper and chill one hour.
Slice and bake at 400°.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add brown sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Spread creamed mixture evenly in a 9-inch cast-iron skillet.
Arrange pineapple slices and cherries evenly over creamed mixture.

title: ruby salad
directions: Drain beets; measure liquid.
Add water to make 1 cup liquid. Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water.
Add measured liquid, vinegar, horseradish, onion and pepper.
Chill until thickened. Fold in beets and celery.
Spoon into individual molds or a 1 quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto crisp lettuce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn dogs
directions: Put skewers in hot dogs and set aside.
Mix corn meal, flour, baking powder, salt and egg.
Dip hot dogs in batter and then deep fry at 350°.

title: crunchy creamed corn
directions: Pour corn in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cracker mixture evenly over corn, then with a teaspoon, cut butter and drop pieces on top of the cracker crumbs.
Cook in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: jose grinan's super bowl cider
directions: Pour six oz. boiling water into mugs.
Add one caramel cube. Stir in cider mix.
Top with half of the whipped cream and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serves 2.

title: angel food candy fairy food
directions: In a heavy saucepan, bring to 290° (crack) the brown sugar and corn syrup.
Add baking soda.
Stir and while foaming, pour onto a buttered 15 x 18-inch cookie sheet.
You have to work fast.
Cool until bottom of pan is cold.
Turn pan over on waxed paper; bang pan until loose.
Break in pieces with knife point.
Dip each piece into melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper to dry.

title: sour cream dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, sugar and salt in boiling water.
Stir in light cream and vanilla (mixture may look curdled but will become smooth).
Stir in sour cream.
Chill until slightly thickened. Beat until smooth.
Pour into 3 or 4-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Cook tortellini to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain; rinse with cold water.

title: dilled okra
directions: Bring all the ingredients to a boil. Pack okra into jar, cover okra with hot vinegar mixture, seal.	Let stand 2 weeks before opening.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add other ingredients.
After mixture is jellied, cover with topping.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, rice, cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, onion, cheese and water.
Melt stick of butter on stove, crumble roll of crackers and combine crackers with butter. Pour over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
(Check after about 20 minutes.)

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange in greased casserole dish by layers, broccoli, chicken, then pour sauce over all.
(Sauce is the soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.)
Top with crumbs and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix eggs, cooking oil and milk.
Add flour, sugar and blueberries.
Spoon into muffin pan.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12.
These freeze well.

title: pasta with fresh vegetables in garlic sauce
directions: Cut carrots and zucchini lengthwise in thin slices with peeler.
Add to 1-inch boiling water in medium saucepan.
Cook until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Set aside.

title: la-millionaire's mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in large pot.
Add remaining ingredients and boil slowly, uncovered, until liquid is reduced to nearly all butter. Do not scorch.
Serve hot in a chafing dish with toothpicks.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In a medium bowl, cream margarine.
Gradually add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
In a small bowl, using a fork or pastry blender, mash bananas until pureed.
Add to creamed mixture using mixer, until smooth.
With a spoon, add flour until flour is just moistened. Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan and bake for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Melt the Velveeta cheese.
Add onions, tomatoes and meat to the melted cheese.
Keep hot in crock-pot until time to serve and serve over chips or with chips.

title: here's to your health hoagie
directions: In
small
bowl, combine cucumbers, carrot, green onion and salad dressing.
Set aside.

title: peanut butter and syrup
directions: Mix together and enjoy. May put on bread.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Cook sugar, butter and syrup in saucepan for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and soda. Whip until foamy.
Mix well with popcorn.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Add peanuts, if desired.

title: bubble up
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Spread walnuts on bottom.
Separate dough into 12 balls and place in single layer on top of nuts.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar.
Sprinkle on pudding.
Dot with butter.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring brown sugar, sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes, then add vanilla, maple flavoring and baking soda.
Cover popcorn with mixture and stir well.
Bake in oven at 250° for 1 hour and stir every 10 minutes.
(May add pecans or peanuts, if you wish.)

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from pork chops.
Put pork chops in the center of a baking dish or roasting pan.
Fill the side spaces with the potatoes.
Mix all other ingredients together for the sauce.
(You may want to double the sauce recipe if you use more chops.) Simmer the sauce for 5 minutes.
Pour over the potatoes and chops. Bake at 375° for 2 hours.

title: best cornbread
directions: Beat egg until light and frothy. Add milk and honey.
Combine the cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt. Add butter and stir well.
Pour the batter into a greased baking pan. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Serve with fresh butter.
Beat until stiff 1/2 pint heavy cream and 1 egg, beaten.
Refrigerate.

title: potato sticks
directions: Wash potatoes.
Cut lengthwise into quarters, then each quarter into thirds.
Brush potatoes with butter, melted.
Roll and coat them in a mixture of bread crumbs, cheese, salt and garlic powder.
On a baking sheet, spread out potatoes in a single layer and bake in a preheated 400° oven for about 30 minutes until tender inside and crispy brown outside.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Beat
eggs.
Add
rest	of ingredients.
Pour in crust. Bake for
30 minutes at 350°.
Pie will have a crusty top when done.

title: crab apple pickles
directions: Wash apples.
Stick cloves in some apples, being sure some cloves get in jar.
Heat sugar, liquid and spices until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Add apples and simmer until barely tender. Pack into hot jars.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: herbed chili-spaghetti
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, garlic and green pepper in Dutch oven until browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain off drippings. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: green beans bundles
directions: Cut bacon slices in half.
Wrap around a bunch of green beans, until all the beans and bacon are used.
Place in a baking dish. Make a glaze from all of the other ingredients.
Pour over the beans.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or bake in the microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Flour fruits, candy and nuts.
Mix well.
Add coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
Press firmly into wax paper-lined stem pan. Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to rolling boil. Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat about 1 minute or until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, all at one time; continue beating until smooth.
Drop dough by scant 1/4 cupfuls 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until puffed and golden.
Cool away from draft.
Cut off tops.
Pull out any filaments of soft dough.
Fill with Cool Whip or vanilla pudding.
Dust with powdered sugar!

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes in a large bowl.
Salt and pepper. Combine 2 tablespoons of flour with milk.
Mix well until flour dissolves.
Pour over potatoes; let potatoes soak in milk and seasoning while grating cheese.
In a greased 2-quart casserole, put a layer of potatoes and dot with butter.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon flour; cover with cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with 3 layers of potatoes and cheese.
Stir seasoned milk and pour over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes or until cheese is brown.
Then cover and bake until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes longer.

title: thumbprints
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add yolks and mix in vanilla and salt. Gradually add
flour.
Shape
in
balls
and dip in egg whites, then in
walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes and push in center with
thumb.
Then	bake
another
10 to 12 minutes. Cool and fill with frosting.

title: great potatoes
directions: Spray a casserole dish.
Layer bottom with Tater Tots.
Mix together in a medium pan over medium heat, the soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour over Tater Tots.
Mix corn flakes and butter together in a bowl.
Spread on top.
Cook at 375° for about 1 hour or until bubbly and potatoes are cooked through.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix eggs, flavorings, oil, milk, sugar and poppy seed.
Add flour, salt and baking powder and mix well.
Put in 2 loaf pans, bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Poke holes in top.
Drizzle with following glaze:

title: ground beef with spaghetti parmigiana
directions: In saucepot, prepare spaghetti as label directs; drain.
Return spaghetti to saucepot.

title: fruit cookies
directions: *Can use 1 pound of chipped chocolate instead of walnuts and raisins.

title: egg custard
directions: Melt butter and then add the other ingredients. Pour into pie plate. Cook in the oven at 350° for about 1 hour. Will make its own crust.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients but flour and chips together.
Then mix in flour.
After all is mixed together, add in chocolate chips. Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: jello mold
directions: Bring jello and pineapple to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes. Cool.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: white chili(low-fat)
directions: Cook onions in large pot until tender.
Add seasonings and peppers.
Stir well.
Add chicken, beans and broth and bring to a boil.
Simmer until ready to eat.
(Better if prepared the day before and refrigerated.)
Serve with Mexican Cornbread (see recipe).

title: pickle and ham roll-ups
directions: Pat ham and pickle dry with paper towel. Spread 13 ham slices with 1 tablespoon cheese. Top each with pickle spear. Roll up. Wrap each in wax paper or plastic wrap. Chill. Cut each roll in 4 to 6 pieces. Makes 62 to 78.

title: louisiana sweet potato pie
directions: Mix whipping cream, vinegar and soda. Set aside. Blend potatoes, sugar, baking powder, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and salt in processor. Add first mixture. Blend. Pour into unbaked pie crust. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Turn to 300° and bake for 40 to 50 minutes longer.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix the sliced zucchini, salt, milk, onion and milk.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and cracker crumbs on top, then add oleo and grated cheese.
Pour in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes in uncovered casserole.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice dough, place on a jelly roll pan, bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Blend the next 3 ingredients and spread on cooled cookies. Top cream cheese with the fruit.
Combine cornstarch and sugar.
Add water slowly and cook till thick.
Add dry jello and butter. Cool slightly and spread over fruit.

title: hines family jam cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Mix spices with flour and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add jam, nuts and cherries.
Bake in stem pan at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: vicki's everything but the kitchen sink chicken and broccoli
directions: Grease casserole dish and place cooked rice, chicken and broccoli mixture in it.
Combine remaining ingredients (except for noodles) and pour over other mixture.
Stir well to blend ingredients.
Cover with egg noodles.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.
(This is Charles' favorite casserole.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on and let cool.
Peel skins and grate potatoes in large bowl.
Grate cheese and add all ingredients except bread crumbs and butter.
Mix well.
Spread mixture in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top of mixture.
Melt butter and pour over bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, uncovered.

title: guacamole
directions: Smash avocados with cream cheese until creamy.
Add about 1/2 small jar of picante (more to taste).
Squeeze some lemon in mixture.
Add about a cup of grated cheese and season with salts and pepper to taste.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding until thick; then add other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: red potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes and boil in jackets.
When done, cut 1/8-inch slices.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, horseradish, celery seed and salt; set aside.
Then mix parsley and onions in another bowl. In a large bowl, put potatoes (salt each layer of potatoes lightly).
Then cover with mayonnaise mixture, then onion mixture. Continue layering with parsley/onion mixture on top and refrigerate.
Do not stir.
This needs to be made the night before.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: linda smith's apple-grape salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Pour remaining 1 cup boiling water over cream cheese cut into chunks.
Combine and refrigerate until mixture is partially set.
Add apples, marshmallows, grapes and nuts.
Chill until set.

title: date nut bread(julia veach's)
directions: Mix sifted soda with chopped dates; pour boiling water over this mixture.
Allow to stand until water cools.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla.
Combine with date mixture.
Stir in flour and nuts, which have been dredged in flour.

title: gremoleta brushchetta
directions: In small bowl combine last four ingredients.
Stir well to mix.
Spread mixture over bread slices; arrange slices in single layer on cookie sheet.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake about 15 minutes or until bread is golden brown.

title: chuck's pasta and fagioli(beans and macaroni)
directions: Fry garlic in oil until golden brown.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes and onion; cook 10 minutes.
Add beans; stir gently. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni al dente; drain.
Add to mixture.
Add parsley.
Serve immediately or pasta will absorb all the liquid.

title: dream pie
directions: Beat whipped topping mix, 1 cup milk and vanilla in large bowl with electric mixer on high speed for 6 minutes or until topping thickens and forms peaks.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cover with strips of bacon. Cover beans and bake 1 hour. Remove cover and bake another hour.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add strawberries, bananas, crushed pineapple and nuts.
Pour half the mixture into mold.
Let jell.
Spread two 1/2 pint containers of sour cream over mixture. Pour on remaining mixture and let jell.

title: chili sauce
directions: Boil 4 hours.
Hot pack.
Stir periodically so sauce maintains red color.

title: carrot ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Place 1 pan pie shell of the 2 count package of shells into the oven (4 shells will be in oven) at 300°.
While shells lightly brown, cook frozen vegetables on stove in pot of large size.
Add 2 cans broth and 2 cans cream of chicken soup.
Stir to mix.
Then let simmer on warm, stirring occasionally, so it does not stick. Use two cups of the juice to stir in flour and make a thick stirrable paste.
Pour back into the pot of vegetables.
Add salt and pepper for taste.

title: that green stuff
directions: Boil 1 cup water and add to marshmallows.
When melted, add jello and stir until dissolves.
Add 1 cup cold water and pineapple.
Place in refrigerator until sets up.
Shred the cream cheese into it and fold in whipped cream and pecans. Fix the night before you want to serve it.

title: tomato salad ring
directions: Combine tomato juice, pepper, basil and onions; heat to boiling.
Reduce
heat
to simmer; cook for 10 minutes. Strain out onions;
keep
liquid
hot.
Soak
gelatin
in water for 5 minutes.
Add to hot tomato juice.
Stir until dissolved.
Add remaining
ingredients
and
mix
well.
Pour into mold; chill until firm.
Arrange lettuce in
a serving platter; unmold the salad into the lettuce.

title: old fashioned apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix and stir in diced apples and nuts.
Put butterscotch chips on top.
Bake in a sheet pan, 13 x 9-inch or 2 (9 x 9-inch) pans, at 350° until firm.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Step 3:
Spread on top of Dream Whip mixture.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash and slice squash; boil until tender.
Drain and mash. Add onion, eggs and crackers; mix well.
In a 1-quart pot, melt butter and Velveeta cheese over low heat.
Add milk and 1 cup of grated cheese.
Pour into squash mixture.
Stir well.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bread crumbs. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: dinette cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour square, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Measure all ingredients in large mixer bowl. Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes high speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Pour into pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool, if desired.
Frost with peppermint cream cheese frosting.

title: yum-yum salad
directions: Heat pineapple and water; add jello.
Let set until partially congealed; fold in cream, salad dressing and cheese.
Place in refrigerator.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix together the milk, flour, shortening, salt and baking powder.
Roll out on board 1/4-inch thickness.
Slice apples.
Lay on top of dough mixture.
Mix 1 cup sugar (leaving 1 cup for later), nutmeg and cinnamon and spread over apples.
Roll all together and slice off 3/4-inch in thickness.
Place in large pan.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine milk and water. Add pudding mix, beat well. Chill for 10 minutes. Fold in cool whip. Line bottom of pan with vanilla wafers. Slice bananas and put on top of wafers. Then pour pudding on top of that. Repeat twice.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Mix first 3 and sprinkle salt over and let stand for 1 hour. Boil vinegar, water, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Let cool.
Squeeze cabbage out of water; pour cooled vinegar over cabbage and put in bag.
Freeze.

title: blueberry oatmeal bars
directions: Drain berries.
Reserve 1 cup syrup (add water to make one cup, if needed).
Combine reserved syrup with cornstarch and lemon juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in blueberries.
Set aside.
Combine flour, oats, sugar, baking powder, allspice and salt.
Cut in butter or margarine with pastry blender.
Press 2/3 of mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool in pan.
Combine confectioners sugar and milk; drizzle over top. Cut into bars.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: homemade pancakes
directions: Mix all together.
Add milk to desired thickness.
Cook in buttered skillet.

title: coconut dream pie
directions: Beat whipped topping mix with 1 cup milk and vanilla, using large mixer bowl. Beat on high with electric mixer about 6 minutes or until topping thickens and forms peaks. Add remaining milk, pie filling mix and coconut. Blend on low speed. Beat on high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Spoon into pie shell. Toast coconut and sprinkle on top of pie. Chill at least 4 hours before serving.

title: buffalo stew
directions: Cut the buffalo into bite size pieces; should take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over a turkey pit fire for about 4 weeks at 460°. This will serve about 2,000 people.
If more are expected, two rabbits may be added.
But do not add the rabbits unless necessary, as most people do not like to find a hare in their stew.
Serves approximately 2,000.

title: white trash carrots
directions: Steam or boil carrots and onion in a medium saucepan until tender.
Remove excess water.
Add milk and Velveeta cheese over a low heat until cheese is thoroughly melted.
Stir in crumbled potato chips and serve.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 375° to 400°.
Measure Bisquick, sugar, nutmeg, soft butter, milk and egg in mixing bowl.
Beat until all ingredients are moist and butter has blended (do not overmix). Grease muffin tins; fill 2/3 full.
Place in oven and bake at 375° to 400°.

title: excellent steak
directions: I defrost steak in refrigerator.
Then I put steak into a 9 x 13-inch pan and completely cover in soy sauce.
Marinate for 24 hours.
This also tenderizes steak.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Saute onion
and pepper in oleo.
Add flour; set aside. Beat eggs, milk,
salt
and pepper.
Add ham and 1 cup cheese, onions and
pepper.
Sprinkle
cup
cheese
on pie crust. Pour in ham and cheese mixture.
Bake in 350° oven until firm, about 30 minutes.

title: raw peach pie
directions: Put peeled peach halves (fresh) open side down in an unbaked pie shell. Mix butter, flour and sugar; add egg. Beat together and pour over peaches. Bake 1 hour at 300°. Serve with whipped or ice cream.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Cook mostaccioli noodles. Drain. Rinse and cool. Add vegetables and blend together.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Fold in chocolate chips and grated German chocolate bar.
Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.	Cool 10 to 15 minutes onto plate and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: catfish stew
directions: Cut fatback meat in pieces and fry until brown.
Drain grease. Next fry onions until tender.
Add fatback, onions and tomato soup in a big pot.
Bring to a boil.
Cut heat down on medium heat; add catfish.
Cover and cook until fish is done.

title: pear relish
directions: Run pears, onions, bell peppers and hot peppers through food chopper.
Mix with sugar, vinegar and spices.
Cook 30 minutes. Discard spices.
Pack in hot, sterile jars.

title: old fashioned peanut brittle
directions: Melt butter or margarine in small saucepan over very low heat. Add peanuts and salt; allow to warm.
Place sugar in large thick skillet over medium heat.
Stir continuously until sugar caramelizes into golden brown syrup.
Stir peanuts into syrup quickly.
Pour onto large buttered surface at once.
With big spoon, stretch and pull candy into thin sheet.
Cool; break into pieces.
Yield:
1 1/2 pounds.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple and pie filling to jello; mix well.
Chill until set.

title: beefy appetizer soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Stir well. Serves 5.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put cubed bread in greased 9 x 9 baking pan.
Beat eggs, add brown sugar, one stick melted butter and cinnamon.	Pour over bread.
Bake one hour at 250°.
Combine sugar and flour.
Add 1 stick melted butter and water.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and pour over baked bread.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Stir in milk. Stir in corn meal, sugar and salt. Bake in preheated 450° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut into squares and serve hot with butter or margarine.
Makes 9 servings.

title: white trash
directions: Toss cereal, raisins and peanuts together.
Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Try to coat well.
Pour 1/2 box of powdered sugar in bottom of grocery bag.
Pour mix in bag.
Pour rest of powdered sugar on top of cereal mixture.
Shake bag vigorously.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Use a medium size casserole dish.
Heat soup and cheese together in a small pot.
Place green beans in casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 onions and bacon bits over the beans.
Pour cheese mixture over top and bake at 350°.
Sprinkle the rest of your onions and bacon bits on top and bake about 5 more minutes. Yield:
8 servings.

title: rice with chicken or turkey and cheese
directions: Measure fat into pan and heat over medium heat.
Add chopped onion and brown slightly.
Add chicken broth to boiling.
Add uncooked rice; stir and reduce heat to low.
Cover pan tightly and cook over low heat 20 minutes.
Add chicken or turkey and cheese. Cook over very low heat until cheese melts and chicken heats.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings, about 3/4 cup each.

title: snack dip
directions: Cook egg, vinegar and sugar until slightly thickened.
Beat into softened cream cheese.
Add chopped vegetables (onion, pimento and pepper).
Mix and refrigerate.
Great with chips, crackers or vegetables.

title: green chilies and rice
directions: Cook rice according to package	directions.
When done, stir in	sour
cream.
Layer
1/2 rice	mixture,
green chilies, 1/2 cheese in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Repeat layers. Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: taco stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 350° for 1 hour (or until done), unwrapped. Cool slightly.
Brown hamburger meat.
Prepare taco seasoning mix according to package directions.
Slice potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop out potato into a large bowl.
Add cooked taco meat and 1 1/2 cups of cheese; mix well.
Spoon potato mixture back into potato skins.
Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Crush Ritz crackers. Melt 1/2 stick butter in casserole. Drain pineapple. Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1/3 cup flour.
Add pineapple. Put in casserole. Cover with Ritz crackers. Melt 1/2 stick butter. Pour over pineapple. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: green bean supreme
directions: Cook onion in margarine.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and sour cream to make a sauce.
Stir in beans and put in casserole dish. Sprinkle with potato chips and top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: To each pound ground chuck, add 3/4 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder, small onion (chopped), 2 slices bread (saturated with milk) and 1 egg.
Mix bread well into meat along with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in loaf pan.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Boil water, sugar and cornstarch until thick and smooth.
Set aside until cool.
Stir in Jell-O and strawberries.
When cool, pour into baked pie shells or graham cracker crumbs.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: banana and black walnut cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg yolks and mix.
Add vanilla, bananas and walnuts.
Mix and add milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold beaten egg whites in last.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Do not preheat oven.)
I like to add a little black walnut flavoring.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Combine dressing and margarine.
Combine soups, milk and chicken broth on stove and cook.
Grease a large casserole dish. Layer 1/2 of dressing and margarine mixture.
Layer chicken, then pour soup mixture over chicken.
Top with other half of dressing and margarine mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: jello pretzel salad
directions: Crust:
Cream 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Add pretzels and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: old fashion ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light, adding sugar and salt gradually.
Beat mixture well.
Add cream and vanilla.
Add milk last.
Allow about 2 1/2 inches for swelling in freezer can.
Freeze in dasher-type old fashion ice cream freezer.

title: creamy corn pudding
directions: In a small skillet, over medium heat, melt 2 teaspoons margarine.
Add onion and green pepper.
Saute until tender.
In a medium bowl, combine eggs, corn, 1/3 cup vanilla wafer crumbs, salt, pepper, pimentos and sauteed vegetables.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Set dish in shallow pan of hot water in oven.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Melt remaining margarine. Mix in remaining wafer crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of casserole and bake 5 minutes more or until done.

title: dump salad
directions: Stir in a large bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.
This is great served plain or on thin sliced cake.

title: pleasant hill eggplant casserole
directions: Cook diced and peeled eggplant in salt water until tender. Mix all ingredients with enough cracker crumbs to make stuffing consistency.
Pour into greased casserole.
Cover top with buttered cracker crumbs and bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mamie rhodes' jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
It will be a little sticky, but not doughy.

title: quick scalloped potatoes
directions: Over medium heat in hot margarine, cook onion until tender. Don't let skillet overheat.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper; heat to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: fettucini carbonara
directions: Cook bacon well and crumble.
Cook fettucini and place in warm serving dish.
Add all remaining ingredients and toss until all fettucini is coated.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Pour tidbits in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar and flour on top.
Add cheese.
Crush the crackers; mix with melted oleo. Pour over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cheesy lamb chops
directions: Set oven control to broil and/or 550°. Broil lamb chops with tops about 3-inches from heat until brown, about 7 minutes. Cut cheese to fit chops. Turn lamb chops. Broil until done, 5 to 7 minutes longer.
Place onion and cheese slice on each lamb chop. Broil until cheese begins to melt, about 30 seconds.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix meat with crumbs, eggs and milk; blend milk.
Make into large balls.
Place in glass baking dish in single layer.
Combine tomato soup, sugar, vinegar and mustard; pour over meatballs.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch or larger pan on bottom and sides with vanilla wafers.
Spoon softened ice cream over the wafers.
Melt chocolate chips in heavy saucepan.
When melted, add the evaporated milk and marshmallows.
Stir constantly and cook until the chocolate mixture is thickened (and marshmallows have melted). Pour over ice cream and sprinkle with pecans.
Freeze until solid.

title: corn casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: nana's spinach and beans
directions: In a saucepan, add 1 cup of water, garlic, oil and some parsley.
When water boils, add spinach and let cook for about 10 minutes.
Add the whole, undrained can of beans.
Cover and let cook for about 20 minutes.

title: microwave corn on the cob
directions: Shuck and wash corn.
Wrap in Saran Wrap.
One corn per wrap. Microwave on High 2 minutes per ear.

title: apricot squares
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Blend in egg.
Add flour, coconut, nuts and salt.
Spread 1/2 mixture into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread with apricot jam.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler and mix well. Cook over simmering water until thick, stirring frequently.
Beat before using.
Serve hot or cold over ice cream.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook full powder (High) for 7 to 9 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add baking soda and stir very quickly and pour onto greased baking sheet.
Cool 15 minutes and break into pieces.

title: haole lomilomi salmon
directions: Shred salmon.
Combine all ingredients and chill for several hours or overnight.
Serve as spread with an assortment of crackers.

title: feta pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with "Healthy Salad Dressing". Refrigerate.
Keeps for about 1 week.

title: liver dumpling soup
directions: *Use your food processor or hand grinder to grind the liver.

title: cantina
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Combine any type of pasta (3 or 4 kinds) and cook until tender; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, chopped pepperoni, mushrooms and green peppers; simmer 30 minutes. After the ground beef has been drained, add to sauce mixture.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Mix together salad dressing, milk, dressing mix and pasta in large shallow bowl.
Arrange remaining ingredients over pasta mixture.
Cover and chill.
Makes 18 servings, about 14 cups.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla, mixing well.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Divide dough into thirds; roll out onto floured surface. Place on lightly greased cookie sheets, about 2 inches apart. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375° until lightly browned.

title: cinnamon diamonds
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar; beat in egg yolk and vanilla. Stir together flour and cinnamon.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Pat into ungreased baking pan.
Brush with egg white.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Lightly press them into the top.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cut into diamond shapes while warm.
Makes 48.

title: nestle crunch cake
directions: Prepare a German chocolate cake according to the package directions.
While still warm, punch holes in the cake (I use the handle of a wooden spoon).
Spread two jars of caramel ice cream topping over the cake.
Cool completely.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Crush Nestle Quick candy bars and sprinkle over top.

title: heavenly flavored pork
directions: Mix all together and cook slowly for 3 hours with lid.
Add water as needed.

title: noodles with character
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add oil, garlic and anise seed and stir until fragrant, about 1 minute. Mix in all remaining ingredients and toss until heated through, approximately 2 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper and serve. Makes four servings.

title: dijon honey dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients together well.
Refrigerate.
Dressing will keep about 3 weeks.
Discard when oil starts to separate. (Minced garlic may be added.)

title: caramel pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and condensed milk until smooth.
Fold in La Creme.
Put 1/4 of the mixture in each shell.
Drizzle with the caramel topping (may be melted in microwave first).
Sprinkle with pecans.
Repeat the layers.
Freeze and serve frozen.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine sugar, water, cinnamon and nutmeg in a saucepan. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add butter.
Set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soups, green beans, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil noodles as directed on package.
Drain and spread in buttered pan while hot.
Add layer of each, chicken, green beans, soup mixture, mushrooms, potato chips and cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: cheesy mostaccioli
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine pasta, meat, soup and spaghetti sauce.
Add pepper, seasoning and 2 cups Mozzarella cheese.
Mix. Place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: green bean casserole(low-fat and sugar-free)
directions: Thaw and drain spinach and green beans.
Combine with onion, water, salt, garlic powder, basil, nutmeg and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir vegetable mixture into beaten eggs; stir mixture well.
Turn into an 8-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes (or bake until set).
Place cheese on top; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 2 to 3 minutes more before serving. Serves 8.

title: apricot bundt cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients together to boiling.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
A family favorite.

title: cheddar cheese potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, butter and salt.
Mix well and in baking dish layer potatoes and cheese.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 40 minutes at 425° until potatoes are tender.

title: strawberry supreme
directions: Mix all of the above and spread in an 8-inch square pan or pie plate.
Bake at 350 for approximately 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes to keep it crumbly and crunchy.
This is not a "pat in" or solid crust.
Let is cool completely before filling.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put chicken in water and cook; remove skin and fat. Take the chicken from the broth and debone. Add butter and bouillon cubes to the broth. In a bowl, add flour, salt, egg and enough warm water to make a soft dough. Roll out on floured surface to about 1/4-inch thick. Cut into strips about 1-inch wide. Drop dumplings into boiling broth. When done, return chicken to the pot. Heat and serve.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir enough to just mix and stir until blended.
Do not overbeat.
Stir in buttermilk.
Then stir in melted margarine and butter extract. Pour in 3 unbaked 9-inch pie shells and bake 40 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken tomato soup
directions: Saute chicken, green pepper, onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add other ingredients, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes. Garnish with sour cream, chopped green onion and Cheddar cheese, grated.

title: lemon pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in slow cooker. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Top with onion and lemon slices. Sprinkle with brown sugar; drizzle with ketchup. Cover and cook on low for 6 hours or until meat juice runs clear.

title: better brussels sprouts
directions: Cut off stem and "X" bottom of each sprout.
Over low heat, melt the butter with olive oil in a large pot.
Add garlic; cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add sprouts; toss with butter mixture.
Add chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Cover; cook for 10 to 15 minutes over low.
Do not overcook.
Drain; return to pot.
Before serving, toss with melted butter and parsley.

title: creamed hamburger
directions: Saute onion in margarine until golden brown.
Stir in beef and cook until crumbly.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Stir and cook for 5 minutes.
Add soup and simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve on baked potatoes, rice or noodles.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with marshmallow cream.
Add food coloring.

title: asparagus ham spirals
directions: Place asparagus in a skillet, add 1/2 inch of water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 3-5 minutes or until crisp and tender. Drain and set aside. Separate crescent dough into four rectangles, seal perforations. Spread cream cheese over each rectangle to with in 1/4 inch of edges. Top each with ham, leaving 1/2 inch uncovered on one long side. Place two asparagus spears along the long side with the ham, roll up and press seam to seal. Cut each roll into seven pieces. Place cut side down one inch apart on greased baking sheets. Combine butter and garlic powder, brush over spirals. Bake at 375 degrees for 10-12 minute or until golden brown. Makes 28 appetizers.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and mashed bananas.
Mix well.
Sift flour and soda together and add to mixture.
Add nuts and mix well.
Pour into greased loaf or tube pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 35 minutes.

title: pizza - healthy
directions: Spray Za bread lightly with olive oil or Pam and spread low-fat no sugar added pasta sauce.
Add your favorite vegetables and top with nonfat shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: salmon bake(crock-pot cooking)
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water, combine all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high for 2 to 4 hours.
Yields 4 servings, about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Cook 30 minutes the first 5 ingredients.
Add cans of cream of celery soup (undiluted) and Velveeta cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.

title: overnight french toast deluxe
directions: Place bread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine eggs, milk, sugar, salt, orange juice and vanilla; beat well.
Pour mixture over bread slices and turn slices to coat evenly.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, melt 2 tablespoons margarine in a large skillet; remove 4 slices bread from dish and saute 4 minutes or until browned on each side.
Repeat procedure with remaining margarine and bread.
Sprinkle with xxxx sugar and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: raspberry torte
directions: Mix like pie crust; press in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: penuche fudge
directions: Boil milk and sugar to form a soft ball stage. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla. Heat mixture until creamy and thickened.
Pour into greased pan. When cooled, cut into squares.

title: round steak and vegetable casserole
directions: Season steak with salt; dip in flour.
Brown steak in oil. Arrange steak in baking dish.
Place vegetables over steak.
Add soups and cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: penny's pizza
directions: Make crust according to directions on package.
Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Spread sauce on crust.
Place 1/2 of pepperoni on sauce, then sausage and hamburger.
Add pepper, onions and garlic powder.
Use 1/2 of cheese on top of this, then the other 1/2 of pepperoni.
Add the remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° until crust is brown and cheese is melted.
Makes 1 large pizza.

title: chocolate mousse napoleons(with strawberries and cream)
directions: 1) Thaw pastry sheet at room temperature, 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

title: chocolate dump cake
directions: Mix cake mix, melted butter and egg.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar, eggs and cocoa.
Blend with mixer.
Pour over cake mix in pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Bake or boil sweet potatoes.
Mash sweet potatoes and add margarine.
Next add sugar, Pet milk, eggs and vanilla.
Taste for desired sweetness.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until pie is firm.

title: watercress omelette
directions: Melt butter in an 8-inch omelette pan or skillet over moderate heat.
Combine eggs, watercress, salt and pepper; add to pan. Cook, lifting the edges with a fork until omelette is done.
Fold omelette in half; turn out onto a serving plate.
Top with sour cream and caviar.
Serves 2.

title: almond pound cake(torta di mandorle)
directions: From my sister, Pauline.

title: homemade syrup
directions: Use saucepan. Brown sugar until light brown. Add water and cook over low fire until thickened. Serve with pancakes or hot biscuits. Easy and delicious.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Mix together buttermilk and soda.
Add flour to creamed mixture with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour. Fold in vanilla, pecans, coconut and beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 round 8 or 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Stir in pineapple and bread cubes.
Pour into greased dish and bake for approximately 45 minutes until top is browned.
Serve hot or cold.
Good with ham.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients.
Bake in an oblong pan at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes. Take out of oven and pour on marshmallow cream.
Put cake back in oven for 10 minutes longer. Remove from oven and let cool.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix
cabbage, green pepper, onion and pimento together. Make a
sauce
of
vinegar, salt, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed
and turmeric.	Bring sauce to boil.
Pour over cabbage. Mix well. Refrigerate 12 hours.
Keeps for weeks.

title: gourmet zucchini
directions: Saute the zucchini, carrots and onions.
Add chicken soup; bring to a boil.
Add sour cream and 1 1/2 cups of stuffing mix. Put in buttered casserole.
Cover with 1/2 cup stuffing mix tossed in softened 1/2 cup margarine on top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: zucchini bisque
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add zucchini, mushrooms, onion and parsley.
Cook over medium heat until vegetables are crispy-tender (6 to 8 minutes).

title: my favorite caramel cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9 1/2-inch) layer pans.
Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Add oil and 2/3 of the milk.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer. Add remaining milk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes longer. Pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until centers spring back when lightly pressed with fingertip.
Cool, then frost.

title: heavenly orange mold(recipe served at club meetings)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of hot water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Let thicken some and then add fruits and Cool Whip. Chill and serve.

title: cranberry mousse pie
directions: In a saucepan, heat cran-raspberry juice cocktail to boiling; remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
In a bowl, beat cranberry sauce with an electric beater on high for 1 minute. Stir in gelatin mixture.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 1/2 hours, until thickened, but not set.
Fold in nondairy whipped topping until mixture is thoroughly blended.
Spoon into dessert dishes or 9-inch prepared pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: velvety custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly stir in hot milk.
Pour at once into pie shell. Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake pie 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Chop nuts and fruits.
Put in large bowl and dredge with 3/4 cup flour; set aside.
Grease and line tube pan with waxed paper.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Cook the first 6 ingredients until tender (about 30 minutes). Add the cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add the soup. Return to the heat 5 to 10 minutes on low. Stir in the milk.
If desired, garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: celia's lasagna
directions: Brown the first 4 ingredients, salt and pepper to taste.
In a saucepan, mix the tomato juice, paste, mushroom soup, celery salt and sugar.
Add in browned ingredients; simmer until thickened (approximately 3 hours).
Boil 10 to 12 lasagna noodles for 8 minutes; drain and rinse.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, place sauce on bottom, noodles, sauce, cheese, noodles, sauce, cheese and noodles until all used.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, covered with foil, then for 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Blend in blender.
Cook for 7 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes; add Certo and put in jars.

title: delectables(need we say more)
directions: Melt chocolate and butter slowly in a double boiler.
Remove from heat and combine with all ingredients.
Spoon into tiny paper baking cups that have been placed in muffin tins about half full. Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Yields 36.

title: barbara's chicken, chicken soup
directions: Place chicken in large casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.
Enjoy.

title: good morning coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar and salt; cut in shortening until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture.
To remaining crumb mixture, add baking powder, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat on medium 2 minutes.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until set.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add confectioners sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Freeze.
Set out to slightly soften before serving.

title: molasses stack cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses.
Sift flour. Add spices and sift again.
Mix.
Bake in thin layers, 3 tablespoons per layer.
Stack with applesauce or dried apple or apples of your choice.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: microwave stuffed mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch glass pie plate.
Add onion and cook in microwave for 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients except mushrooms.
Stuff mushroom caps; pile mixture high.
Put 8 mushrooms on paper plate and cover with wax paper.
Cook 2 minutes in microwave.
Serve.

title: clam chowder
directions: In large pot, gently saute pork until rendered.
Remove pork and add butter.
Stir over low heat.
When bubbly, add onions and continue sauteing until transparent.
Add cubed potatoes and cook about 5 minutes, stirring to keep moist.
Add flour and cook an additional 3 minutes or so, again stirring well.
Add clam juice and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add chopped clams and cream and heat through, taking care not to bring to a boil.
When well heated, serve.

title: apricot delight
directions: Mix and stir first 3 ingredients until melted.
Add the 2 cups cold water and refrigerate to thicken.
When slightly thick, add crushed pineapple, drained.
Save pineapple juice for sauce.
Add bananas.
Jell until firm.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick, sausage and cheese together, mixing well.
Add milk and blend.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut shell or smaller.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 100 to 150 sausage balls.
Great to serve for breakfast or lunch!

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender; debone.
Reserve 2 cups of broth. Combine chicken, soup and broth in large casserole dish; add vegetables, if desired.
Top with dough and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom

title: elegant italian chicken(easy but elegant!)
directions: Mix the cream cheese, soup and wine together.
Set aside.
In frying pan, melt 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle in the Italian salad dressing mix.
Lightly saute chicken in pan.
Place in greased casserole dish. Top
with sauce mixture. Bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes. Remove foil and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry bars($25,000 pillsbury bakeoff winner)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using solid shortening (not oil) grease and flour 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: fruit stuffed pork
directions: Cut pork loin lengthwise in 1/2, but not all the through. Open and spread flat.
Arrange apricots and prunes down center. Fold pork in original shape.
Secure with toothpicks.

title: chocolate-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Blend in chocolate, flavorings and 2 tablespoons water.
Mix flour, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt; stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and nuts. Form into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with sugared bottom of tumbler.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the gelatin and water together in a large bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased mold or Bundt pan.
Chill until set.

title: onion rice
directions: Clean rice with water.
Put into big ovenproof bowl.
Add 3 cups boiling water, onion soup mix and margarine.
Mix together. Put in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: 40 clove chicken felice
directions: Place chicken into 9 x 13-inch baking dish, skin side up. Sprinkle all ingredients evenly over chicken.
Squeeze juice from lemon and sprinkle over top.
Cut remaining lemon rind into pieces and arrange throughout.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove foil and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Mix flour, oleo and pecans.
Mix and press in greased pan. Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup whipped topping and pour over cooled mixture.
Chill.
Next mix lemon instant pudding and milk.
Whip until thick and pour on cream cheese.
Top with whipped cream if desired.

title: picture-perfect turkey in 45 minutes
directions: Rub turkey with mixture of seasonings, inside and out.
Heat 1 1/2 cups vegetable oil in a large deep fryer to 375°.
Gently lower bird into hot oil with breast up.
Cook 4 1/2 minutes; turn frequently.
Bird will not brown until it is done internally.

title: bottom's up gingerbread
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Chop up nuts over butter. Sprinkle nuts.
Pour apple pie filling over butter.
Prepare gingerbread mix as directed.
Pour mix over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Turn on platter.
Top with Cool Whip.
Yields 45 cookies.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Layer these and add fried onion rings on top.
Brown until cooked.

title: old fashioned cheese potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter or margarine. Add flour, salt and pepper. Cook and stir until a thick paste forms.
Gradually add milk. Cook and stir until the mixture begins to thicken. Add cheese. Cook and stir until melted.
Place potatoes in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or baking dish.
Pour sauce over the potatoes. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour or until the potatoes are tender.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: mexican chicken bake
directions: Cube chicken.
Mix mushroom soup, milk, chiles and onion together.
Place 1 cup crushed Doritos in bottom of greased shallow casserole dish.
Next, place half the chicken.
Cover it with half of soup mixture.

title: crab won tons
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Place 1 teaspoon of mixture in center of wrapper and seal according to directions on package.
Deep fat fry in hot oil until golden brown.
These freeze well, too!

title: cracker candy
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil and spray with Pam.
Boil sugar and butter for 3 minutes.
Place saltine crackers on foil with edges touching.
Pour mix of sugar and butter over crackers. Bake in oven at 400° for 4 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over and put back in oven for 1 minute.
Take out, spread chocolate chips over crackers and refrigerate to harden.

title: white chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugars; beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg and mix well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Blend in vanilla; stir in chocolate and nuts.
Chill for 1 hour.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let stand a few minutes before removing.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: fig preserves
directions: Mash figs; simmer boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Put into jars.

title: appetizer
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in cheese until thoroughly melted. Spread on loaves of party rye.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions on package until just tender.
Drain.
Place in a greased casserole.
Mix onion, celery, cheese, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Spread over vegetables. Melt oleo and mix with Ritz crackers crumbs.
Spread on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: low-fat chocolate cake
directions: Lightly grease and flour two 8 x 1 1/2-inch or 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans.
Stir together flour, cocoa powder and baking soda.
In large mixer bowl beat margarine or butter with electric mixer on medium speed about 30 seconds.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until well combined.
Add egg and egg white, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each.
Stir in yogurt.
Add dry ingredients and cold water alternately to beaten mixture, beating on low speed after each addition just until combined.
Pour batter into baking pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes for 9-inch layers or 30 to 35 minutes for 8-inch layers or until a wooden toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes on wire racks, then remove from pans.
Cool.

title: modern marble cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening with sugar until fluffy.
Beat eggs thoroughly and add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately, beating well.
Add vanilla. Divide batter into halves.
Melt chocolate and add with 2 tablespoons milk to one half; blend well.
Drop batter by tablespoons into greased pan, alternating white and chocolate. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
The fun of baking a marble cake is to see what designs come through.

title: berry good smoothie
directions: Combine the juice and banana in a blender. Add in strawberries according to desired thickness. Blend until smooth.

title: smoked sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients (except sausage) together in crock-pot. Cut sausage into thin slices and mix into sauce.
Cook about 15 minutes on high setting.
Turn off and let stand about 12 hours. Turn crock-pot on (low setting) about 3 hours before serving. Serves about 25 persons.

title: applesauce gingerbread
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in sugar and molasses.
Add eggs, then beat in applesauce.
Sift flour, soda, ginger and cinnamon into mixture.
Blend well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fried chicken batter
directions: Mix in cup and pour over chicken. Let meat soak in this marinade for up to 6 hours. Salt and pepper to taste. Roll in flour and deep-fry.

title: kraut salad relish
directions: Toss ingredients and cover.
Chill 4 to 12 hours.
Toss again and drain before serving with entree of your choice.
Good with outdoor barbecue.
Will keep well in refrigerator.

title: stuffed pizza florentine
directions: Preparation Time: 20 to 25 minutes.
Cooking Time: 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: quick orange nut bread
directions: In large bowl, sift flour with sugar, baking powder, allspice, salt and baking soda.
Beat egg thoroughly and combine with orange rind, juice and melted butter.
Add liquid to flour mixture all at once.
Stir only until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) in preheated 350° oven for about 50 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: delicious swiss steak
directions: Mix together mustard, flour and salt.
Pound dry mixture into steak; cover both sides.
Brown both sides.
Cover meat with onions, carrots and tomatoes.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce, salt and brown sugar over all in long pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: dot's chicken
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Spray casserole with nonstick vegetable spray.
Arrange chicken in baking pan.
Slice oranges, then cut into half moons; do not peel.
Tuck orange slices around the chicken; save some for garnish.
Stir together honey, lemon juice, mustard, curry and ginger.
Pour about half the mixture over the chicken.
Bake chicken at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: "you name it" dessert
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Add chopped nuts (optional) and serve.

title: hot butterscotch punch
directions: Melt brown sugar in a 2-quart pan over medium low heat while stirring.
Add hot water and bring the mixture to the boiling point.
Add butter and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Add milk and heat. Blend in salt and vanilla extract.
Garnish with cream ground nutmeg.
This is an alternative to hot cocoa and tastes good in the winter!

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually beat in sugar, then oil. Combine dry ingredients. Add to egg mixture alternately with zucchini.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Turn into greased and floured 9-inch tube pan. Bake at 450° for 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes. Turn out and cool.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 of the M&M's.
Reserve the rest of the M&M's for decorating.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate with the remaining M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: savory baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into large casserole dish. Bake, covered, in a 325° oven for 3 hours, stirring occasionally. Uncover for the last 1/2 hour of baking.

title: fresh vegetable marinade
directions: Remove flowerets from broccoli; cut in bite-size pieces. Combine broccoli, mushrooms and all vegetables.
Toss lightly. Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour over vegetables. Garnish with celery leaves and cherry tomatoes.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: orange fruit salad
directions: Mix the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix all remaining ingredients with above.
Refrigerate.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook mushrooms, garlic, celery, onion and green pepper in 1/4 cup butter until tender.
Combine with remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup butter and place in a greased casserole.
Pour remaining melted butter over casserole and bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except langostinos.
Heat on medium heat and add langostinos.
Stir and serve.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apples in baking dish.
Combine flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, oats and pecans in bowl; mix well.
Add margarine; mix well.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Fry the sausage; drain and rinse off grease. Melt the cream cheese and sausage together. Use 13 x 9-inch pan. Open 1 package of crescent rolls and line the bottom of the pan. Add sausage-cream cheese mixture on top. Layer the top with crescent rolls like a pie top. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat together sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla, salt and cinnamon. Add flour and soda and beat.
Stir in nuts and raw apples. The batter will be stiff.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Cool and frost.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Cook until thick pudding, jello and hot water.
Cool completely.
Add mandarin oranges and whipped topping and mix all together and refrigerate.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Cook first five ingredients until tender.
Add 1 cup grated cheese and eggs.
Spread rolls in greased glass pie plate.
Pour in mixture.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: oreo supreme
directions: Mix and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan 30 Oreo cookies crushed, 3/4 stick melted margarine.
Soften 1/2 gallon of vanilla ice cream and spread over Oreo crust.
Put in freezer and let harden.
Mix in saucepan, chocolate squares, 2 tablespoons margarine, sugar, evaporated milk.
Boil for 8 minutes and let cool.
Spread over ice cream and place in freezer to harden.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with grated Oreos if desired.
Keep in freezer.
Yummy.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat, bell pepper, onion, chili powder and cumin seed. Drain and set aside.
Chop tomato and lettuce; set aside.
On low heat, melt cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Crunch bag of Fritos.
Mix all ingredients when ready to serve.

title: banana split pie
directions: Slice bananas and place in bottom of pie crust.
Then put drained pineapple over bananas.
Mix pudding as directed and add cream cheese.
Pour over bananas.
Chill 2 hours.
Add whipped cream, nuts and cherries and serve.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed. With large fork, poke holes throughout cake. Pour coconut milk over cake until saturated. Refrigerate 2 hours. Spoon pineapple on top first, then add Cool Whip over top of pineapple. Sprinkle coconut over top of Cool Whip. Refrigerate for 45 minutes.
Serve. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In large frying pan, saute onions, bell pepper and garlic in 1 tablespoon olive oil until tender.
Pour into large Dutch oven. Then brown meat and add to onions, pepper and garlic.
Mix tomatoes, tomato paste and sugar into meat and vegetable mixture. Cook, covered, on high until mixture starts to bubble, watching carefully.
Turn down to low and cook 4 hours, stirring every now and then.
Serve over cooked spaghetti noodles.
Serves about 8.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix banana pudding mix with milk. Layer oblong dish with wafers, then sliced bananas. Add layer of pudding; repeat until ending with pudding on top. Crumble a handful of wafers on top of pudding for decoration.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together a day ahead and let it marinate (refrigerate) overnight.
Prior to serving, mix remaining 1/4 bottle Viva Italian dressing.
Toss or mix good.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Peel onions; slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Separate into rings. Sift flour with baking powder, salt and sugar.
Combine milk, egg and fat; add to dry ingredients all at once.
Beat until smooth. Dip onion rings in batter; fry until golden brown in deep fat at 375°.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Sprinkle with additional salt. Yields 4 servings.

title: fat-free peach cobbler(serves 10)
directions: Save out 9 tablespoons of peach juice from canned peaches. Set aside.
Place all remaining peaches and juice in pot over medium heat; stir occasionally.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking soda and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In another bowl, thoroughly beat banana until no large pieces remain.
Add in peach juice and skim milk.
Mix well.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients (not the warming peach mixture).
Mix together well.
Set aside. When peach mixture begins to bubble, add in potato flakes and stir constantly for about a minute.
Pour peach mixture into an 11 x 15-inch pan.
Drop dough mixture by large spoonfuls onto the top of peaches.
Place in 350° oven for about 25 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean from the biscuits.
Let stand after cooking for an hour or more.
Serve warm with fat-free frozen vanilla yogurt or ice cream.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery, raisins and walnuts.
Mix together lemon juice, yogurt, mayonnaise, honey and salt.
Stir until well blended.
Add dressing to apple mixture, mix well and chill. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, shortening and sugars. Add eggs; beat well. Add flour, cream of tartar and vanilla. Mix well. Drop by 1/2 teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: stir-fried vegetables
directions: Combine soy sauce, oyster sauce, white wine, sesame oil and pepper.
Mix well and set aside.
Combine mushrooms and hot water in a small bowl; let stand 15 minutes.
Drain.
Remove and discard stems.
Thinly slice caps.
Set aside.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and
mash.
Mix sugar, mayonnaise, onions, egg, salt and pepper
together and combine with squash.
Place in a casserole dish and
top
with cracker crumbs, grated cheese and 1/2 stick butter.
Cook in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frosting
directions: Blend shortening and sugar together.
Add salt, water and extracts.
Whip on medium speed with mixer.

title: ted's pie crust
directions: Mix and sift flour, sugar and salt; blend in Crisco with fork until well balled like small BB's.
Add ice water, knead and roll out to size needed.

title: yellow pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, one cup at a time and cream well. Add eggs, two at a time, creaming well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt, then add to batter, mixing well.
Add lemon and vanilla.
Pour batter into a tube cake pan.
Bake in preheated oven 40 minutes at 275°.
Then turn heat to 300° and bake 50 to 60 minutes longer.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "vegetable soup"
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion until meat is brown.
Add rest of ingredients and desired amount of water.
Let simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature and mix in sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Enjoy with apple slices!

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in order given.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Dissolve brown sugar in water.
Add butter. Stir until butter is melted.
Slowly pour over raisin mixture. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter.
Mix until smooth.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles.
Seal perforation.
Add 1/2 cup of mixture to center of rectangle.
Wrap the crescent roll around the mixture and seal well.
Brush tops of chicken squares with small amount of melted butter.
Bake in an ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°, until golden brown.
Makes 4 squares.

title: potato cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Heat skillet; use cooking oil. Spoon out potato mixture to make 2 to 3-inch cakes.
Brown on each side over medium heat.

title: sweet potato-pork chop casserole
directions: Brown the pork chops in small amount of fat in a skillet. Place in a large casserole and sprinkle with half the salt and pepper.
Place sweet potatoes over chops and sprinkle with remaining salt and pepper.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Lightly blend together in a bowl ice cream and milk.
Add pudding.
Beat until just mixed, one minute.
Pour at once into a pie shell.
Let stand in refrigerator about 1 hour before serving.

title: no cook play dough(for children)
directions: Add food coloring to water before mixing into dough.
Slowly add water to dry ingredients until desired consistency.
Store in refrigerator.
If play dough gets gooey, just add more flour.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Place pineapple in bottom of baking dish.
Place blueberries on top of pineapple. Sprinkle sugar on blueberries.
Cover with cake mix (dry).
Sprinkle chopped pecans to cover.
Add melted margarine to top of pecans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: mallow fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: pecan pies
directions: Preheat oven at 350° for 10 minutes, then turn oven down to 275° and cook for an hour.

title: crabmeat spread dip
directions: Drain crabmeat.
Mix the crabmeat with cocktail sauce.
Let cream cheese soften.
Spread on the bottom of a serving plate. Then spread crabmeat over the cream cheese.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: potato onion soup
directions: Boil potatoes.
Pour off water and save.
Mash potatoes.
Fry bacon crisp.
Remove and fry onions in drippings.
Remove and add to mashed potatoes.
Add potato water, milk, butter and seasonings.

title: chocolate mint cookies
directions: Melt 1 cup mint chocolate chips.
In large bowl cream butter and sugar.
Add melted mint chips and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add remaining mint chips; stir well.
Dough will be soft.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap; freeze until firm (about 20 minutes).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: just for kids magic mud slime
directions: Spoon cornstarch into a small bowl.
Add water and food coloring; stir.
It should be difficult to stir even when the water and cornstarch are fully mixed.
If it is too runny add more cornstarch; if crumbly, add water.
Store in airtight container. When you press the slime it feels solid because you squeeze out some water.
When you stop squeezing, water flows back again and it becomes runny.

title: taco casserole
directions: Salt meat and brown in small amount of fat until done.
Season with chili powder.
Drain off excess fat.
Crush 3/4 of Doritos and spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Spread meat mixture evenly over Doritos; chop onion and spread over meat mixture, spread beans over this mixture.
Spread soup over beans, spread tomatoes over soup.
Grate cheese and spread over tomatoes and crush rest of Doritos and spread over cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
(This and a salad makes a meal.)

title: fried cheese meltaways
directions: In a large frying pan, heat 2 inches of oil to 375°.
In mixing bowl, mix Bisquick, milk and egg; beat with hand beaters until smooth.
Dredge cheese cubes in Bisquick, coating them lightly.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, cocoa powder, salt, baking powder and soda.
In mixer bowl, beat together butter and sugar on low speed of electric mixer until fluffy. Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well. Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture; beat until well blended.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press down center of dough with thumb.
Drain cherries, reserving juice.
Place a
cherry in the center of each cookie.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease casserole well with butter; casserole dish should be 4-quart size.
Add 1 1/2 cups uncooked rice.
Slice onion very thin and place over top of rice.
Salt, pepper and paprika 8 or 9 pieces of chicken and place over onion and rice (straight from water).
Top with 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 can chicken broth (Swanson).
Stir top ingredients gently into the rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli, drain and arrange in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 6.

title: pork-rice casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in a skillet, seasoning to taste.
Put in one layer
in	a
shallow 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, then cover the pork chops with mixture. Cover baking dish
with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes to
1 hour
and 30 minutes.
After 2/3 of the cooking time, add a little more water if the rice needs more moisture.

title: marie date roll
directions: Stir the sugars and milk constantly until forms a soft ball. Stir in the dates and cook to hard ball.
Add the nuts, butter and vanilla. Beat until it holds shape.
Pour out on a damp cloth and work into a roll. Chill and slice.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix together, shape into a ball and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: basic beaver
directions: Sprinkle serving size pieces of beaver with seasoned salt. Mix Dale's, liquid smoke and water in large cast-iron skillet and bring to simmer.
Add beaver pieces to skillet and cook until tender.
Remove.
Clean skillet.
Add bacon drippings and reheat. Batter cooked pieces of beaver in flour and return to skillet. Fry to a golden brown.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking dish, 8 x 8-inches.
Cook and stir ground beef until brown.
Drain.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, cheese and onion.
Mix baking mix and water to soft dough.
Pat in pan; press 1/2 inch up sides.
Layer beef, tomatoes and green pepper in pan.
Spoon sour cream over top.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake until edges of dough are brown, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add sugar, eggs, Wesson oil and grated carrots.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven (layers).

title: festive fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Place fruit and almonds in layers in a shallow baking dish.
Set aside.

title: autumn soup
directions: *One 28 ounce can tomatoes can be substituted; reduce water to 3 cups.

title: topped strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add strawberries and pineapple. Chill until set.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar.
Add in Cool Whip and blend well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: sister farmer's famous coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, sugar, flour and baking powder together.
Add butter, milk and egg yolks.
Beat with mixer real good.
Add flavors and beat well.
Cook until done.
Use 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Frost when cake is cooled.

title: m y f cheese nachos
directions: Melt cheese and add chilies.
Can put in crock-pot.
Pour over nacho chips or Doritos.

title: classic macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl combine mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add noodles, celery, green pepper, tomato, onion and cucumber.
Toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.
