Makes 5 cups.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Toss together bread crumbs and pineapple chunks and place in a greased 2-quart dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican chip dip
directions: Layer in a 9 x 9-inch pan, starting with cream cheese, then spread chili on next.
Pour as much or as little picante sauce over.
Top with plenty of cheese; a mixture of Monterey Jack and Cheddar is good.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: elephant balls
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, peanut butter and Rice Krispies together with your hands (shape into balls).
Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler and add paraffin as needed.
Dip balls in chocolate and let set until cool.

title: chicken and ham casserole
directions: Wipe chicken breasts with damp cloth.
In a large skillet, bring broth to boiling.
Add chicken breasts; reduce heat and simmer, covered, 20 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken; reserve broth.

title: molasses coconut chews
directions: Cream together the white and brown sugar and the shortening. Add the beaten eggs, vanilla and molasses.
Beat well.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt and stir in.
Stir in coconut flakes.
Shape into small balls and place on greased cookie sheet about 3 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit kabobs
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries.
Peel kiwi fruit; cut in chunks same size as cherries or pineapple.
Place on picks the kiwi, cherry and pineapple.

title: shortribs with tomatoes and bacon
directions: Sprinkle shortribs with paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat with flour.
Cook bacon in Dutch oven about 5 minutes.
Remove bacon using slotted spoon and reserve.
Working in batches, brown shortribs on all sides; set aside.
Add onions and garlic to Dutch oven; over medium heat, cook until tender, about 8 minutes.
Mix in tomato paste and 4 teaspoons rosemary.
Add wine and bring to boil until liquid is reduced by half (about 6 minutes).
Add tomatoes and broth.
Return shortribs, any juices and bacon to Dutch oven; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until tender, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Uncover and simmer until liquid is slightly thickened, about 30 minutes.
(Can be made 1 day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.
Re-warm over medium heat, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes.)
Add peas to shortribs; simmer, uncovered, until peas are crisp-tender, about 2 to 3 minutes. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons rosemary.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Combine water with rice and onion soup in oblong casserole. Lay chicken on top.
Add cream of chicken soup over chicken.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°, uncovered.

title: hermits
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, molasses and water.
Beat eggs and reserve 1 teaspoon to coat top of herbs for glazing.
Add flour, soda and spices which have been sifted together.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Divide dough into long rolls on greased cookie sheet. Coat top with remainder of egg.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cut on the bias.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Marinate sauerkraut and mayonnaise for 30 minutes.
Arrange pieces of turkey, swiss cheese and corned beef on 6 buttered slices of rye bread.
Spread 1/3 cup marinate kraut on each slice of bread.

title: turkey burgers(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Form into 4 ounce patties.
Lay on a broiler pan and broil for 3 to 4 minutes per side, or grill until done.
Makes 4 (4 ounce) patties.

title: jamaican rice and peas
directions: Make 1	quart
of
coconut
milk
by
adding water to 1 grated coconut.
Strain through sieve.
Wash red beans. Add to milk with 2
pegs
of garlic.
Boil until tender.
Add thyme, hot pepper and
green	onion;	salt
to
taste.
Simmer for 2 minutes. Add washed rice (liquid should be about 1 inch above rice).
Bring
to a	boil,
cover
and cook on low heat until liquid
disappears and
rice
is
cooked.
Serve with Chicken Fricassee and boiled or fried plantain.

title: roasted mustard potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray roasting pan 3 times to coat with vegetable oil.
Put the mustard, paprika, cumin, chili powder and cayenne pepper in a large bowl.
Whisk to blend.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up lettuce, cauliflower and onions into small pieces. Crumble bacon on top.
Mix Miracle Whip and sugar in bowl. Dribble on top of cauliflower mixture; let set overnight.
Toss when ready to serve.

title: southern chocolate gravy
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Add milk.
Stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Reduce heat to low for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve over biscuits.

title: festive green pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Add bacon, onion and cheese.
Mix milk, mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar.
Add to peas.
Stir gently.
Garnish with pimento.
Serves 8 to 10.
Good potluck dish.
Can make ahead of time.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Combine pudding, sugar, milk and margarine into a saucepan. Cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a full boil.
Lower heat and boil slowly for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in Planters peanuts.
Beat until candy thickens (about 15 minutes). Quickly drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper forming clusters. Makes about 24.
Refrigerate.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix eggs with sugar and shortening.
Mix flour, potato chips and vanilla.
I roll in little balls and press down with a fork. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: meat ball sauce
directions: Take 1 cup of friendship and add 2 cups of thoughtfulness. Cream smoothly with a pinch of gentleness and a dash of powdered kindness.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut, flour and pound round steak.
Then brown each piece of meat in a little oil.
When well browned, cover with a mixture of canned tomatoes, celery, onion, carrots, bay leaf, garlic powder and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover pan and cook on low heat for 1 1/2 hours.

title: party salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, measuring 1/2 cup syrup.
Add to Jell-O.
Chill until very thick.
Fold in pineapple, cheese, cherries and almonds.
Pour into individual molds or 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice and water until rice is tender.
Simmer until water is gone.
Put into a 2-quart casserole the other ingredients.
Add cooked rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let set in oven 10 more minutes.

title: strawberry ice cream pie
directions: Blend crumbs and butter.
Press firmly on bottom and around sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 or 2 hours.

title: butter fingers
directions: Mix in the order listed. When mixed thoroughly, chill dough about 45 minutes or 1 hour.
Shape like fingers and bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar after cooling some, but while still warm.
Store in an airtight container and keep in a cool place.
Nice for the holidays.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine and mix thoroughly.
Pack into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: gobble goodies
directions: With a parent's help, melt the margarine over medium heat in a large saucepan.
Add the marshmallows and stir the mixture until the marshmallows are completely melted.
Remove the pan from the heat and stir in the cereal.
Stir the mixture until the cereal is well coated.
Cool the mixture for 10 minutes.
While it's cooling, twist apart some sandwich cookies.
Butter your hands and shape the cereal mixture into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Frost the inside of the cookie halves that have no filling on them.
Press candy corns into the frosting in the shape of a fan.
Add a little frosting below the candy corns.
Then press a cereal ball into the center of each cookie.
Spread frosting on remaining cookie halves and stick them to the bottoms of the cereal balls.
Put a dab of frosting on a candy corn and stick it onto the cereal ball to make the turkey's head.
Repeat for each turkey.
Use the turkeys to decorate your family's Thanksgiving table.
(And when you're through with dinner, gobble them up.)

title: three-cheese pie
directions: Mix cheeses, onion and flour.
Spread in greased pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Beat eggs slightly; beat in milk, salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Cook, uncovered, in a 350° oven until set, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes. Arrange tomato slices around edge of pie, overlapping slices slightly.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook ingredients together and put in unbaked 2 crust pie shell. Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in bowl.
Add soup and shortening. Beat at low to medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and water. Beat 2 minutes more.
Add optional ingredients.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch pan bake 35 to 40 minutes; tube pan bake 1 hour).

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat eggs; add milk and butter and mix into dry ingredients. Pour into muffin pans.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425°.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together.
Just before serving, add 3 quarts of ginger ale.
Add ice.

title: mexican dip salad
directions: Put in layers the bean dip, green chilies, guacamole, sour cream mixed with taco seasoning, cheese, olives and tomatoes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat margarine and syrup in saucepan and set aside.
In mixing bowl, mix sugar and eggs together.
Pour warm syrup mixture over eggs and sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well. brush 1 egg white on unbaked pie crusts.
Spread pecans in bottom of pie crusts.
Pour above mixture in crusts over pecans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pie crust
directions: Measure flour into a large bowl.
Add lard.
Mix until crumbly with mixer.
Add water and salt; mix well with a fork.
Roll out on floured board.
Makes 5 crusts.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs; beat well.
Gradually add dry ingredients and milk.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when testing.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Spread bread cubes in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over bread cubes.
Blend slightly beaten eggs, milk, salt, mustard, onion powder and pepper.
Pour this mixture over the bread and cheese.
Bake at 325° until egg mixture is set, about 40 to 45 minutes.
In the meantime, fry 10 slices bacon until crisp.
Sprinkle on casserole during the last 10 minutes of baking.
Serves 10.

title: work of art fruit pizza
directions: Combine all glaze ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Stir until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture boils.
Boil for 1 minute.
Cool and spoon over pies.
Yields 2 fruit pies.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Line muffin tin with foil cupcake liners.
Place one vanilla wafer in each liner.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour over wafers, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Remove from pan when cooled. Chill for 2 hours. Top with fruit or pie filling.

title: rich caramel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: joyce's chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then turn oven to 350° and bake until set, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: kentucky apple cake
directions: Beat eggs with a mixer until thick and light. Combine sugar and oil. Pour into eggs with mixer on medium speed. Stir together flour and cinnamon, then add to egg mixture with vanilla. Beat to mix. Stir
in walnuts. Spread apples in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Pour batter over apples, spreading to cover. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Remove from oven and cool. Spread with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: irish scones
directions: Measure and mix the flour, sugar and soda.
Cut in margarine until well mixed and grainy looking.
In a separate bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups buttermilk and beaten egg.
Add raisins.

title: cheese soup
directions: Bring water and salt to boil; add carrots, celery and potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Cook onion in margarine; add flour, milk and chicken broth.
When smooth, add cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add vegetables plus the water they were cooked in. Makes 2 1/2 quarts, about 5 servings.

title: hot tuna-macaroni toss(try a hot salad for a change)
directions: Cook macaroni following package directions.
Drain.
In skillet, mix Italian dressing, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Heat just to boiling.
Add drained macaroni, tuna, celery and green pepper.
Toss and heat through.
Stir in mayonnaise. Top with green pepper rings.
Serve hot. Serves four.

title: marshmallow delight
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in milk on stove in top of double boiler until they are thoroughly melted, then set aside to cool.
Whip the cream.
Roll graham crackers fine and put 1/2 of them in bottom of pan (9 x 13-inch).
When the pineapple is well drained, add to marshmallow mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon mixture on crumbs and sprinkle rest of crumbs on top.
Place in refrigerator about 8 hours so as to serve cold.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil together until forms soft ball in cold water. Remove from heat. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. DO NOT BEAT. STIR.

title: congealed ambrosia salad
directions: Dissolve orange Jell-O and sugar in the hot water.
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Place in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours to congeal.
Serves 8.

title: supreme squash casserole
directions: Place croutons in bottom of casserole dish.
Spread mixture on top.
Cover with cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple coleslaw
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and milk. Place cabbage and pineapple in a large salad bowl; add dressing and toss. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Defrost hash browns.
Add 1/2 cup butter, salt and pepper and mix together.
Add sour cream, grated cheese, soup and onions; blend.
Pour into 3 quart casserole dish.

title: triple good bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In medium saucepan, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat; cool slightly and set aside.
Beat sugar, margarine and vanilla until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients; blend until evenly mixed and crumbly.
Reserve 2 cups.
Press remaining mixture onto bottom of prepared pan. Spread raisin mixture to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Sprinkle with remaining oat mixture; pat lightly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2-inch bars.

title: sesame seed baked chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in dressing overnight in refrigerator.
One hour before serving, preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in flat pan.
Roll chicken in seed.
Place in pan.
Bake for 30 minutes. Turn chicken; bake 30 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: life
directions: Mix thoroughly with tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy for others.
Fold in 5 cups of prayers and 4 cups of faith to lighten other ingredients and to raise the texture to great heights of Christian living.
After pouring all this into your daily life, bake well with the warmth of human kindness.
I serve with a smile.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan, bring to hard boil and stir constantly. Boil one minute. Cool. Add vanilla and beat until creamy.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix eggs, milk, soup, cheese and mushrooms in a bowl. In cooking dish, layer sausage then hash browns. Pour liquids over the top Refrigerate 1 hour before cooking. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When completely cooled, cut in squares.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together soups and Veg-All; add chicken breasts.
Use Pillsbury Ready-Crust.
Bake bottom crust about 7 to 8 minutes. Pour in mixture and add top crust.
Prick crust to vent.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, butter and pecans.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook on 325° until done, then let cool.
Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar together and spread on top of cake layer.
Then spread raspberries on top of that.
Spread raspberry frosting on top of that.
Refrigerate.

title: aunt mattie's cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover and let stand in refrigerator until fully chilled.
Serve over lettuce.

title: st. mark's soup
directions: Brown beef and onion; add other ingredients and simmer.
Good made in a crock-pot.

title: cranberry-raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry and lemon gelatins in boiling water.
Stir in frozen raspberries, breaking up large pieces.
Break up cranberry sauce with fork; stir into gelatin mixture.
Chill until partially set.
Carefully pour in lemon-lime beverage, stirring gently.
Turn into 6-cup mold.
Chill 5 to 6 hours or overnight. Unmold on crisp greens.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: beef tips
directions: In a crock-pot set on low heat, mix stew meat, soups and water.
Cook all day until tender.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Stir corn syrup and sugar in heavy pan over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat; add butter and chocolate.
Cool slightly.
Beat in eggs, salt and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes or until when knife inserted comes out clean.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Combine carrots and water in a medium saucepan; cover and cook over medium heat 15 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain, reserving liquid; add enough water to liquid to make 3 tablespoons. Set carrots aside.
Combine carrots, liquid, orange juice and the next 4 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook for 1 minute or until thickened.
Add carrots; cook 1 minute, stirring well.
Transfer to serving dish.
Yields 4 servings (about 68 calories per 1/2 cup serving).

title: spring garden special
directions: Saute onions and meat until thoroughly cooked.
Add tomatoes and seasonings and cook for a short time.
Add green beans and carrots.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: linguica puffs
directions: Brown linguica and add to Cheddar cheese and Bisquick.
Mix well and then add water.
Batter will be on the sticky side.
Make into balls and flatten on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: holiday vegetable medley
directions: Thaw vegetables and saute with onion in 3 tablespoons oleo or butter.
Mix soup and sour cream well, then fold in 1 cup of croutons.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat remaining croutons in 1 tablespoon of oleo until covered and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pasta fagioli
directions: Saute beef in oil in large pot until beef starts to brown. Add onions, carrots, celery and tomatoes and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse beans and add to the pot.
Then, add beef stock, oregano, pepper, Tabasco, spaghetti sauce and pasta. Simmer until celery and carrots are tender - about 45 minutes. Makes about 4 1/2 quarts of soup.

title: hot spice tea
directions: Combine.
To serve, mix with hot boiling water.
Store in tight jar.

title: granny's potato soup
directions: Cook first five ingredients together.
Mix together flour, salt and pepper.
Make a hole in flour and break 1 egg.
Mix together so that mixture looks like pie crust before adding water. These are called rivels.
When potatoes are cooked, add milk and let come to a full boil.
Add rivels and let cook for a few minutes (approximately 5 to 10 minutes).

title: mocha pound cake
directions: Slice cake horizontally into 3 layers.
Place on serving plate. Chop candy into fine pieces, reserving 2 tablespoons.
Fold remaining candy into whipped topping.
Stir in coffee powder. Spread between layers and over and side of cake.
Sprinkle with reserved candy.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Cream the first three ingredients.
Add eggs and mix well. Add milk, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until middle of pie does not shake.

title: black forest parfaits
directions: Pour milk into small mixer bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat at lowest speed of electric mixer until well blended (1 to 2 minutes).
Pour half of pudding into individual dessert dishes. Top with 1 cup of the cherries and 1 cup of whipped topping. Spoon remaining pudding over this.
Add remainder of cherries and whipped topping.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate crunch cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars. Add beaten eggs. Put soda into hot water and add. Add vanilla, salt and flour. Beat until mixed. I use electric mixer. Add chips. Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: In a 2-quart dish, bring brown sugar, white corn syrup, butter and salt to a boil for 2 minutes. Stir in soda.
In brown grocery bag, pour mixture over popcorn. Cook 1 1/2 minutes in bag on High. Shake. Cook 1 1/2 minutes on High again. Allow to sit 1 minute. Enjoy.

title: nachos ole
directions: Combine cheese sauce and salsa; pour over chips.
Top with green onions, tomato, pepper and sour cream.

title: homemade cottage cheese
directions: Place utensil with ingredients in a pan of hot water and heat until curd separates.
Don't boil.
When mixture gets too hot, it becomes tough.
Work in salt and cream.
Drain.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour ingredients in baking casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chops & potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops in lightly greased skillet.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and set aside.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 tsp. seasoned salt.	Stir in potatoes, 1/2 c. cheese and 1/2 can onions.	Spoon mixture into 9 X 13 inch baking dish.
Arrange chops over potatoes.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.

title: ham rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ham.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly on one side of each ham slice; roll up and secure with a wooden pick.
Cover and chill.

title: sam's baked chicken
directions: Put chicken in butter, then in crumbs in baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and garlic salt.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: red punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid in a quart of water.
Add sugar, orange juice and cranapple juice; mix.
Add water to make 2 gallons.
Be sure to taste for right amount of sugar to suit your own taste! Freeze until slushy.

title: escalloped eggplant au gratin
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Cook in salted water until soft. Drain well; add bread cubes, butter, eggs, salt, pepper and all but 1/2 cup of cheese.
Sprinkle half the fine bread crumbs over bottom of buttered baking dish.
Add eggplant mixture.
Cover with remaining bread crumbs and cheese.
Cover with lid or foil and bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove cover and brown for 5 minutes.

title: apricot glazed chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow pan.
Mix together all the ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for one hour. Baste during baking.
(I cover with foil at about 40 minutes to keep chicken moist.)
Recipe can easily be cut in half.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook sugar and milk until it forms a very firm ball, but not hard, when dropped in cold water. Add pecans and dates. Stir well and remove from fire. Beat until dates become pulpy. Pour mixture over a wet cloth. Roll and let stand until cool; slice.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Sift flour and soda together.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add buttermilk and blend.
Add dry ingredients.
If too thick, mix with hand.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours in tube pan.

title: easy goulash
directions: Brown ground beef in 6-quart saucepan.
Season to taste.
Add tomatoes, onions and macaroni.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: tommy's s'mores
directions: Put 1/2 Hershey bar on graham cracker.
Put halved marshmallows (as many that will cover) on top of chocolate.
Cover with another graham cracker.
Put in a medium oven and heat until slightly melted.
Serve immediately.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Microwave butter and cocoa in a 2 1/2-quart glass casserole on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Pour batter into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Microwave on High for 10 to 11 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn after 5 minutes.
Leave cake in pan.
Spread miniature marshmallows over warm cake.
Top with Fudge Icing.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef with onions and bell peppers; drain well.
Stir in tomato sauce, sugar and spices.
Simmer for 15 minutes; stir occasionally.
Serve over hot spaghetti noodles.

title: pam's punch
directions: Combine sugar, lemon juice and boiling water.
Stir until dissolved; let cool.
Then add pineapple juice, frozen lemonade and frozen strawberry daiquiri mix.
Stir.
Freeze in 2-quart Ziploc bags.
Before serving, thaw until slushy and add 1 bottle of ginger ale per bag of frozen punch.

title: pauline's pecan pistachio salad
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Combine flour and nuts. Mix in pan with oleo.
Pat in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip. Spread on crust.
Mix pudding and milk; spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining cream cheese and sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate.

title: refrigerator pickles(good - try it!)
directions: Mix these ingredients and pour hot syrup over this mixture.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Bake in a rectangle 13 x 9-inch pan.
After cooling cake completely, frost as follows: mix pudding with milk and beat very little.
Beat in cream cheese, then fold in Cool Whip.
Frost cake with this mixture, then top with drained pineapple, shredded coconut, chopped walnuts and chopped cherries.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce and taco sauce.
Spread mixture evenly in casserole dish.
Mix corn bread according to package directions, then add 1/2 of the French fried onion rings.
Spoon corn bread and onion batter over the beef and bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with grated cheese and the rest of the onion rings.
Put back into hot oven for 2 to 3 minutes to melt the cheese.
Serve hot.

title: raisin spice cake
directions: Boil first 8 ingredients together for 3 minutes, and then let cool.
After mixture has cooled, add 1/4 cup of cold water to which 1 teaspoon baking soda is added.
Sift 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon baking powder together and add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef porkiepines
directions: Mix
ground beef, rice, onion, salt and pepper in bowl. Roll into
balls,
brown
in skillet without oil.
Mix tomato sauce and
tomato soup; pour over meatballs;
simmer about 30 minutes and serve.

title: pineapple orange jello salad
directions: Place pineapple in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add jello, stirring until completely dissolved.
Stir in buttermilk, coconut and pecans; cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Chill until firm.
Serves 15.

title: brisket
directions: In a large pan, salt lean side with salts.
Add liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce, then flip over and do the same to the fat.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 275°, covered, for 5 hours.
Bake for 1 hour uncovered.
Cover with barbecue sauce; cook at 325°.
Rake off the fat, but leave the juices in the pan until completely finished cooking.
Yields 8 servings.

title: german chocolate frosting
directions: Cook and stir until thickened all ingredients except coconut and walnuts.
When thick, add walnuts and coconut.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and sugar in a large mixing bowl, then blend in milk, egg and oil.
Cook at 350° in electric skillet.
Yields 8 pancakes.

title: pasghetti pizza
directions: Break spaghetti into 2-inch pieces.
Cook, drain and cool. Beat eggs lightly.
Stir in milk, 1 cup cheese and garlic powder. Add cooked spaghetti and stir together.

title: toasted coconut desert
directions: Cream flour and butter.
Then add chopped pecans.
Press into 9 X 13 dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add salt, vanilla and flour; mix well.
Press through cookie press onto baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 8 minutes.

title: irish freckle bread
directions: Cook potato in 1 cup water until tender.
Mash potato and add water to make 1 cup and return to pan.
Stir in currants.
Cool to lukewarm.
Put yeast into 1/2 cup warm water in large bowl.
Stir until yeast dissolves.
Stir in potato mixture, eggs, sugar and melted oleo.
Stir in 2 cups flour with salt.
Turn onto board. Knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise 1 hour until double.
Punch down.
Divide in half.
Makes two 8-inch round breads.
Let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven.
Stir in flour and cook over low heat until brown.
Add celery, onions and bell pepper.
Cook slowly until tender.
Add rest of ingredients except shrimp and rice.
Simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Add shrimp, cover and simmer about 7 minutes or until shrimp are pink and tender.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: annie's pizza bites
directions: On a 9 by 13-inch cookie sheet, roll out 1 can pizza dough to edges of cookie sheet.
Spread pizza sauce evenly over crust leaving 1/2-inch space around the edges of the crust.
Sprinkle pepperoni and cheese evenly over sauce.
Roll out remaining can of dough into a 9 by 13-inch rectangle.
Carefully place this on top. With a pizza cutter, score into 16 rectangles.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, butter and 6 tablespoons sugar and spread in a 9 1/2 x 13 1/2 glass dish. Bake for 30 minutes at 250° or until browned. Cool completely.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Separate cauliflower and chop up lettuce.
Pour bacon bits on top of salad.
Mix rest of ingredients and use as dressing for salad.
Serves 12.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, egg and sugar and mix well.
Shape into small balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix in cheese and Cool Whip.
Add jello (dry), then marshmallows and mix well.
Let set in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours until firm.

title: no cook do-dads
directions: Boil sugar and Karo syrup together one minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Special K; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Re-shape and cool.

title: ham sandwiches au gratin
directions: Spread toast with 3 tablespoons butter, then with deviled ham and cover with a second slice of toast.
Melt remaining butter, blend in flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add milk and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add chopped eggs, green pepper and cheese, if desired.
Pour over toast.
Serves 4.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together well butter, cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat after each.
Fold in flour.
Add vanilla.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: shrimp and salmon casserole
directions: Saute pepper, celery and onion in 1 stick butter. Mix with salmon, rice, cheese, mushroom soup and mushrooms. Put in casserole. Mix shrimp soup and shrimp. Pour on top. Top with bread crumbs. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake 20 minutes at 375°. This freezes well.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Bake pie shell at 425° until shell begins to brown.
Combine butter, brown sugar, pecans and coconut in saucepan.
Heat until butter and sugar are melted, stirring occasionally.
Spread in bottom of hot pie shell.
Return to oven for 5 minutes or until bubbly; cool.
Combine pie filling mix, chocolate and milk in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour over coconut mixture in shell.
Cover surface with plastic wrap. Chill at least 4 hours.
Before serving, remove plastic wrap and garnish with whipped topping and sprinkle with additional coconut, if desired.

title: snappy barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Cut all the fat you can off of the roast.
Place beef in Dutch oven.
Combine all remaining ingredients; pour over beef.
Cover and bake at 350° for 5 hours, turning beef occasionally.
Shred beef with a fork, removing any fat.
Serve on rolls or buns. Yields about 24 servings.

title: carrots diane
directions: Cut carrots into bite size pieces.
Boil until tender to your taste.
Drain.
Place butter in skillet.
Add carrots to butter. Add Dijon mustard and brown sugar.
Stir until well coated.
Serve hot.
Garnish with parsley.

title: nancy's dipped chicken
directions: Simmer for 15 minutes, then dip chicken in sauce and cook on grill, brushing frequently with more sauce.

title: lisa's chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in salt water.
When chicken is done, remove from but save broth.
Shred chicken and set aside.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth and cook 10 minutes until done, drain both. Return pot with spaghetti to stove, put over low heat.
Add chicken, soup, Rotel and cheese.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
When cheese is melted, dinner is done!

title: hot cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Put apples in casserole.
Add cranberries; sprinkle white sugar over cranberries.
Mix flour, brown sugar, oatmeal and then add melted butter.
Mix with nuts.
Spread over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(If Jonathan apples are used add 2 to 3 tablespoons of water to apples.)
If canned whole cranberries are used, cook apples before adding rest of ingredients.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Add vanilla and sour cream.
Add Cool Whip and just a squeeze of lemon.
Mix together.
Pour into pie shell and let sit in refrigerator.
Best if left overnight.
Before serving, add fruit of any kind.

title: roundup bean casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain grease.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a large casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti corn
directions: Stir all ingredients together and put in a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes with the cover on and 30 more minutes with the cover off.
Cover with aluminum foil.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound and cut chicken into serving pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Lightly beat egg and milk.
Combine Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce to cover baking dish; set aside. Dip chicken in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Melt Crisco in a skillet; brown chicken on both sides.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Place sliced cheese on top of chicken or sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Pour remaining sauce on top of chicken.
Cover baking dish with foil.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken liver stroganoff
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Set aside.
Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Dredge livers in 2 tablespoons flour and seasonings.
Add livers to skillet and brown.
Sprinkle livers with any remaining flour mixture and add bacon and mushrooms. Cover and simmer about 10 minutes.
Remove to a serving platter. Blend 1 tablespoon flour, sour cream and 1/4 cup water and stir into pan drippings.
Stir and cook until thick.
Pour over livers. Serve with parsleyed noodles, mashed potatoes or rice.

title: lemon walnut tea bread
directions: Lemon Icing:
Stir 1 cup powdered sugar and 4 to 5 teaspoons lemon juice together until smooth and thick but pourable.

title: cora's coconut cream pie
directions: Mix well and press in large square or oblong dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix chicken, cream of chicken and sour cream together; set aside.
Melt butter and pour over cracker crumbs.
Add poppy seed and mix together.
Pour 1/2 cracker mixture into casserole dish, then chicken mixture.
Top with last half of cracker mixture. Cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In a saucepan combine soup, milk, cheese, garlic and pepper. Add broccoli and carrots.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and cook for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add spaghetti and heat through.

title: turkey corn chowder
directions: In a 6-quart saucepan, saute onions, pepper, celery slices and turkey in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves six to eight.

title: caramel pound cake
directions: Cream
butter
and Crisco well until creamy.
Add sugar and eggs,
one at a time, beating well.
Add flour with baking powder and salt
sifted
together.
Add vanilla and evaporated milk, then nuts.
Bake in
a greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: grandma bounds syrup cookies
directions: Beat soda into syrup until white.
Add rest of ingredients. Add flour until dough is stiff.
Roll and cut or pinch off small ball and press down.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Drain oysters, saving 1/2 cup of liquor.
Mix liquor with 1/2 cup of milk; melt butter or margarine and mix with the cracker crumbs.
Spread a layer of buttered crumbs in a casserole.
Add 1/4 of oysters, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour a little of the liquor/milk mixture over the oysters and sprinkle on more crumbs. Repeat until out of oysters.
Top with buttered crumbs and pour on remaining liquor.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: miraculous microwave chocolate cake
directions: Cut out a circle of wax paper to fit bottom of 8-inch round plastic or glass pan, 1 1/2-inch deep. (I use square pan.) Cut another to make a collar to line sides to come up 1-inch higher.

title: chicken pie
directions: Stew chicken with seasonings added.
Remove bones and dice chicken.
Melt butter in skillet or large Corning Ware casserole dish; stir in flour.
Add broth and milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until medium sauce is made.
Place chicken and vegetables in casserole.
Salt and pepper, if desired, and mix well.
Cover with latticed pir crust.
Bake at 350° until golden brown and mixture is bubbly.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and 1/2 taco seasoning until smooth.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.
Fry ground beef and drain off excess fat.
Mix meat, 1 cup water and 1/2 of taco seasoning and bring to boil.
Let this simmer and then cool.
Place meat mixture over cream cheese mixture.
Layer on lettuce, tomato, cheese, onion, olives, green pepper, taco sauce and salsa.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients; beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 1 minute.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield: 6 dozen.

title: oatmeal peach crumble
directions: Arrange peaches in oiled 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with the lemon juice and cinnamon.
Dot with margarine.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased baking dish.
Cover with topping.

title: chocolate lover's frosting
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 cup confectioners sugar, cocoa, butter, 2 measuring tablespoons milk and vanilla extract; beat until creamy.
Gradually add remaining confectioners sugar alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fills and frosts one 8-inch layer cake.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in a buttered casserole dish.
Put cooked sausage on top.
Mix egg and sour cream together and layer with cheese. Bake at 350 degrees until brown (approx. 30 to 40 minutes).

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place a layer of 1/3 of the potatoes in a buttered 2-quart casserole; cover with 1/2 of the onion slices.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; sprinkle 1/2 the mixture over the onion layer; dot with 1/2 the butter.
Repeat layers, ending with a potato layer.
Pour hot milk over all and dust lightly with paprika. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 1/4 hours or until potatoes are very tender and milk is nearly all absorbed.
Makes 8 servings.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Sift together sugar, soda, flour and salt.
Add to first mixture and beat.
Then add the mashed bananas and fold in 2 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: cornbread mix
directions: Sift and measure cornmeal and flour.
Add baking powder, salt and sugar to cornmeal mixture and sift together.
Cut in the shortening until it is fine grained.
Store in a cool place.
If you use buttermilk, add 2 teaspoons soda to this recipe and use only half as much of the baking powder.
If you want to cook the cornbread in a waffle iron, use 1 cup of the shortening instead of 1/2 cup.
To use, add 1 egg and 1/2 cup of milk for each cup of the mix.
Stir in the small mixing bowl until well blended.
Pour into well-greased muffin tins or a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican hominygroves, texas
directions: Fry bacon to a crisp.
Remove back from skillet and add sliced onions and chopped green pepper to hot bacon grease.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, flour and mix with a little water and all the seasonings.
Cover and cook slowly one to two hours.
Add hominy and let simmer 10 minutes or longer.
Just before serving, add the grated cheese and bacon, broken up.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix and set aside in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare topping and pour over chicken mixture.

title: cherry sauce
directions: Mix chopped apple, jelly and preserves in medium saucepan. Mix cider, vinegar, and cornstarch; stir into pan.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly until thickened, about 1 minute. Great over ham.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss ingredients. Serve chilled.

title: mulled cider
directions: Mix the ingredients in a saucepan.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Add 3/8 cup brown sugar.
Simmer 5 more minutes.

title: easy pizza appetizers
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain, then add next 4 ingredients, stirring until cheese is melted.
Spread on bread.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until bubbly.

title: oyster corn bread dressing
directions: Chop oysters and combine first 8 ingredients in a large bowl. Stir in enough broth until mixture is very moist.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish (or pan).
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice (do not peel) 6 quarts cucumbers.
Soak 10 hours in canning salt and 9 cups of water.
Drain.

title: opal's bread
directions: Put yeast in warm water. Do not stir; set aside and let rise or work. Mix eggs, salt, sugar, Crisco, warm milk and bread flour. Add yeast mixture and let rise in bowl.
Knead and poke down and knead again. Form into 3 loaves. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and make bite size balls.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: german cornbread
directions: Melt a little grease in heavy iron skillet.
Let it get hot, then pour batter in. Bake at 400° until knife inserted in center comes out clean. This will take about 25 to 30 minutes.
Keeping in refrigerator will keep it moist. Good for holiday season.

title: hot pasta salad vinaigrette
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil.
Add celery, onion and garlic.
Cook about 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Meanwhile, cook shells in boiling water according to package directions.
When vegetables are ready, add 1/4 cup olive oil, vinegar, sugar, mustard, oregano and basil. Bring to boil, stirring until blended.
Remove from heat.
Drain shells.
Mix all ingredients together.
Serve immediately, sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 2 to 3 main dishes or 4 to 6 side dish servings.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix ingredients. Cover 20 minutes. Roll on floured surface. Cut out rolls. Makes about 65 rolls. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar and flour place pineapple in dish.
Sprinkle sugar and flour mixture over pineapple put cheese on mixture.
Pour 1/3 cup pineapple juice over it.
Make a topping of crackers and Margarine and put on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook together mushrooms, onion, pepper and sausage; drain off grease.
Add cubed cheese to meat mixture to melt; add noodles and rest of ingredients together.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You may not want this much cheese; if not, cut down on the amount.

title: apple pie(all american)
directions: If apples aren't juicy, add a little water. Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes, then at 375° for 10 minutes and finally at 350° until done.

title: guest pie
directions: Stir together until well mixed.
Put lemon juice in last. Pour into 1 large oblong pan or 2 (9-inch) pans with a graham or vanilla wafer pie crust.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Makes a lovely moist chocolate cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tuscan bean and cabbage soup
directions: Melt butter with oil in heavy, large pot over medium heat. Add onion, celery and garlic and cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add cabbage and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add stock, tomatoes, beans, ham bone, basil or pesto, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Taste and adjust seasoning.
Discard bone.
Can be prepared 1 day ahead.
Cool, cover and refrigerate.
Bring soup to simmer before continuing. Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saut onion in butter until limp.
Mix chicken, chilies and chicken soup.
Remove from heat.
Place 2 tablespoons of chicken mixture in middle of tortillas and roll.
Lay, rolled side down, on buttered baking dish.

title: oven-fried chicken(low-fat)
directions: Remove skin from chicken and brush each piece with vegetable oil.
Dredge lightly in flour or bread crumbs.
Season with pepper and paprika.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn and bake an additional 10 to 25 minutes, until tender.

title: sara's chicken and rice soup
directions: In a pot, add chicken, water, onion, bay leaf, parsley and celery tops. Cook until tender. Strain. Add all other ingredients and simmer.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: Heat juice to boiling.
Stir in jello until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce.
Chill until partially set.
Add Cool Whip. Chill until firm.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: wagon wheel dip
directions: In large mixing bowl, place mayonnaise and blend with salt pepper and paprika.
Put pickles, olives, onion, green pepper and garlic through food chopper; chop fine.
Drain.
Add to mayonnaise.
Add cheese and remaining ingredients; blend thoroughly.
Store overnight in refrigerator.
Serve with Melba toast, crackers or chips.

title: finger cucumber sandwiches
directions: Slice cucumber very thin, salt down and let stand 1/2 hour. Squeeze out the juice.
Add lemon, finely cut onion and a little thick cream.
Spread between sandwich bread.
Cut into finger shapes.

title: old faith sugar-cream pie
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together the sugar and the flour.
Add the whipping cream.
Lightly cream vanilla and teaspoon salt. Beat with mixer for about 6 minutes or until fluffy and thickened. Cover and let the cream mixture stand for 1 hour in the refrigerator.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 415° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 375° and bake pie for about 20 minutes or until filling doesn't jiggle.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: the best date-nut bread(two bowls)
directions: Add dash of salt to flour.
Mix together all ingredients with fingers until mealy and set aside.

title: grits casserole
directions: Bring tomatoes to boil.
Add grits; cover and set aside. Brown ground beef and chopped onion; drain.
Add to tomatoes.
Add vegies, beans and cheese.
Pour into casserole; top with French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: overtime apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. In large bowl, sift flour (or mix well) with sugar, soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Add apples, nuts, 1/2 cup margarine or butter and eggs.

title: noodles
directions: Roll out thin.
Cut and dry on table or countertop.
Drop into boiling broth (chicken or turkey).
Cook about 10 minutes.

title: zito pie
directions: Whip cheese, vanilla and sugar together.
Fold in Cool Whip and divide into two pie shells.
Top with pie mix.
Refrigerate.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and beat until creamy. Put in four 9-inch cake pans that have been well-greased.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until cake leaves side of pan.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Brown pork in heavy skillet.
Remove and place in oblong baking dish.
Add 1/2 cup water to skillet and onions, mushroom and celery.
Saute until tender.
Mix 1/2 cup water and 1 tablespoon flour, add to vegetables.
Stir until thickened.
Pour veggies over meat, cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until fork-tender.
Serves 5 to 6. Serve with rice.

title: betty gilchrist's swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls and brown, then simmer in diluted tomato soup until done.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Cream butter, sugars, eggs and nuts.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture; mix well.
Put in rolls, and put
in refrigerator until chilled.
Cut in slices and bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas.
Spread on the 5 tortillas.
Roll up and wrap in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate several hours.
To serve, cut into slices, 3/4 to 1-inch.
Serve with salsa.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar thoroughly.
Blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to banana mixture, alternating with milk.
Mix thoroughly after each addition.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours, or until cake tester comes out clean.
Makes 2 small loaves.
Very good for the holidays!

title: cabbage and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cabbage and cauliflower until tender, add onions and stir.
Drain the liquid from the cooked mixture.
Butter and salt to taste.
Pour into a well-greased casserole dish.
Layer with cream of celery soup, next layer of Cheddar cheese, then top with crushed potato chips or saltine crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Marinate steak overnight. Barbecue on a grill and baste often while turning. Cook according to taste. Cut meat on the diagonal.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix crackers, margarine and sugar.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix pumpkin, milk, pie spice and instant pudding until smooth. Spread over cracker crust.
Spread Cool Whip over top of pudding. Top with crushed nuts.
This is good, easy and no cooking required.

title: devon dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate.
Tasty as raw vegetable dip.

title: cheese squares
directions: Beat together cheese and butter; add flour, salt, pepper and raisins.
Roll in wax paper and chill overnight.
Slice and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into roll and wrap in aluminum foil.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 300°
for 1 hour, then turn oven to 450°
for 15 more minutes.

title: it don't matter(15 minute dish)
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Combine noodles and beef with cream of mushroom.
Heat over stove, then serve.

title: appetillas
directions: Combine all ingredients except tortillas.
Spread over top of tortillas.
Roll tightly, wrap in plastic wrap, refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 3/4 inch slices.
Yields 64 .

title: gooey cake squares
directions: Melt butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sugar, flour and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: jimmy dean beans
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add other ingredients, slow bake about 2 hours.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, 1 tablespoon of sugar and melted butter together and spread into long baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup of pecans over and press down, forming crust.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool completely.

title: oriental seasoning
directions: In jar with screw-top lid, combine soy sauce, molasses, ginger, mustard, garlic powder and onion powder.
Shake to mix. Store, covered, in refrigerator for up to six weeks.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Split each chicken wing at joint and discard tip.
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and toss with dressing mix.
Mix half of the dressing mixture with squash, soup, sour cream, onion, carrots and pepper.
Turn mixture into lightly-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; spread evenly.
Sprinkle remaining dressing mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put bread crumbs in long cake pan and pour pineapple over it. Combine the eggs, sugar and melted butter or oleo and pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low-fat banana bread
directions: Stir together the flour, soda and salt.
In a separate bowl, mix applesauce and sugar until smooth (can use mixer).
Add eggs and bananas.
Beat until well mixed.

title: dijon chicken
directions: Saute chicken 2 minutes on each side in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients that have been mixed together.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes, stirring until chicken is tender.
Serves 5, 175 calories per serving.

title: crisped dill beans
directions: Stem beans and pack uniformly and tightly in hot jars.
To each jar, add 1/4 teaspoon pepper flakes (more if you like it hotter), 1 clove garlic and 1 head dill.
Heat together water, salt and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Pour
over beans.
Adjust lids at once.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes. Remove jars from canner and allow to cool.
Chill well before serving.
Enjoy.

title: dad's corn muffins
directions: Grease muffin cups.
Mix egg and milk together.
Add to flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and salt. Mix together.
Add the melted shortening.
Mix until moist. Fill muffin cups 3/4 of the way.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread(yeast)
directions: Scald poppy seeds with hot water to cover good.
Set a few hours or overnight.
Grind, then add sugar,
eggs,
vanilla, and cinnamon.
Or can also add 1/4 to 1/2 cup cream and cook till bubbles in heavy kettle that doesn't scorch easy, stir all the while.

title: nolte's serious beans
directions: Start with skillet.
Brown the bacon; drain and reserve. Brown the Polish sausage; set aside.
Saute the chopped onion in the remaining bacon fat.
Open the kidney beans, butter beans and lima beans; drain in colander.
Combine the remaining ingredients, except bacon fat, with above ingredients.
Mix all above ingredients together with the bacon fat.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve hot or at room temperature. Better the second day.
(I usually double recipe.)

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in potatoes and onion.
Add butter.
Use lightly greased griddle.
Bake to golden brown, turning once.
Serve with applesauce.
(Potatoes may be precooked in microwave for 2 minutes before grating.)

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix this well and form into small balls.
Melt semi-sweet chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler or melt chocolate bark and dip balls in either one.
Place covered balls on waxed paper to set.

title: rocky road
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over warm water on low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Spread half the chocolate in foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the walnuts and all the raisins; cover with marshmallows.
Drizzle remaining chocolate over top; press remaining walnuts into chocolate.
Chill until firm.
Remove from pan; peel off foil.
Cut in 24 squares.
Wrap; store in refrigerator.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Saute celery, green pepper and onion in butter. Remove from heat.
Add Worcestershire, pepper, mushrooms, half and half and mayo.
Combine sauce with cooked rice, crabmeat and shrimp.
Bake in shallow dish, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, butter, brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla. Sift together and stir in the flour and salt.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip in slightly beaten egg whites.
Roll in the nuts.
Place about 1-inch
apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in a 375° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven. Quickly press thumb gently on top of each cookie. Return to oven and bake 8 minutes longer.
Cool.
Place a bit of chopped candied fruit, sparkling jelly or tinted confectioners sugar icing in thumbprints.
Makes about 2 dozen 1 1/2-inch cookies.

title: junior's cake
directions: Mix together. Pour in greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Leave cake in pan. Melt together 2 sticks margarine and 1 cup sugar and pour over cake. Serve cake in the pan.

title: 9 day slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, onions and green pepper.
Add sugar.
Mix good and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: thyme jelly
directions: Make infusion of thyme and water.
Strain and add enough water to make one half cup.
Combine with juices and honey in large saucepan.
Bring to full rolling boil and add pectin, stirring constantly.
Boil hard 30 seconds and give sheet test for jellying point.
Remove from heat and skim.
Pour into hot, sterilized glasses and seal.
A very pretty jelly to highlight venison, game, poultry and cheese dishes.

title: apple fluff pie
directions: Combine applesauce, lemon juice, salt, flour and well beaten egg yolks.
Cook over hot water until thick and smooth.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake at 425°
until crust is brown and filling is firm.

title: tuna layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, macaroni, cucumber, tomatoes, tuna, peas and cheese in a 3-quart serving bowl.
Spread Miracle Whip over salad, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Toss to serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: famous dill dip
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Mix with pretzels and press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and mix.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
Gradually beat into creamed mixture.
Last, stir in marshmallows, by hand.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crusty baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Trim off excess fat.
Pat dry.
Set aside.
In a bowl, beat egg and milk.
In another bowl, combine potato flakes, garlic salt, paprika and poultry seasoning.
Blend in cheese.
Dip chicken in egg mixture.
Then roll them in potato flake mixture to coat evenly on all sides.
Place chicken in baking dish or pan.
Sprinkle with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes, turning chicken once.
Increase oven temperature to 425°.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear when pierced with fork.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour and shortening by hand (or you may use a cutter) until the mixture is crumbly. Add milk. Mix well to form a ball of dough. Pinch off pieces of dough and form biscuits in your hand. Press biscuits onto lightly greased cookie sheet or baking pan. "Pat" top of each biscuit so that dough will not be too thick. Bake in 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. "Brown" tops.

title: cod or haddock baked
directions: Combine tomatoes, onion and parsley (set aside).
Combine vinegar, oil, garlic, pepper and salt (set aside).
In casserole, place a layer of tomato mixture, then layer of fish and the layer of oil mixture.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Add rice and stir.
Add beef consomme and onion soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
If desired, add mushrooms or green pepper or sausage.

title: sixty minute rolls
directions: Insert dough hooks into mixer. Thoroughly mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast. Combine milk, water and margarine into saucepan and heat over low heat until liquids are warm; margarine doesn't have to melt. Gradually add to dry ingredients. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Scrape bowl occasionally. Add 1/2 cup of flour to make thick batter form into ball. Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover; place bowl over pan of warm water. Let stand 15 minutes. Roll out. Cut out and place in pan. Let rise. Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.

title: energy drink
directions: Mix and chill.
Drain 1/2 to 3/4 cup every morning.

title: baked mostaccioli
directions: Cook mostaccioli noodles according to directions.
While this is cooking, saute turkey Italian sausage and onions until browned. After mostaccioli's are cooked, drain thoroughly.

title: jeff's cheesecake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Mix in sugar and toss with melted margarine.
Press into 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
In a small bowl mix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Put in refrigerator until it looks like egg whites.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix well.
Roll out to fit pie pan.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; set aside.
Pour hot water over sugar, Crisco and salt.
Cool to lukewarm, then add 1/2 cup flour.
Add dissolved yeast, egg and half of remaining flour. Beat thoroughly.
Add enough flour to form soft ball of dough. Turn out on lightly floured board and let rest 5 to 10 minutes. Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down, grease top and cover with a damp cloth and refrigerate.
When ready to bake, shape into rolls and place in greased pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: chicken-potato casserole
directions: Just mix everything together.
Sprinkle some Cheddar cheese across the top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: potato dish
directions: Saute onion and bacon together.
Grate the peeled potatoes and rinse them with cold water.
Drain.
Combine the onions, bacon, garlic, parsley, cheese and pepper.
Mix in with potatoes. Spread in a shallow pan (9 x13-inch).
In a separate bowl, whisk eggs and cream.
Add salt to eggs and cream mixture.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until top is brown. Serves 8.

title: spicy garden salad
directions: Chunk the tomatoes and cucumbers.
Dice the white onion, bell peppers and jalapeno peppers.
Thoroughly mix all ingredients and place in a large bowl with a lid.
Pour the 2 cups of Italian dressing over the mixture and stir.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in deep baking dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice, sugar and cinnamon. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over apples. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: lazy-day lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salt water. Drain. Combine oregano with spaghetti sauce. In greased 10 x 6 x 1/2 inch baking dish, alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella and sauce, using sauce for top layer. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Reserve 1/2 cup of mixture to mix with raisins and gumdrops.
Add vanilla to milk.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk to the first mixture.
Add floured gumdrops, raisins and nuts.
Bake in large, greased loaf pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Keeps well.

title: christmas green rice
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Cook broccoli in 1 cup water for 5 minutes, drain.
Saute vegetables in 1/2 stick margarine and mix with broccoli and rice.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over rice and vegetable mixture.
Add cheese and mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cafe bread pudding
directions: Combine eggs, milk, sugar, raisins in a large bowl.
Blend in pieces of bread, rolls or doughnuts.
Pour mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: pork chops in foil
directions: Mix wine, rosemary and thyme together; set aside.
Take 4 pieces of foil, large enough to enclose chop loosely.
Place 1 tablespoon of butter on dull side of foil, in center.
Place chop on it, cover with 1/4 of mushrooms.
Fold up sides to make an unleakable pouch; pour in 1/4 cup wine mixture, then fold over foil so that there is an airspace, but so it's sealed tightly. Repeat with other chops.

title: stuffed chicken rolls
directions: Flatten chicken to 1/8-inch thickness. Place ham and cheese on each breast. Roll up and tuck in ends. Secure with a toothpick. Combine the flour Parmesan cheese, sage, paprika and pepper. Coat chicken on all sides. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour. In a large skillet, brown chicken in oil over medium-high heat. Transfer to a 5-quart slow cooker. Combine soup and broth. Pour over chicken. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours. Remove toothpicks. Garnish with parsley, if desired. Yield: 6 servings.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover bottom with bread crumbs.
In skillet, cook crumbled sausage and drain.
Cover bread with sausage and cheese.
In a bowl, beat eggs, dry mustard, pepper and salt.
Pour over sausage.
Cover with aluminum foil (leave on for 1/2 baking time).
Refrigerate overnight.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and powder; add soda and milk. Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Alternate additions of milk mixture and flour; add vanilla.
Chill.
Roll out and cut out.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 8 to 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Set aside.

Bring to a boil the salt, pepper, sugar, garlic powder, tomato sauce, tomato paste and mushrooms. Simmer 15 minutes; set aside. Soften cream cheese and sour cream together. Set aside. Cook noodles. Put 1 cup of the tomato sauce mixture and 1 cup hamburger on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1/2 cream cheese mixture, then 1/2 noodles on top of that and 1/2 of the cheese, then repeat the layers. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or if baking cold, bake for 40 minutes.

title: tuna bake italiano
directions: Combine macaroni, tuna, tomato sauce, Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning in a medium size bowl.
In a 1 cup measure, combine instant chicken broth and boiling water; stir into tuna mixture.
Spoon mixture into a 6 cup baking dish.
Top with slices of Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly hot and cheese is melted.

title: baked creamy rice pudding
directions: In a large saucepan, combine evaporated milk and water.
Add cooked rice and cook over low heat, about 25 minutes.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Combine a little rice mixture with beaten eggs, then blend all well back into pudding.
Cook two to three minutes. Pour pudding into buttered 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Place casserole in pan of hot water, then bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until a knife inserted near the edge comes out clean.
When cool, the pudding may be served with whipped cream.

title: chicken crescent squares
directions: Blend together cream cheese, butter and milk.
Add salt, pepper, chives, pimento and chicken. Separate crescent rolls into 4 squares.
Spoon 1/2 cup of chicken mixture into the middle of each square.
Pull 4 corners to the top and seal.
Brush tops with melted butter and roll in crushed croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: cheesy chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients including just 2 cups of cheese and excluding the tortillas.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of the mixture into each tortilla and add a little extra cheese.
Roll and place seam side down in a baking dish.
Pour the remainder of the mixture over the filled tortillas and sprinkle more cheese on top.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: With fork mix together first four ingredients.
In separate dish beat remaining ingredients; combine the two mixtures, stirring with fork until all ingredients are moistened.
With hands, mold dough into a ball.
Chill at least 15 minutes before rolling. Dough can be left in refrigerator up to two weeks or can be frozen. Makes five 9-inch shells.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, chocolate, sugar, butter and vanilla until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until a knife inserted halfway between center and sides comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Serves 8.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix thoroughly applesauce, brown sugar and shortening.
Set aside.
In separate bowl, mix all dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts.
Add applesauce mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° in a 9-inch pan.

title: citrus berry cream punch
directions: Puree strawberries.
In large punch bowl, combine puree and nectar.
Before serving, top with scoops of ice cream.
Add ginger ale.
Garnish as desired.
Serves 20.

title: southern pie
directions: Mix cereal, eggs and warm water and set aside.
Mix all together and pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Tastes like pecans.

title: festive florentine crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together spinach, Cheddar cheese, crumbs and bacon in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Unroll dough; separate into 16 triangles.
Cut each in half lengthwise, forming 32 triangles.
Spread each triangle with rounded teaspoonfuls spinach mixture.
Roll up, starting at wide end.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush dough with beaten egg, if desired.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked moist pork chops
directions: Use casserole dish with cover and large enough to accommodate chops. Place halved apples, skin-peel side down, enough to cover bottom of dish.
Salt and pepper chops.
Arrange over apples. Place onion slices over chops.
Cover.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and put in a buttered square casserole.
Sprinkle top with corn flake crumbs.
Pour melted butter over top.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: southern salad
directions: Beat the cream cheese until it's fluffy. Add the milk a little at a time, beating well between additions. Stir in the pie filling, pineapple and pecans. Fold in the Cool Whip. Top with additional nuts and chill.

title: potato-cheese casserole
directions: Put hash browns in buttered large casserole dish.
Mix soups with 1/2 pound grated cheese and sour cream.
Layer over potatoes. Top with remaining 1/2 pound grated cheese.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: coconut bars
directions: Bottom layer:
Mix together and press in small square dish 1/2 cup butter, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 cup flour.
Bake 10 minutes in 350 degree oven.
Mix remaining ingredients together. Put this mixture on top of the bottom layer and bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: mac and cheese
directions: Drain cooked macaroni; add 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix.
Put in 9 x 11 baking dish.
In saucepan, mix all other ingredients; heat until cheeses are all melted.
Pour over macaroni.
Top with Velveeta slices and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
I like my cheese a little on the brown side.

title: low calorie milkshake
directions: Put into a blender and mix until thick.

title: eggnog(1 glass)
directions: Beat egg with electric beaters.
Add sugar; beat again and add milk and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Pour into tall glasses and sprinkle top with nutmeg.

title: cheese cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat the cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into crust.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Add onion.
Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan or skillet.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: mema's 24 hour salad
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar, pineapple syrup, salt, vinegar and butter in a saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until thick.
Fold remaining ingredients into the bowl and chill for 24 hours.

title: layer lettuce salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, pepper and peas in large glass salad bowl.
Spread mayonnaise on top, covering completely to edges. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours. Sprinkle with bacon before serving.

title: cornflaked potatoes
directions: Roll potatoes in serving size balls.
Coat with diluted egg. Roll in crumbs.
When ready to bake, place on greased sheet.
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes.

title: walnut - raisin cookies
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar, egg and vanilla in mixer until light and fluffy.
In separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt.
At low speed, gradually add flour mixture to first mixture. Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: california strawberry fruit salad
directions: Arrange fruit in sections on platter lined with salad greens. Serve with Lime Sauce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: double apple cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Beat in 2 eggs.
Add apples and vanilla.
In a large bowl mix flour with cinnamon and baking soda. Mix the 2 mixtures.
Core 2 to 3 apples; cut into thin wedges. Arrange some wedges on sides of well-greased 9-inch round, 1 1/2-inch deep cake pan.
Spoon in batter, level.
Arrange remaining wedges on top.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Glaze apple topping with 1/4 cup melted currant jelly.

title: oniony meat loaf for 2
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients.
In a shallow baking pan, shape into loaf.
Bake for 40 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water for 5 minutes.
Beat egg and add soup, mayonnaise, cheese and onion.
Mix well.
Add broccoli and place in ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and add pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until set.

title: drop donut holes
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, salt, oil, extract and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Mix flour and powder.
Add alternately with milk to egg mixture.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon into deep hot fat and fry 2 1/2 minutes until brown.
Donuts will rise to surface so keep them submerged to assure even cooking.
Drain on paper towels.
Shake with sugar in brown bag.
Makes 50.

title: shish kabobs
directions: Cut meat into cubes.
Combine garlic salt, pepper, mustard, chili powder, onion, vinegar, catsup and oil in small bowl.
Place cubes of meat in plastic bag and pour combined ingredients over meat.
Close bag and turn bag so meat is completely covered. Refrigerate overnight.
Pierce onions with ice pick several times to prevent them from falling apart when you add them to boiling water for 10 minutes.
Add green pepper to same boiling water for 5 minutes, stirring meat and vegetables on skewers alternately.

title: tortilla rolls(servings:  6)
directions: Slice all vegetables lengthwise in thin strips.
Marinate in Herb Oil (save teaspoon for mayonnaise) for at least two hours. Season with salt and pepper to taste and grill lightly.
Warm tortillas; spread with jalapeno mayonnaise.
Spread grilled vegetables on tortillas evenly.
Roll tortillas tightly; trim ends and cut into 3 equal parts.
Garnish with chopped cilantro.

title: remove grease stains
directions: Mix all together.
Pour on stain and let stand for a few minutes, then wash.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Mix other ingredients; pour into buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot chile dip
directions: Put all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or microwave on High, covered, for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring once or twice during cooking time or until cheese is melted and blended.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 4 cups. Stores well in refrigerator.
Reheat in microwave.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Saute chopped dates in oleo or butter about 2 minutes.
Add mashed potatoes and heat through.
Put mixture in a casserole. Smooth top and pour syrup over mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: onion ring batter
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add buttermilk and egg. Beat until smooth. Dip thinly sliced onion rings into batter.
Fry in deep hot oil.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter; gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together the dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Chill overnight.
Roll dough thin and cook 10 to 12 minutes in moderate oven.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add shortening, orange rind, orange juice and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in cranberries and pecans.
Pour in greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 large or 5 small loaves.

title: pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Cook on medium until thickens.
When it's done, you can put bananas or coconut in it.

title: florida dessert
directions: In saucepan, bring butter and sugar to a boil, stirring constantly.
In a bowl, combine Rice Krispies, nuts and coconut. Pour butter sauce over Rice Krispies mixture and mix well.
Press 1/2 of mixture into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Spread softened ice cream over Rice Krispies.
Top with remaining 1/2 of Rice Krispies mixture.
Freeze before serving.

title: fluffy meat loaf
directions: *You can change 1/2 pound of beef to 1/2 pound of lean pork (ground) for a variation.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream with spoon.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside rest of batter.
Mix cinnamon and brown sugar.
Spread over first layer of batter.
Pour rest of batter over this part.
