Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: banana muffins
directions: Stir all ingredients together and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes in muffin pans that have been greased or sprayed with nonstick spray.
If you use nonstick spray, these have no fat and count as 2 fruits, 1 milk and 1 protein.
It makes 3 to 4 muffins and the exchanges are if all the muffins are eaten at one time.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Beat on medium speed 1/2 minute.
Pour into pan.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly.
(If self-rising flour is used, omit baking powder and salt.)

title: fun putty
directions: Mix all ingredients together until blended.
If colored putty is desired, mix food coloring with starch before adding glue. Otherwise, mix starch and glue together until blended.
If the putty is too sticky, add more starch until it has a smooth consistency.
This recipe is surprisingly similar to commercial putty found in stores.

title: chili for 25 people
directions: Cook and drain ground beef, cook onions and peppers and save juice.
In a large pot or bowl, mix all ingredients.
Remember to rinse kidney beans.
Pour into large baking pan or roaster and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes until hot and done.

title: frosted pretzels
directions: Measure 2 cups frosting.
Heat it up in top of double boiler over hot water until frosting is liquid, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.
Dip the pretzels in the frosting with your fingers, then place them on wax paper.
Let dry 8 hours.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen good chewy cookies.

title: harlequin baked beans
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and brown, add sliced onion (rings), brown sugar, vinegar, garlic salt, and mustard.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Drain lima, butter and kidney beans.
Place all beans in casserole or bean pot.
Pour bacon mixture over beans. Stir lightly, bake 1 hour at 350.

title: "light" red velvet cake
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese at medium speed with electric mixer until creamy; gradually add sugar.
Beat well.
Gradually add egg substitute; beat well.
Stir in food coloring.
Combine cake flour and next 3 ingredients; add to butter mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into 3 (9-inch) round cake pans coated with cooking spray.
Bake for 18 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool completely on wire racks.
Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.

title: baked spinach and flounder
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cook spinach as label directs, adding onion; drain very well.
Stir in egg, garlic clove and salt.
In pan, layer flounder, spinach and cheese; then one slice of tomato on each.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: cooked brisket on grill
directions: Trim excess fat from brisket.
Mix together oil, lemon juice, salt, pepper, garlic and parsley.
Marinate brisket in mixture for 3 hours at room temperature, turning frequently.
Drain the meat and cook on slow fire until desired doneness.
Baste with barbecue sauce and serve sliced very thinly.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Combine the drink mix, sugar and pineapple juice in a plastic gallon container.
Add water until container is full.
Freeze until icy.

title: fruit salad
directions: Boil shell noodles in salted water and let cool. Cook eggs, sugar, vinegar, salt and juice of lemon together until thickened. Cool and then add 1 c. whipped cream. Cut up apples, grapes, bananas, oranges or can use mandarin orange sections and pineapple chunks. Add fruit to the shell noodles and pour cooled dressing over it just before ready to serve.

title: sour cream-lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, lemon rind, juice, egg yolks and milk in heavy saucepan; cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir in butter and cool mixture to room temperature.
Stir in sour cream and pour filling into pie shell.
Cover with whipped cream and garnish with lemon twists.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pizza lasagna
directions: Cook noodles until tender. Grease pan.
Layer noodles in bottom of pan. Spread half of the ground beef mixture on noodles and half jar of sauce.
Add 1 cup cheese. Layer noodles again with beef, sauce and topping. Cook until hot.
Remove from oven. Add remaining cheese.
Return to oven.
Cook until cheese has melted. Bake at 350°.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix all together; put in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with corn chips.
Delish!!

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Cream oil, eggs and sugar.
Sift together and add to cream mixture flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk, poppy seed, vanilla and butter. Stir together, mixture will be loose.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: tomato-chive dressing
directions: In blender container combine all ingredients and process at high speed until blended.
Makes 4 servings, about 1/4 cup each.

title: old fashioned dandelion salad
directions: Wash and pick over the greens thoroughly to be sure no grain of sand remains.
Dry on paper towels; tear into pieces and chill. Fry the bacon until crisp.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of the fat and drain the bacon on paper towels.
Add the sugar, flour and salt to the fat.
Cook and stir 3 minutes.
Add the vinegar and water and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add the chopped onion and the greens.
Toss well to coat thoroughly; cover and cook 2 or 3 minutes, just to wilt the dandelions.
Serve garnished with the bacon pieces.
A good salad we enjoyed in Iowa when I was growing up.
Dandelions were always plentiful in everyone's yard.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: *May use 2 cups half and half instead of separate milk and cream.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain off excess fat.
Separate crescent roll dough into 8 triangles.
Place triangles on an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward the center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust.
Seal any perforations. Top with crumbled sausage, hash brown potatoes and Cheddar cheese. Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper in a bowl; beat until thoroughly mixed.
Pour mixture over crust and toppings.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cranberry onion pork roast
directions: Season roast with salt and pepper; place over indirect heat on grill.
Stir together cranberry sauce and onion soup mix and heat, covered, in microwave until hot.
Baste roast with cranberry mixture every 10 minutes until roast is done.
Heat any leftover basting mixture to boiling, stir and boil for 5-10 minutes and serve alongside roast.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Mix well. Add remaining ingredients, except coconut. Cook until thick. Remove from heat. Add coconut; pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together soften margarine, nuts & flour. Press into bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350 degree for 20 minutes. Let cool. Mix sugar cream cheese, & Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust. Mix vanilla chocolate pudding & milk with mixer. Pour over cream cheese mixture. Top with Cool Whip and chill before serving.

title: fruit pizza(everyone's favorite)
directions: Cut sugar cookie roll and press into a pizza pan. Bake and let cool. Top with Cool Whip and fruit, starting with less expensive fruit around edges. (I normally use cantaloupe.)
Next, circle around your fruits using the most expensive in the middle (uses less and saves money when fruit is not on sale).
Cut like a pizza and enjoy!

title: swedish tea ring
directions: Mix milk, 1/2 cup sugar and salt together.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir into milk mixture.
Stir in eggs and shortening. Mix in with spoon, then with hand, the plain flour.
Add flour in two additions.
Gather into ball and knead on lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl. Cover with damp cloth and let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Punch down and let rise again 30 to 45 minutes.
Divide dough into 2 equal parts (makes 2 large rings).

title: potato soup
directions: Cook butter and onion in large pot until tender.
Add soups, milks, salt, pepper and hash browns.
Cook on medium-low until hot, stirring frequently.

title: chicken breasts with creamy mustard sauce
directions: Pat chicken breasts dry with paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Saute chicken in butter and oil in a large skillet, shaking pan occasionally to prevent sticking, until lightly golden, about 6 minutes.
Turn.
Lower heat.
Saute until chicken is tender, about 4 minutes longer.
Chicken should feel springy, with no pink remaining.
Cover skillet; cook 2 minutes longer to steam. Remove to warm platter.
Cover and keep warm.
Pour fat into a cup. Measure and return 2 tablespoons to skillet.
Saute green onions 30 seconds.
Add mushrooms.
Cook and stir until mushrooms are lightly golden, about 1 minute.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Melt together in microwave or cook in double boiler.

title: cheese cookie
directions: Let cheese and margarine come to room temperature.
Blend all ingredients, except Rice Krispies.
Add Rice Krispies and blend with spoon.
Roll into balls.
Press flat with damp fork.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 18 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables until tender in 1 quart of water.
Add 2 cans of undiluted cream of celery soup.
Add 1 pound of cubed Velveeta and cook until melted.

title: cherry cheese brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed on package, except bake for 20 minutes.
Beat vanilla, egg, milk and cream cheese in a large bowl until smooth.
Pour over baked brownie layer.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese layer is set, about 25 minutes.
Cool for 2 hours.
Spread with cherry pie filling.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate strawberry shortcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Grease two 9-inch layer pans. In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, 1/3 cup sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Cut in butter or margarine until the mixture resemble coarse crumbs. Add milk, mixing just until moistened. Spread batter evenly into two prepared layer pans. Bake for 15 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool. In a medium size mixing bowl, combine strawberries and 1/4 cup sugar. Let this mixture stand for 10 minutes. Cover the bottom shortcake layer with half of strawberry mixture and half of the whipped topping. Top with second shortcake layer, remaining strawberry mixture and whipped topping. Drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: kimbo's chicken salad
directions: *I put the chicken in a food processor to chop it.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Do not stir.
Sift cocoa and sugar in large mixing bowl; add milk and sticks of butter on top.
Remember do not stir.
Cook on High for 6 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir thoroughly. Add vanilla and pecans.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into buttered glass platter.
Cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Cut and serve.
Do not double recipe.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans together.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
When cool, mix 1 cup of Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over crust. Mix both pudding mixes and add milk until thickened, then spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with rest of Cool Whip and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients and let sit overnight.
(Add anything else you like.)

title: butterscotch cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix adding milk, eggs, the 1/2 cup butterscotch dessert mix and the 1 teaspoon vanilla extract.
Mix and bake as directed on package in three greased and wax paper lined, 9-inch layer pans.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put the strawberries, whole or halved, in 9-inch pie shell. Put sugar, cornstarch and water into pan and cook until boiling. Reduce heat and cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly. Add the strawberry Jell-O (dry) directly from package. Pour over berries. Refrigerate immediately. Serve with whipped cream.

title: debbie's luscious dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan; freeze.
Cream powdered sugar and eggs.
Add butter and chocolate.
Beat until fluffy, 5 minutes or more.
Spread over graham cracker mixture; freeze.
Whip the cream.
Add marshmallows and candy, reserving a little of the candy.
Spread on top of chocolate mixture.
Sprinkle remaining candy on top of cream mixture.
Freeze.
Take out 15 minutes before serving.

title: blue cheese olive ball
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Add Blue cheese and beat well.
Stir in chives and chopped olives.
Mixture will be soft.
Shape mixture into a ball and roll in pecans.
Refrigerate overnight. (This allows the flavor to ripen.) Serve with crackers.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Then add milk, vanilla and lemon.
Stir in rice and cinnamon.
Bake in greased 9 x 13 dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Check after 45 minutes.
When knife inserted in center comes out clean, it is done.
Rice stays on bottom and the top is like custard and creamy.

title: coconut pie
directions: Stir together sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Blend milk and egg yolks.
Gradually stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Mix in pumpkin, cloves and cinnamon.
Add flour, baking powder and baking soda alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Mix in nuts. Pour batter in 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven until done when tested.

title: no-fat broccoli and pasta
directions: Boil broccoli florets in salted water in a large pot until soft.
Remove florets with strainer spoon (reserve water) and mash in a large bowl with the garlic, salt, pepper and cheese.
Cook pasta in the same water as broccoli until al dente.
Strain into colander and add to bowl of broccoli mixture.
Toss thoroughly and add or correct seasonings.
Serve hot.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend well.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) paper-lined pans.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back.
Freeze until cooled, but not frozen.
Slice in half to make 4 layers.

title: classic italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Remove sausage meat from casings.
In 8-quart Dutch oven over high heat, cook sausage meat and ground beef, stirring often until all pan juices evaporate and meat is browned.
With slotted spoon remove mixture to bowl.

title: soyed chicken wings
directions: Place chicken wings in stock pot; sprinkle with ginger and wine.
Cover and simmer over medium-high heat until wine is almost evaporated.
Add remaining ingredients, mixed well.
Simmer and cook, covered, for 1 hour, stirring wings often and keeping heat at medium to medium-high.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marinated artichoke salad
directions: Drain artichoke hearts, reserving 3 tablespoons liquid. Combine artichoke hearts, reserved liquid and next 6 ingredients in a shallow container.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight. Spoon salad into a lettuce lined bowl and garnish with egg slices and bacon.
Yields 6 servings.

title: good-for you salad
directions: Combine cucumber, green pepper and lettuce in a salad bowl; toss well.
In a medium bowl, combine seasoned salt and yogurt. Mix well.
Pour dressing on salad and mix well.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper on both sides.
Arrange potatoes in baking dish.
Mix soup, milk and onions and pour over potatoes.
Place chops on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix, shape and broil or pan-fry until brown.
Drain.

title: desiree's coconut cake
directions: Mix well.
Fill 3 (8-inch) layer pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: mom's apple cake
directions: Mix. Spread in 9-inch square pan which has been greased and floured; bake at 350° 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: aunt trish's good pancake recipe
directions: Mix "wet" ingredients and then stir in the dry ingredients. Cook on top of stove & add a dab of butter to pancake as it comes off the griddle.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Cream shortenings until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually along with 1/2 cup milk, then add eggs one at a time.
Add flour mixture and rest of milk a little at a time.
The longer you beat, the better.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: oven-fried chicken and dressing
directions: Cut chicken in serving pieces; dip into flour seasoned with salt and pepper; brown in hot fat or Pam spray.
Combine remaining ingredients using 1/2 cup soup.
Arrange chicken in Dutch oven or large casserole.
Pile dressing in center.
Make gravy of pan drippings, using 2 tablespoons flour and enough water with remaining soup to make 2 cups; pour over chicken.
Cover closely; bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin and cream cheese roll-up
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon, pumpkin pie spice, nutmeg, and salt.
Beat eggs and sugar in a large bowl until fluffy.
Beat in pumpkin.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 15 minutes. Loosen cake with a knife around edges.
Invert onto clean damp towel dusted with powdered sugar.
Trim 1/4-inch from all sides. Roll up cake and towel together from short side.
Place seam side down on rack.
Cool.

title: date nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300° to 325°.
Have loaf pan ready.
Mix dates and pecans.
Sift dry ingredients and add to dates and pecans.
Mix well (it's easier to use your hands).
Add cherries, pineapple, vanilla and beaten eggs.
Bake in loaf pan in slow oven (300° to 325°) for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican wedding rings
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla. Chill; form into small balls.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: spanish rice with meat
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, beef and rice in oil until brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover tightly and simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pat down well in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 275° for 10 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and bananas.
Beat in eggs.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir gently into egg mixture alternately with liquids.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into greased 10 x 6 x 3-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: weight watchers salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Put in a jar or bottle.
Keep in refrigerator.
Counts as 1/2 milk.

title: zimmerinski
directions: Marinate sirloin in sherry, soy sauce and garlic for 1 hour. Spray frying pan with cooking spray.
Stir-fry steak strips for 2 minutes.
Push up onto side.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes, then pull steaks back into vegetables and stir-fry for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add soup; stir until heated well.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4 to 6 depending on appetites.
(Careful not to overcook steak.)

title: chicken or turkey a la king
directions: In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook green pepper 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in flour and salt until blended.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened.
Add meat, mushrooms with their liquid, pimentos and bouillon; heat to boiling, stirring often. Reduce heat to low; cover, simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over biscuits.

title: dried peaches
directions: Put sugar and vinegar over peach peelings and let stand overnight.
Cook until thick.
Fill jars and seal.
Use to make fried pies.

title: oatmeal jumble bars
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except jam; mix well.
Reserve 1 cup mixture;
press remaining on bottom of prepared pan.
Spread jam evenly over base to within 1/2 inch of edge of pan; sprinkle with reserved mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely; cut into bars.
Makes 13 x 9-inch pan of bars.

title: bun bars
directions: Melt together chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Pour half of mixture onto a lightly greased 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
(Cool in fridge for 1/2 hour.)
Add peanuts to other half of mixture.
Set aside.
Melt margarine; add evaporated milk.
Stir in pudding and sugar.
Mix with mixer until smooth.
Add maple flavoring.
Spread over first layer.
Cool in fridge for 1 hour.
Cover with remaining chocolate/peanut mixture and chill.
Cut into squares and refrigerate.

title: macaroni saled
directions: Cook macaroni and drane.
Add all of the above mix and put in frig.

title: tabasco chicken salad
directions: Blend together mayonnaise, sour cream, Tabasco, curry powder, salt, lime juice, onion and capers.
Combine chicken, celery, almonds and pineapple in large bowl; add dressing and toss lightly.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: day after thanksgiving turkey soup
directions: Heat butter in a skillet and saute onion and garlic until onion is translucent.
Transfer contents of the skillet into a slow cooker.
Add all other ingredients except the cream.
Cover, turn on low and cook for about 6 hours or until the vegetables are tender.
Stir in heavy cream and heat thoroughly before serving. Serves 8.

title: fruit salad #2
directions: Fix pudding according to box directions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water together and cook until mixture threads.
Add peanuts and stir continuously, cooking until syrup mixture turns light brown in color and peanuts are done.
Remove from fire; add soda, salt and butter.
Stir until thoroughly mixed and pour onto buttered table top as thin as possible.
Stretch. Break up and bag.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potatoes. Mix and then fold in potatoes. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: garden casserole
directions: Brown ground meat with onion, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper.
Drain well.
In large boiler add green beans, corn, tomatoes and English peas.
Drain all vegetables.
Cook the potatoes and carrots a short while.
Drain.
Add this mixture and the meat mixture to the vegetables in the large boiler and mix well.
Heat thoroughly, then pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes while you prepare cheese biscuits for the topping.

title: lite strawberry plus salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Combine Jell-O and water; dissolve well.
Fold rest of ingredients in all at once and mix well.
Pour half of this mixture in 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan and refrigerate 1 1/2 hours at least (leave rest of mix at room temperature).
Then 1 1/2 hours later, cover mixture with 1 pint of sour cream.
Spoon rest of mixture very carefully over sour cream and refrigerate until set firm.

title: pralines
directions: Butter the sides of a heavy 2-quart saucepan. Place sugars, salt, corn syrup, milk, and butter in saucepan. Over medium heat, stir mixture constantly with a wooden spoon until sugars have dissolved and mixture comes to a boil. Continue to cook to a soft ball stage, approximately 236°. on a candy thermometer. If you do a cold water test, the ball of candy will flatten when you take it out of the water. Remove from heat and allow to cool for 10 minutes. Add vanilla and nuts; beat with a spoon by hand for approximately 2 minutes or until candy is slightly thick and begins to lose its gloss. Quickly drop heaping tablespoons onto waxed paper. If the candy becomes stiff, add a few drops of hot water.

title: make your own eagle brand milk
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and beat one minute. Refrigerate until thick.
Makes 1 1/4 cups or same as 2 cans.

title: apple crunch
directions: Pack firmly in a buttered baking dish, apples to a depth of 1 1/2-inches.
Apples should be pared and coarsely chopped.
Dot apples with cinnamon.
Mix white sugar, butter and flour.
This mixture will be crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 45 minutes in a moderate oven.
Serve with ice cream or cream.

title: mound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 3 layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool.

title: tea time tassies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg. Add vanilla and nuts. Fill the centers and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Break into pieces.
To drippings in skillet, add flour, water, vinegar, sugar, salt and mustard.
Lay potatoes in casserole with one layer potatoes and one layer of thinly sliced onions until casserole is filled.
Pour dressing over top and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream together the eggs, sugar and margarine.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into eggs and sugar mixture.
Add raisins, nuts and coconut.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 300° for 1 hour.

title: sausage and artichoke pie(9-inch size)
directions: Do not add salt.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar; beat well.
Gradually add flour and beat well.
Add milk, vanilla, coconut and oleo.
Pour into ungreased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: better oven baked barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs well; pour off excess fat.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over ribs.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 2 hours, basting with sauce 3 or 4 times.
Remove cover, bake for 15 minutes longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cream of chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
In separate pot, cook butter, flour, salt, pepper and 2 1/2 cups of broth until it bubbles.
Add 1 1/2 cups of milk and reboil 1 minute.
Turn on low and add chicken (that you chunked).
Serve over sweet peas and egg noodles.

title: powder house salad delight
directions: Mix ingredients and chill for at least 3 hours.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Saute onions, peppers and tomatoes.
Add all remaining ingredients, including wieners, and marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° until sauce thickens.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and run at high for 1 minute. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan (Pyrex).
Bake for 50 minutes in a 325° oven until crust forms on bottom, custard in middle and coconut on top.
Makes a large pie so use a deep pan.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix oleo, beans, eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans; mix good.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: baked salmon
directions: Saute ingredients.
Clean salmon; lay on heavy aluminum foil. Pour ingredients over and inside of fish.
Top with lemon slices and onion slices.
Fold over foil and seal.
Can be baked in oven for 1 hour at 350° or put on the barbecue grill; turn over once during baking time.
Baking time depends on the size of the fish.

title: hot relish
directions: Wash peppers, remove seeds and core.
In a 6 to 8-quart boiler, combine sugar, vinegar, water and pickling salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add all ingredients and bring to a boil for about 5 minutes.
Place a clove of garlic in each hot, sterilized pint jar.
Fill jars to 1/2-inch of top.
Use plenty of liquid when filling.
Remove air bubbles.
Wipe jar tops and threads clean. Place hot lids and band on.
Screw tight.
Process in boiling water canner for 5 minutes to seal.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Place in casserole dish.
Layer cheese and undiluted soup.
Moisten stuffing.
Mix with water and crumble on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: oreo pie
directions: Beat egg whites and sugar in bowl until stiff peaks form. fold in nuts and crushed Oreos.
Spoon into buttered 8-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread with whipped topping before serving.

title: scandinavian relish
directions: Mix together and add the following dressing.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli according to package directions. Drain well.
Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.
Combine the broccoli with the soup, eggs, cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Mix well.
Spoon in casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Then mix rest of ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet, greased.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine.
Pour condensed milk over crumbs.
Top with chips; press down firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until lightly brown.
Cool and cut into bars.
Store at room temperature.

title: old fashioned chocolate pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients good.
Put on stove and cook until it thickens.
You may want to double this recipe.
It's so good you'll need it for hungry folks who love chocolate pudding.

title: lynda's full meal deal
directions: Cover; simmer 1/2 to 3/4 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve with hot biscuits or hot baked bread.
Yield:
1 large stew pot full.

title: baked barley
directions: Melt butter in skillet; saute onion and garlic.
Add barley and spices.
Cook until barley is brown.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In a heavy saucepan, lightly brown the garlic in oil.
Add the onion and saute until translucent.
Add the mushrooms, broccoli, zucchini, eggplant, celery, carrots and the red and green peppers and saute just until tender.
Add the wine and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Add the cornstarch and broth mixture and stir until thickened.
Add basil and marjoram.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve on a bed of hot fettucini noodles.
Serve topped with freshly grated Parmesan and shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Add a fresh loaf of French bread and wa la!

title: play doh
directions: Heat all ingredients over low heat in saucepan, stirring until ball forms.
Knead.

title: taco dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Spread beans in bottom of casserole dish 9 X 13.
In large bowl combine cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Mix in garlic.
Spread mixture over beans in casserole.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake 15-18 minutes.
Top with olives, tomato and onion.
Garnish with additional sour cream if desired.
May also add fresh parsley and cilantro (2 Tbsp.) if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: danish red cabbage
directions: Put cabbage in a heavy, porcelain lined iron pot with vinegar. Add fat.
Carefully bring to a boil.
Add a little water if necessary.
Add apples, allspice berries, salt, sugar and raisins. Cabbage should be juicy but not soupy.
Taste for salt and give the pepper mill a few turns.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Thoroughly mix crushed pineapple, Cool Whip, coconut, marshmallows, chopped nuts, cherries and milk.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: mary's four cheesy macaroni
directions: Pour milk in pan, add warm block margarine or butter.
Add cheese and bread.
Cook until melted.
Add salt and pepper.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in sifter; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after adding each.
Add pumpkin; mix well.
Add dry ingredients to mixture alternately with water (can use milk instead); mix well after each addition.
Add pecans and blend. You can add 2/3 cup prepared mincemeat now (but I never do!). Spoon into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans; bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
(I usually bake at 325° in cake pan or 2 pans that equal a cake pan for 20 to 30 minutes.
These can also work for muffins for 12 to 15 minutes.)

title: golash
directions: Saute beef and butter until light brown.
Add vegetables. Saute until tender.
Add soup mix, beef base and Worcestershire sauce.
Add 1 quart water.
Cook 45 minutes.
May need to use more water to your taste so it won't be salty.
Add Kitchen Bouquet for color.
You can add more or any ingredients.
If you want, more beef or vegetables, add.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together;
pour in pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 20 minutes.	To test, put knife into pie halfway between
center and edge.
If knife comes out dry, then pie is
cooked.
If
there is anything on the knife, then leave and cook a little longer.

title: spinach & artichoke casserole(award winner)
directions: Coat 9 x 13 pan with cooking spray. Layer artichokes then spinach in pan. Cream together cream cheese & milk, pour over vegetables. Place slices of Jack cheese over cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle with parmesan. Bake at 350 for 40-60 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together corn, crackers, salt and pepper to taste and egg. Pour into well-greased pan.
Garnish top with additional crumbled Club crackers (3 or 4) and strips of bacon (if you like); a few dollops of butter here and there on the crumbled crackers is nice too.
Place in 350° oven for 1 hour, until top is light brown and bacon is fully cooked.
Check before the hour is up to be sure it doesn't burn.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Cut dried beef in small pieces.
Mix together all ingredients and let stand overnight.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients together well and refrigerate overnight. Makes enough dressing for 2 packages of tiny rolls with shaved ham in center.

title: brown rice
directions: Broil onion in margarine until onion is light brown.
Pour into casserole and add remaining ingredients. Cover dish with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts tarragon
directions: Skin, debone and half the chicken breasts lengthwise.
Pare and slice the carrots into 1/4-inch rounds.
In 6-quart dutch oven, heat oil and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add chicken breasts (half at a time to cover bottom of pan); saute until brown on all sides.
Remove chicken as it browns.
Brown remainder of chicken. To drippings in dutch oven, add shallots and carrots; saute, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until golden.
Return chicken to dutch oven; heat.
When hot, heat Cognac in ladle; ignite and pour flaming over chicken. Add wine, chopped tarragon, chervil, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer gently, covered, 30 minutes.
Remove chicken to heated serving platter; keep warm.
Strain drippings in dutch oven and discard vegetables. In a bowl, combine cream, egg yolk and flour; mix well with wire whisk.
Stir cream mixture into drippings in dutch oven; bring to just boiling, stirring constantly.
Add more wine if sauce seems too thick.
Meanwhile, saute mushrooms in hot margarine until tender, 5 minutes.
Spoon sauce over chicken and garnish with mushrooms and tarragon.
Optional:
May be served over a bed of rice.
Serves 8.

title: fried okra
directions: Wash okra well and drain.
Cut off tip and stem ends; cut okra crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Combine water and salt.
Pour over okra and soak for 30 minutes.
Drain, rinse well and drain again. Roll okra in cornmeal and fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain well on absorbent towels.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Take a handful of potatoes with a marshmallow in the middle and shape into a ball.
Roll the potato ball in some coconut and pecans.
Do not grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Watch closely.

title: nut tarts
directions: Blend room temperature cheese, butter and flour; chill for 1 hour.
Divide into 24 equal parts; shape each part into a small ball.
Press into bottom and 1/2-inch up the side of small buttered 2-inch muffin cups; chill.
Blend remaining ingredients and place one teaspoon of mixture in each pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen small tarts.

title: ann's oyster chowder
directions: In 5-quart crock-pot, place soup, milk, spinach and bacon. Melt butter in skillet. Saute onion and oysters. Cook 5 minutes. Add wine. Cover and cook 20 minutes on low. Add to crock-pot. Simmer 1 hour or longer.
Skee-rum-ious.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if tough, otherwise just scrub and rinse.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in baking dish.
Fan them slightly.
Sprinkle with salt; drizzle with butter and sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheeses. Return to oven for another 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned, cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft inside.
Check for fork.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Add flour and soda.
Add oatmeal; stir well.
Add nuts. Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325°.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: one minute chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla, in saucepan.
Cook, stirring frequently, until mixtures comes to a full rolling boil. Boil 1 minute and remove from heat.
Cool.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Make cake; cool.
Cut into small bite-size pieces.
Layer bottom of large bowl with cake.
Mix each pudding with 1 3/4 cups milk and 1/4 cup Kahlua.
Pour over cake.
Put one (8 ounce) Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Repeat the layers with remaining ingredients.

title: angel biscuits
directions: In a 1-cup measure, dissolve yeast in water.
In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in butter until it is fine.
Stir in yeast mixture and enough of the buttermilk to make a fairly soft dough.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix together the sour cream, mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add the Blue cheese and minced onion.
Chill.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Beat eggs and margarine; mix thoroughly.
Add sugar and flour. Add milk and eggs gradually.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes or scrub and rinse.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use handle of spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way through.
Put potatoes in baking dish, fan slightly.
Sprinkle with salt; drizzle with butter and sprinkle with herbs and spices.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Stir into the warm liquids; cook until thick enough for gravy.
Add vanilla and serve over buttered biscuits.

title: gingersnaps
directions: *Additional sugar to use as a dip; do not add to mix.

title: chewy homemade breadsticks
directions: In a large bowl, sprinkle yeast over the 1/4 cup water.
Stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in salad oil, sugar, salt, milk and 2 cups flour.
Beat on medium speed for 5 minutes or until dough pulls from sides of bowl in stretchy strand.
Stir in about 1 cup flour to form a stiff dough.
Turn onto a lightly floured board.
Knead for 10 minutes or until smooth.
Turn dough over in a lightly greased bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Let rise in a warm place for 1 hour or until doubled.
Turn dough out onto board.
Knead to expel trapped air.
Cut into 12 equal pieces.
Cover and let rest 5 minutes. Roll each piece out into a log, about 12 inches long. Set breadsticks 1-inch apart, on a greased baking sheet.
Brush tops lightly with oil.
Sprinkle with caraway seed.
Let rise in a warm place for 20 minutes or until puffy.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden.
Cool on pan for 2 minutes.

title: pineapple carrot cake(yields 1 bundt cake)
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Add drained pineapple juice.
Add well-beaten eggs, oil and vanilla.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Batter will be stiff.
Add pineapple, carrots and nuts and beat well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and frost.

title: fried rice
directions: Prepare veggies.
If using canned bean sprouts, rinse, drain and pat dry.
Work on high heat.
Add 1 tablespoon oil; heat until hot.
Add eggs; stir until soft scrambled.
Put on side of wok. Add 2 tablespoons oil, bean sprouts, salt and mushrooms.
Stir-fry 1 minute; move up on side with eggs.
Remove wok from heat; wipe bowl with paper towel.
Return to heat.
Add remaining oil and heat; add rice and stir until hot.
Add soy sauce; continue stirring until well mixed.
Add green onions and meat.
Return remaining ingredients to wok bowl; stir-fry for 1/2 minute.

title: busy day pot roast
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Put meat in heavy casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over meat.
Cover and bake 3 hours or until done.
Thicken gravy to serve.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix water, soups and rice.
Put in a casserole dish.
Then melt or soften butter.
Add pepper and salt.
Roll chicken in this mixture.
Place on top of rice and soup.
Add remaining butter. Cover dish and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Beat brown sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add egg and beat.
Add sour milk, flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add rhubarb and mix well.
Top with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake in glass pan at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter, then mix with yellow cake mix.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, form crust on bottom.
Combine cream cheese, 3/4 of box of powdered sugar and eggs.
Mix until creamy; pour over cake mix.
Cook about 30 to 35 minutes, or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with rest of powdered sugar.

title: no cooking play dough
directions: Mix all things together in a bowl.
Knead.
Keep dough in a plastic bag or container.
Store in the refrigerator.
Use food coloring if you like.

title: sherry cake
directions: Dredge fruit and nuts with 1 cup flour.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat thoroughly.
Add flour and mix together.
Add sherry.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Put into greased and floured spring-form pan and bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: deviled potato salad
directions: Cut eggs in half and remove yolk.
Mash yolk and mix with vinegar and mustard.
Add mayonnaise, sour cream and celery seed. Mix well.
Chop egg white and combine with potatoes, celery, onion and pimento.
Fold in egg yolk mix.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Beat milk and lemon juice for 5 minutes.
Mix in other ingredients.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill and serve.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Into a punch bowl, place one layer of the cake.

Add one package of pudding mix, prepared by the directions on the package, half of the fruit cocktail, pineapple and pie filling, half of the nuts, one container of whipped topping and one package of coconut. Add second layer of cake and repeat all the layers, ending with coconut.
Chill until serving time.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Mix in bowl. Combine green beans, celery soup and mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Add dried onions for topping and microwave for 30 minutes.
Serve as side dish.

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken in chunks and combine with oil, orange juice and vinegar; let stand for 30 minutes. Add rest of ingredients.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Place rolls flat in oblong baking dish. Press to spread out as far as they will go. Spread a thin layer of mustard over dough (spicy mustard is good). Saute zucchini and onions in oil or butter until onions are crystal color. Mix in bowl the vegetables, eggs, 1/2 of cheese and the seasonings. Pour over dough; dot with butter and place balance of cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes to 1/2 hour until crust is brown and cheese is bubbly.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Put ingredients in pan and cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove.
Add 1/2 cup nuts and 2 cups Rice Krispies.
Cool until able to handle and form into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Slice peeled potatoes into rounds.
Layer potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Make a layer of potatoes.
Dot potatoes with butter, salt, pepper and 1/2 can soup.
Make another row of potatoes with butter, salt, pepper and soup.
Lay pork chops on top of potatoes.
Then salt and pepper them.
Cover with foil and bake at 425° for 1 hour or until pork chops look done.
Then take foil off and brown for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Put beans in Pyrex bowl; add mushroom soup.
Top with onions.
Bring to a slow simmer in oven for 20 minutes at 300°.

title: perfect pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and syrup.
Add eggs and melted margarine (not hot, it will curdle eggs).
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: the best hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Store in an airtight container. (Low-fat and low-sugar cocoa mix.)
Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup boiled water.

title: hot chicken chip salad
directions: Select cabbage that is neither too hard (shreds will be coarse) or too soft (it is difficult to shred).
Cut cabbage into quarters, cutting between where leaves are attached to core, so leaves will hold together.

title: sand castle brownie mix
directions: In a 1 quart glass jar, layer the first seven ingredients in order listed, packing well between each layer.
Cover and store in a cool dry place for up to 6 months.

title: patty's cooked frosting
directions: Combine milk, flour and vanilla in a saucepan over medium heat, whisking constantly, until thick.
This mixture must completely cool!
Add remaining ingredients.
Whip until sugar dissolves and frosting is fluffy.
Spread on your favorite cake.

title: puree of anchovies
directions: Mince or pound anchovy fillets.
Moisten bread with enough water to cover, then squeeze dry.
Break into bits or mince with a fork.
Blend in sour cream and vinegar to make a smooth puree. Serve as a spread with dark bread rounds.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix eggs, milk, corn and melted Crisco. Stir in all dry ingredients. Stir lightly. Drop by spoonful in hot Crisco until golden brown (375°).

title: cool as a cucumber soup
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and blend only until cucumber is finely chopped, not smooth.
Chill and serve.
Garnish with a sprinkle of dill or chives, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: taco delight
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Stir in taco seasonings and 1 cup water.
Simmer for 3 to 4 minutes; set aside.
Place crushed chips in an ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer pinto beans, then ground beef mixture over chips.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: miniature cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts and blend thoroughly. Roll mixture into balls about 1/2-inch in diameter.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Chill and serve with toothpicks.
Makes about 24.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Stir and put in 6 muffin tins sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Six muffins equal 1 bread, 1 protein, 1 fruit and 1 milk.

title: mom's coconut cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: northwest cheesecake supreme
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and flour, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until blended. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Blend in sour cream and vanilla; pour over crust. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 250° and continue to bake for 1 hour. Loosen cake from rim of pan; cool before removing from pan. Chill. Top with pie filling just before serving.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Take out stems of large, fresh mushrooms.
Saute in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Add green onions, bread crumbs, meat and parsley or chives.
Moisten with sour cream.
Add seasonings.
Stuff caps with mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese over. Drizzle melted butter over.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot chicken souffle
directions: Trim crusts from bread and cube these on top of chicken mixture.
Combine eggs with milk; pour over all.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour (may be made the day before it is to be used).

title: curry rice
directions: Cook chicken until almost done.
Add carrots and potatoes and onions.
Finish cooking.
Add curry powder, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Mix all together (may make a thickening out of flour and water and add to finished product).

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs and buttermilk together.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Add melted butter; beat until smooth.
Drop from spoon on hot griddle.
Bake on one side about 2 minutes.
Turn and bake about 2 minutes longer.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix
cheese,
Miracle Whip, onion and garlic salt.
Mix shrimp in last.
Refrigerate and serve with crackers.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Put into cooled pie shell or graham cracker crust.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs. Add other ingredients.
Pour onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, sugar and ground nuts.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares immediately.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of boiling water (10 to 15 minutes); drain.
Season to taste.
Combine squash mixture, carrot, sour cream and soup.
Bake in 2-quart casserole at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Top with buttered crumbs for 15 minutes before finishing; brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Spread on flour tortillas.
Roll tightly and refrigerate before cutting (overnight is best.)
Makes about 15 to 20.

title: spanish rice(serves 6)
directions: Combine all ingredients in an oiled baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven (350°), uncovered, for about 1 hour or until rice is soft.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture, then add buttermilk.
Add bananas and pecans last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center of loaf comes out clean.
(Bake bread in loaf pan or Bundt pan.)

title: green beans almondine
directions: Cook beans according to package directions.
Don't overcook. Add butter and almonds, which have been sliced and browned in butter.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak first 2 ingredients together for 1 hour. Mix shortening, brown sugar and egg together thoroughly. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together. Stir in alternately oat mixture and shortening mixture. Mix well together. Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake until golden brown at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 12 individual muffins.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and chill.

title: honey graham treats
directions: Line
cake pan (11
x
14-inches)
with
honey	grahams (break into quarters).
Bring butter and brown sugar to a boil and boil for 1 1/2
minutes.
Pour over graham crackers making sure all are coated.
Sprinkle
with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until mixture begins to thicken.
Let cool 5 minutes, then take out of the pan and break into quarters.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken for 1 hour with enough salt to taste.
After chicken cools, pick meat off the bone in bite-size pieces.
Add celery, pickles and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Good for sandwiches or eat as is.

title: carrot pilaf
directions: Combine carrot and onion; cook in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients until heated through.
Garnish with chopped parsley or mint.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix ingredients and cook until it begins to thicken. Add 1 tablespoon butter and pour in uncooked crust. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°. Bake on cookie sheet pan and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: rump roast
directions: In foil, wrap meat with soup.
Roast at 350° for about 4 hours.
Thicken gravy from juice in pan.
Add mushrooms.

title: apple crunch
directions: Beat egg and add melted butter and vanilla.
Slice apples thinly.
Put into 9-inch greased pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Mix in egg, butter and vanilla; pour over apples. Sprinkle generously with cinnamon.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: microwave chili
directions: Place beef, onion, green pepper and garlic in 3-quart casserole.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes, or until beef is no longer pink and vegetables are tender.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Microwave on High for 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir after cooking.

title: caramel delight
directions: Combine all ingredients together and press into pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Place chopping blade in food processor. Chop vegetables.
Cut up cream cheese into sixths.
Place in processor and pulse until just blended with vegetables (on, off, on, off).
Don't let machine run too long as everything will turn to mush.
That's it. Serve with crackers, Melba toast or vegetables.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix ingredients together (do not drain pineapple).
Pour in pie crust.
Chill until thickened, about 2 hours.

title: rotel dip
directions: Melt cheese and all ingredients.
Ready to serve with chips.

title: coffee cloud cake
directions: Dissolve 1 tablespoon granules in boiling water.
Set aside. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat egg yolks in a large mixing bowl until thick and pale.
Gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar; beat until blended.
Beat an additional 5 minutes at high speed.
Add reserved flour mixture to egg yolk mixture, alternately with reserved coffee mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and 1 cup walnuts.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar at high speed of an electric mixer until foamy.
Gradually add remaining 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form and sugar is dissolved (2 to 4 minutes).
Fold one-fourth of egg white mixture into egg yolk mixture; carefully fold in remaining egg white mixture.
Pour batter into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Invert pan, using a narrow metal spatula; remove from pan.
Place on a serving plate.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Stir in pan butter, Milnot and salt until butter is melted and warm.
In bowl, add 1 pound sugar and melted butter mixture. Knead and wrap around cherries.
Chill overnight.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips.
Add paraffin to chips and melt. Take a fork or toothpick and dip cherry balls into chocolate. Place on waxed paper and chill.
Then leave at room temperature.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Add yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Mix in flour.
Let dough rise 10 minutes and roll into 9 x 12-inch shape.
Spread top of dough with melted butter. Combine sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle across the butter. Roll into jelly roll shape and cut into slices.
Place in greased pan. Let rise and bake at 375° for about 25 minutes. Cover hot rolls with powdered sugar glaze.

title: creamy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken, reserving 2 cups of the broth.
Chill and dice chicken.
Melt butter over low heat; add flour, stirring about 3 to 4 minutes until blended.
Slowly stir in broth, cream and sherry.
Season with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Simmer and stir sauce with wire whisk until thick, smooth and hot.
Saute onion and green pepper into butter; remove.
Saute mushrooms.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms to sauce.
Cook spaghetti; place in bottom of greased casserole.
Cover with chicken and sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Simmer or bake chicken until tender; remove meat from bones. Cut into bite-sized pieces.
Degrease liquid from cooking chicken. To the broth, add enough water to measure 2 1/3 cups.
Bring broth to boil; add rice and seasoning packet; cook according to directions on package until rice is tender and broth is absorbed. Combine ingredients, blending well.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole or 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Cover lightly with foil during first part of baking time; remove foil so mixture browns lightly.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Saute mushrooms and green pepper in butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat; stir until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat and slowly stir in broth and cream. Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Add chicken and pimiento.
Continue cooking until meat is heated through.
Serve hot in patty shells, pastry cases, biscuit rings, timbale cases or over toast points, noodles or fluffy rice. Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Wash and drain broccoli and mushrooms.
Slice into bite-size pieces.
Parboil broccoli.
Mix soup, cheese, mayonnaise and mushrooms in a large bowl.
Add broccoli.

title: rigatoni
directions: Cook Italian sausage on low in small
bottle
of
olive oil. Mix puree, tomato sauce, paste, water
and sugar together; cook on low while sausage is cooking.
Add 4 garlic cloves to
sauce.
Add sausage and oil to sauce.
Cover
and
simmer. Cook rigatoni noodles and serve sauce over noodles.

title: ribbon salad
directions: First, mix lime jello as directed on box.
Put in long dish; set in refrigerator until set.
Then mix lemon jello with 2 cups boiling water; add, while hot, the cheese and pineapple.
Let cool.
Pour on already-set lime jello.
Let this set in refrigerator until firm.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix and blend well all of the ingredients.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.
Cut into small squares to serve.
May be frozen.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and vanilla (and/or lemon juice).
Pour batter on a greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread batter with spoon.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Saute onions in margarine until soft.
Mash potatoes.
Add cheese and beat with mixer.
Add 1/3 of onions to potato mix.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: candy bar brownies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Set aside 1/4 cup. Add remaining dry ingredients to the egg mixture. Mix well. Toss Snickers pieces with reserved flour mixture. Stir into batter. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with milk chocolate candy bar pieces. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool on a wire rack. Chill before cutting.

title: texas salad
directions: Mix lettuce (broken into bite size pieces), onion, cheese and beans together.
Wait until ready to eat; cover with crushed chips and dressing.

title: church supper sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery. Drain fat.
Return to pan and add tomato puree, vinegar, garlic, brown sugar, mustard and salt and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted. Serve on buns.

title: rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over margarine, sugar and salt. Blend and cool. Add beaten eggs. Sprinkle yeast in cup of warm water. Add to mixture. Add flour, one cup at a time. Cover and put in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into wedges no more than 1/2-inch at widest.
Shake in a bag with flour and Parmesan cheese.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Put potatoes in pan, taking care not to have them touch each other.
Salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use foil to cover the first half hour.
Turn after 30 minutes and remove foil.
Kids love these potatoes!

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco and butter.
Add buttermilk.
Roll out; cut into biscuits.
Makes about 2 dozen (according to size of biscuits you cut).

title: browned paprika potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes; brush with melted fat.
Roll potatoes in mixture of cornflake crumbs, paprika and salt.
Bake, covered, in greased baking pan in hot oven (425°) about 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lemon pie(eagle brand pie)
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar and beat together.
Add Eagle Brand milk and mix together.
Add lemon juice and beat well.
Pour in baked pie crust.
Good to eat.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine egg, yolks and milk.
Slowly add the lime juice. Pour into a baked pastry shell.
Chill for 4 hours in the freezer. Before serving, top with whip cream or meringue.

title: clam stew
directions: Cook eggs until hard boiled and put aside.
In medium pot, simmer clams and butter.
The add celery and onions.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook until potatoes are done.
Cut eggs into pieces and add to stew.
Add enough milk to make stew as thick or as thin as you like.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat egg yolks, stir in 1/2 cup sugar, salt and nutmeg; add milk. Pour into pie shell and bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce to 300° and bake about 45 minutes more or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Top with meringue and bake until brown.

title: rich cocoa fudge
directions: Stir together sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full boil.
Without stirring, boil to 234°.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Let cool to 110°.
Beat until it loses its gloss.

title: spinach quiche in a rice crust
directions: Cook rice in water until tender; drain and mix with 1 beaten egg and tablespoon cheese.
Press firmly into 9-inch pie pan to form crust.
Bake crust 3 minutes in 425° oven.
Saute onion in margarine until slightly brown.
Add to spinach, nutmeg, pepper and lemon juice.
Put in crust; sprinkle with remaining cheese. Mix 2 eggs with milk and pour into quiche.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Done when center is firm.
Makes 6 servings, approximately 185 calories per serving.

title: grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients. Place in heavy-duty zip top plastic bag or shallow container. Add tenderloins, turning to coat. Seal or cover and marinate in refrigerator at least 4 hours, turning occasionally. Remove tenderloins from marinade, discarding marinade. Grill tenderloins, uncovered, over medium coals (300° to 350°) for 16 minutes or until meat thermometer inserted in thickest part registers (160° for medium), 20 to 22 minutes for well-done (adjust thermometer), turning once. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before slicing. Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, peanuts, onion and raisins.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over other ingredients and mix well. Sunflower seeds may be used instead of peanuts.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Saute onion in bacon grease or butter and add tomatoes and eggplant (mashed slightly with potato masher).
Add eggs; stir in cheese.
Add bread crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sherbet array!
directions: Mix ingredients in pitcher.

title: peppermint candy ice cream pie
directions: Combine chocolate wafer crumbs and butter in small bowl; mix well.
Press over bottom and up side of 9-inch pie plate.
Combine ice cream and whipped topping in bowl; mix until smooth.
Spoon into pie shell.
Sprinkle with crushed candy.
Freeze until firm. Garnish with additional crushed peppermint candy, if desired. Yield:
6 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into florets.
Add chopped onion and 1 cup of raisins.
Mix together vinegar, mayonnaise and sugar.
Mix together.
Crumble bacon on top.

title: baked apple
directions: Spray dish.
Place apple in dish and sprinkle ground cinnamon; bake in 350° oven until tender.
Remove from oven and sprinkle Equal over it.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk.
Keep out about 1 cup of flour to roll dates and nuts in.
Add coconut, then add to butter mixture. Mix in dates, nuts and orange slices.
Bake at 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
When cake is done, leave in pan and put the following mixture over it.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water and cook until thick and clear.
Take off of heat and add jello to hot mixture.
Cool.
Put fresh blackberries in cooked pie crust.
Pour mixture over berries.
Keep in refrigerator.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: If you like you may add peppermint or cherry flavoring to red coloring.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Use your favorite pie crust recipe.

title: millie's picnic punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sweeten to taste.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: cherry jello
directions: Bring pie filling and Jell-O to boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Do not drain pineapple.
Refrigerate.

title: hobo beans by sandra day peed
directions: Drain excess juice off baked beans and kidney beans.
Add to hamburger with remaining ingredients and put into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cornstarch bread(modeling clay)
directions: Tear off bread crusts and feed to birds.
Shred bread into fine crumbs in bowl.
Add cornstarch and mix.
Add glue and water. Mix with hands into a ball.
May add more water if necessary. Knead until smooth and elastic (10 minutes).
Model objects.
This dough cuts and rolls thin and smooth.
Dries without cracking.

title: chicken continental
directions: Roll chicken in flour. Brown in butter. Remove chicken. Stir soup mixture into drippings. Cook and stir. Bring to a boil. Spread rice in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Pour all but 1/3 of soup mixture over rice. Stir to moisten. Top with chicken and rest of soup mixture. Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: veggie chili
directions: Mix all together; simmer for an hour.
Serves 4.
Wonderful with crusty bread.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve the 2 boxes of jello in the boiling water, mix in the cranberry sauce until smooth, then add pineapple with juice. Pour into mold to gel.

title: crescent veggie dinner rolls
directions: Place rolls in ungreased 11 x 14-inch pan.
Bake until brown; let cool.
Mix Miracle Whip, sour cream, cream cheese and Ranch dressing; spread over crust.
Spread veggies over cream cheese mixture.
Cover with Saran Wrap and press veggies down.
Chill until ready to serve.
Cut with pizza cutter and enjoy.

title: chicken pie
directions: Crust:
Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in butter and shortening until size of peas.
Sprinkle water over mixture a little at a time while tossing lightly with a fork.
Form into a ball.
Place on floured board.
Roll to form a rectangle 21 x 14-inches.
Cut into six 7-inch squares.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Separate frozen roll dough into pieces (each cloverleaf makes 3 pieces).
Combine dry pudding mix with brown sugar and chopped pecans.
Melt margarine.
Place pieces of frozen dough in a well-buttered Bundt pan.
Pour melted margarine over frozen dough and sprinkle with dry pudding, sugar and nut mixture.
Leave pan out overnight, covered, with a towel; the dough rises beautifully by morning.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Invert on platter to serve.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Fold all ingredients together and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream well shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together 3 times and add to shortening and egg mixture: flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add half and half or sour cream.
Drop batter into well-greased bread pans in layers. Between each layer, sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mix (3 parts sugar, 1 part cinnamon).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt and basil; stir in chicken broth and cook until thick and comes to a boil.
Add chicken.
Mix cottage cheese with egg.
Place 1/3 of chicken mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 of noodles, 1/2 of cottage cheese, 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with chicken. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick of butter and cracker crumbs.
Pat into a dish. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, or chill for one hour.

title: crispy cheese sticks
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, shortening and salt until mealy. Stir in cheese and enough milk for a soft but not sticky dough. Turn dough onto a lightly floured board; knead.
Roll pieces of dough between palms to 1/2-inch in diameter and 4 inches long. Bake in an ungreased baking pan at 450° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cool and serve.
Yields 20 to 24 sticks.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip the cream cheese until soft. Blend peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk; blend thoroughly. Fold in Cool Whip. Freeze in graham cracker crust.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except oleo and bread crumbs. Put in a well greased casserole dish.
Put butter over top and add bread crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: nanny's melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove bones and cut up.
Put in 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Put soup and broth in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken and eggs.
Combine oleo, pepper, flour and buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly to form batter.
Spoon or pour batter over top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: strawberry surprise jello
directions: Pour gelatin into boiling water.
When granules dissolve, set aside to cool.
Crushed bananas, thawed strawberries and chopped nuts are added to cooled gelatin.
One-half of the mixture is poured into pan and placed in refrigerator to congeal.
Sour cream is spread over congealed gelatin and remainder of mixture is poured on top of sour cream.
Pan is returned to refrigerator until top portion of the salad is congealed.
Serves 6 to 8 persons.
Make in 9-inch square pan.

title: creamy first-down fudge
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line 9-inch square pan with aluminum foil.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 8 minutes; cool.
In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate chips with Eagle Brand and vanilla. Remove from heat; stir in cheese until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread over prepared crust.
Chill 2 hours or until firm. Lift fudge from pan onto cutting board; peel off foil and cut into squares.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: baked pears delicious
directions: Arrange pear halves, cut side down, in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.

title: lasagna(low cholesterol)
directions: Brown beef in electric frypan with chopped onion.
Add tomato juice, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce and spices.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, layer 1/2 noodles, 1/2 sauce, 1/2 cottage cheese and 1/2 Parmesan cheese.
Repeat all layers and sprinkle with parsley flakes. Cover with foil and let set at least 1/2 hour, longer if desired. Bake covered for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and bake an additional 15 to 25 minutes until top is brown.
Let stand 20 minutes before cutting into 8 servings.

title: pizzaburgers
directions: Brown hamburger.
Grind bologna, American cheese and hamburger.
Add to remaining ingredients (Prego, sage, garlic salt, pepper and oregano).
Spread on hamburger buns, top with Mozzarella cheese and bake at 400° until roll is browned and cheese is melted.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Marinate chicken for at least 3 hours.
Remove chicken; reserve marinade.
Grill chicken or bake at 350°.
Baste often with marinade.
Makes 4 servings.
Each serving contains 151 calories and 3 g fat.

title: shrimp and olive eggs(appetizer)
directions: Split eggs lengthwise.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard, chopped olives and shrimp with the egg yolks.
Stuff egg whites with this mixture. Garnish with baby shrimp and green olive slices.
Serves 6.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer coconut and chopped pecans.
Pour cake mix over coconut and pecan layers.

title: chewy oatmeal bars
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Mix flour, soda and salt together.
Add to above mixture and mix well.
Spread batter in greased jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over the batter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies in half.
Lay in bottom of cake pan.
Mix pudding as box says.
Drain pineapple.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour over Twinkies.
Put in icebox for 30 minutes.
Then take Cool Whip and spread over pudding.
Add nuts.

title: dutch oven meat loaf dinner
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly. Wrap in foil to form approximately 2-inch thick loaf. Place in center of foil-lined Dutch oven. Add chopped potatoes, carrots and/or various other vegetables of your choice in the pan around the meat loaf.

title: black bean 'n olive salsa
directions: In medium bowl, mash 1/2 cup black beans with a fork.
Stir in salsa, remaining black beans, olives, corn, lemon juice and remaining seasoning.
Chill at least 1 hour to blend flavors. Serve as a dip with chips.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix the cream of chicken soup, the cream of mushroom soup and the Lipton onion soup; mix together and add water to your soup cans just to get all soup out (just a little water); pour this into the mixture and stir.

title: potatoes duchess
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 1/2
x 13 casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If desired, during the last 15 minutes add 1 cup crushed potato chips on top.

title: macaroni beef
directions: Saute beef, macaroni, onion, green pepper and garlic powder in oil or water until macaroni turns slightly yellow.
Drain off fat. Add tomato juice and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Uncover and cook for several more minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: morning punch
directions: Combine everything except ginger ale.
Mix well and chill. Add ginger ale just before serving.
Garnish each glass with a strawberry if desired.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: **frito chili pie
directions: Mix meat and water so all meat is moist.
Add all seasonings. Cook until meat is no longer pink.
Alternate layers of meat and Fritos in baking dish.
Add grated cheese.
Add enough water to keep it moist while baking until done in a moderate oven.

title: tufulis
directions: Brown onion, garlic and mushrooms, then mix in large bowl with raw meat, Mozzarella cheese, eggs, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and oregano.
Mix well.
Partially cook manicotti noodles in salt water.
Stuff with meat mixture; place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with tomato sauce; sprinkle with cheese to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, covered.

title: oyster soup(servings:  8)
directions: Melt the butter over medium heat in a 6-quart saucepan, then saute the celery and green onions until tender, but not browned, stirring frequently.
Gradually stir in the flour and cook 5 minutes longer, stirring constantly, over low heat.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove the pan from the heat and scoop out the bay leaves and discard.
Serve immediately.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first five ingredients until smooth in a bowl.
On a 13 x 9-inch glass dish or large pie plate, layer chopped tomatoes, then lettuce.
Spread on top the sauce from bowl.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Stand taco chips on top.
Serve others in bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: irish coffee
directions: Combine all ingredients, except whiskey and whipping cream, in 4 cup glass measure.
Microwave for 8 to 9 minutes on High, or until hot (about 200°).
Stir in whiskey.
Pour into mugs or glasses. Top with dollop of whipped cream.
Do not allow liquid to boil or flavor will be bitter.

title: zucchini loaf
directions: Beat eggs; gradually add sugar and oil.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with grated zucchini.
Stir in raisins and nut meats.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans (bread). Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done (check).
Cool at least 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: chicken wing recipe
directions: Cut off tips and separate each wing at the joint.
Sprinkle wings with salt and pepper to taste.
Heat oil in deep-fat fryer or large heavy pot.
When it is quite hot, add half the wings and cook about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
When wings are golden brown and crisp, remove them and drain well.
Add remaining wings and repeat process.
Meanwhile, melt butter in saucepan, add hot sauce to taste and vinegar.
Pour hot sauce over wings and shake in bucket.
Serve with Blue Cheese dressing and celery sticks.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in small balls and mash with fork. Bake 15 minutes at 300° to 350°.

title: tea cookies
directions: Mix oil, margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Slowly add flour, salt and baking soda and mix well.
Chill dough 1 to 2 hours.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls, space 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten cookie with a glass that is dipped each time in sugar.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: potato-sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onions and drain.
Mix milk, soup and pepper together.
In 9 x 9-inch dish layer one-half potatoes and one-half of soup mixture and one-half cheese and one-half sausage.
Repeat. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and sprinkle a little more Cheddar cheese over top.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: yogurt-dill sauce
directions: Mix all but the last optional ingredient together, adding salt and freshly ground pepper to taste.
If desired, sprinkle capers over top.
Good for cold fish and game birds.
Makes 1 cup.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place apples in a bowl and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup margarine until it looks like crumbs.
Add enough milk and mix until dough leaves sides.
Boil sugar and water; let it come to a good boil and set aside.
Roll dough to 1/4 inch thick. Spread apples on dough.
Roll like jelly roll and slice in 16 slices.
Place in buttered pan.
Pour all of sugar-water syrup over apples and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
