title: chocolate dream pie
directions: Mix and pat into oblong pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven and immediately stir well with fork.
Pat into pie plate, reserving 1/4 cup to sprinkle on top.

title: pennsylvania 8 bean soup
directions: Wash beans and barley.
Place in large kettle and cover with water to 2 inches above beans.
Add 2 tablespoons salt.
Soak overnight and drain in morning.
Add 2 quarts water and ham bone or hock.
Bring to boil and simmer slowly 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove ham bone or hock.
Cut off meat; chop and return to soup.
Add onion, tomatoes, chili powder, lemon juice, sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer 1 hour or more.
Serve with tossed salad and corn bread or crusty French bread.
Enjoy!

title: hot artichoke - spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach and artichoke.
Add all other ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili-chicken stew
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Cook chicken and next 5 ingredients in hot oil in a Dutch oven until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes and next 5 ingredients; cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Top individual servings with remaining ingredients. Yield:
6 servings.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil
cabbage
approximately
15 minutes, then separate leaves.
Cook
rice and add to all the other ingredients.
Put 1/4 to
cup mixture into cabbage leaves; roll and attach ends with toothpicks or put open end down.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Mix cake ingredients well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, 35 minutes if using glass dish.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
Dust with flour and dash of pepper.
In large skillet, brown meat in butter.
Add sliced mushrooms (drained), onion and garlic.
Brown lightly.
Stir in beef broth.
Cover.
Cook about 1 hour or until meat is tender. Stir occasionally.
Gradually stir in sour cream.
Heat about 5 minutes.
Serve over 3 cups cooked noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chili-chicken casserole
directions: Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan with chips.
In a large skillet, over medium heat, saute chicken, onion and garlic in oil until chicken is opaque.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour over chips.
Top with cheeses.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cajun ribs
directions: Combine seasonings.
Rub on all surfaces of ribs.
Place ribs on covered grill over indirect heat.
Grill for 1 1/2 hours.
Cut ribs into serving-sized pieces.
Makes 4 servings.

title: taco shells
directions: Mix ingredients; add enough water for thin pancake batter consistency.
Salt black skillet and heat.
Put batter in by tablespoon.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons in skillet, then tilt skillet until batter almost covers bottom.
Fry until brown, then turn.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Soak apricots in 1 cup water for 30 minutes; drain well.
Mix egg, sugar and melted butter.
Combine dry ingredients to sugar mixture alternately with orange juice.
Fold in apricots and nuts. Pour into greased and floured bread pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: hot rolls
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve dry yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and salt.
Beat and add shortening.
Then add eggs and mix well. Add flour, 2 cups at a time.
I use 7 1/2 cups.
Mix well.
I use mixer, up to 4 cups, then mix the rest with my hands.
Do not knead.
Put into large, greased bowl and let rise, about 3 hours. I cover my bowl with a tea towel dampened with warm water.
It keeps the dough from getting dry on top.

title: mexican style potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes thinly and lightly brown in bacon grease; set aside.
Combine onions, chilies, tomatoes, oregano, cumin and garlic salt to make sauce.
Mix potatoes with bacon and sauce and cook over low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Put in casserole and top with cheese.
Heat in 350° oven until the cheese melts.

title: russian cheese babka
directions: Combine cream cheese, vanilla, butter, cherries, cottage cheese, raisins and pineapple; beat until smooth.
With a moistened piece of cheesecloth, line a clean flowerpot whole.
Put in mix; put on a rack to drain in refrigerator overnight or longer.
Unmold; garnish with candied cherries.
Serves 6.

title: roast chicken
directions: Melt butter in small bowl, season with thyme, garlic and seasoned salt.
Brush on chicken.
Season body cavity with butter mixture.
Place in roasting pan.
Brown in 400° oven for 30 to 45 minutes, uncovered.
Stuff body cavity with cut celery sticks and onions.
Add quartered potatoes and carrots to pan.
Add 1 to 2 cups of water.
Cover; roast in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove chicken and vegetables.
Thicken broth for gravy.

title: avocado salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except avocado and tomato.
Fold in avocado and tomatoes.

title: grandma stephens' peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and baking powder in a large bowl.
Cream margarine and sugars; then beat eggs, peanut butter and vanilla. Mix thoroughly and add to flour.
Knead to form a smooth dough. Roll into hickory nut shaped balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Upon removing from oven, place a chocolate star in the middle.
Yield:
7 dozen cookies.

title: pheasant stew with sage dumplings
directions: Place pheasant pieces and the remaining ingredients in a casserole and add just enough boiling water to cover.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: sausage, tomatoes and potatoes
directions: Brown sausage, potatoes, onion and green pepper.
Drain excess grease.
Add seasonings and sauce.
Simmer about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oven roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In plastic bag or bowl, shake or toss all ingredients until all are coated.
Empty into 13 x 9-inch baking or roasting pan.
Bake, stirring once, 2 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake brownies as directed on box, let cool and then crumble into small pieces. Mix pudding as directed on box.
Crumble candy into small pieces. Using a clear trifle bowl begin the layering of the
ingredients--
1/2 of the brownies, next 1/2 of the pudding, next 1/2 of the cool whip & 1/2 of the candy pieces
-- and repeat layering all of the ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Enjoy after dinner!

title: baked steak
directions: Heavily salt, pepper and garlic salt both sides of steak. Place steak in a 1/2-inch high baking pan, uncovered.
Next, spread ketchup over top.
Add Worcestershire sauce and then place pats of butter on top.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes for medium steak.
Do not cover or turn!! For well-done meat, bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Slice thin to 1/4-inch pieces.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: donna's chili
directions: Brown meat. Saute onion and pepper. Then add all ingredients and simmer for 2 hours or more.

title: waldorf salad cupcakes
directions: Stir together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Put egg, sugar and vanilla into a large bowl and beat with electric mixer at medium speed.
Add mayonnaise until well blended.
Add flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Add apple, walnuts and celery. Spoon into lined baking cups.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in a large mixer bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
(Batter will be stiff.) Drop by rounded teaspoons onto ungreased baking sheets, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 10 dozen.

title: butterfinger cheesecake
directions: Make the graham cracker crust according to the side of the box. Press it into a spring-form pan and cook according to the box.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add the sour cream, then add 1 egg at a time.
Crust two of the candy bars and add to the mixture.
Pour mixture into spring-form pan.
Cook on 350° for an hour or until golden brown.
(It might be a little jiggly in the middle, but that's okay.)
Let it cool completely.
Sprinkle the remaining crushed candy bar on top then remove the side of the pan.

title: impossible custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well with electric mixer.
Pour into pie plate and sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a greased pan (11 x 17 x 1-inch).
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Meanwhile prepare the Crumb Mixture (following).

title: libby's brown rice casserole
directions: Butter baking dish along bottom and sides to prevent sticking.
Mix ingredients and place in dish, covered.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; remove and stir.
Bake an additional 30 minutes or longer or until rice has absorbed liquid.
Makes a great side dish for beef, chicken or pork.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Dice onion; add to hamburger with garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Brown and drain.
Add soup, beans, water and chili powder.
Let simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves about 8.

title: fruit sherbet
directions: Dissolve sugar in 2 cups hot water.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Freeze, stirring several times while freezing.

title: shrimp stew
directions: Use twice the volume of water to the volume of ingredients. Season with a generous amount of salt and an abundance of seafood seasoning.
Bring water to a boil and add first the sausage, boil 7 to 8 minutes; then put the corn in and boil 8 to 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook between 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Drain all out, preferably in a colander.
Use the melted butter for the corn and cocktail sauce for the shrimp.

title: dream cookies
directions: First, preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg (whites) until frothy. Add pinch of salt.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat until real stiff.
Add almond extract, vanilla, pecans and chocolate chips.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, oatmeal, eggs, onion, spices and soup together thoroughly.
Put into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix catsup, mustard and brown sugar together thoroughly.
Put on top of meat.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Mix with canned chili.
Spread on bottom of oblong casserole dish.
Spread sour cream carefully on top.
Lay cheese slices on top of sour cream.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let cool, then sprinkle Doritos on top.
(Sour cream is optional.)

title: strawberry candies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except almonds, food coloring and red sugar.
Chill one hour or until firm.
Using tablespoonfuls, shape Jell-O mixture into strawberries.
Roll in candied red sugar. Color almonds with green food coloring and insert into strawberry for stem.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in saucepan. Bring to a full rolling boil. Stir continually. Continue for 5 minutes over medium heat. Stir continually. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter. Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla; beat until well blended. Pour into greased (butter) 9 x 13 baking dish. Cool at room temperature. Cut into squares.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Chicken:
Skin
chicken and cut into chunks.
In mixing bowl beat
2 eggs and 2 tablespoons of water; set aside.
In a separate bowl
add
cup of flour, salt and pepper to taste. Add
chicken to
egg
mixture,
then into flour mixture; coat well.
In
a stainless steel pan add about 1/2 cup oil.
Make sure the
oil
is very hot.
Fry chicken approximately 3 to 5 minutes
or
until it turns white.
Remove from oil and drain well on napkins.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo or oil.
Add eggs and lightly hand beat. Add flour and other dry ingredients.
Beat lightly again.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: pita bread
directions: Put dry yeast in water and add sugar.
Stir until yeast is dissolved.
Add the flour and salt; mix well.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Make into 18 or 20 equal sized balls and roll to 5-inches in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet and let rise until puffy. Bake at 500° for about 5 minutes, until puffed, but not too brown. Good with dips or stuffing for sandwiches.

title: helen's soup
directions: Mix chicken broth and tomato juice and bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for about 1/2 hour or until macaroni is done.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook on high in crock-pot for 6 or 7 hours.

title: vegetable chili
directions: In large saucepot or Dutch oven, saute zucchini, green pepper, onions, celery, carrots and garlic in oil until crisp-tender. Stir in tomatoes, picante sauce, water, bouillon and cumin.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in olives, chili beans and garbanzo beans; simmer until thoroughly heated.
Serve with cheese on top.
Serves 6 (1 1/2 cups).

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until thick.
Stir constantly over low heat.

title: pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle pecans in pie shell.
Beat eggs in bowl.
Add corn syrup, melted butter and vanilla; mix well.
Add mixture of flour and sugar.
Pour over pecans.
Let stand until pecans rise to top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: 'freshin' fruit drink
directions: In a blender, place broken bananas, chunked melon and enough orange juice to help soften and mix fruits.
Liquify until completely smooth.
Add more orange juice if you want to thin it a bit more.
Pour into tall glasses and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Sip and enjoy.

title: peanut butter surprise(a recipe from mrs. lamberson's rarely used kitchen)
directions: Mix sugar, graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and melted butter or margarine together in medium bowl and firmly press into 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Chill for one hour.

title: memaw galik's pecan brittles(cookies)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat until smooth. Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt and add remaining ingredients,
Post Toasties, pecans and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on well-greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: ham and egg pudding
directions: Combine ham, milk, butter, bread crumbs, salt and pepper. Stir in egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until they are stiff, but not dry.
Fold egg whites into egg yolk mixture.
Pour into 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish that has been rubbed with butter.
Bake in a slow oven (325°) for 20 to 25 minutes or until firm to the touch. Serve at once.

title: new guinnies
directions: Wilt cabbage leaves.
Shape hamburger meat and other ingredients into balls except tomato juice.
Roll in cabbage leaves and fasten with toothpicks.
Cook 1 1/2 hours in tomato juice.
Yields 40.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown rice in butter until slightly brown; add salt and boiling broth.
Cover and let simmer until liquid is absorbed, about 30 minutes.

title: raw applesauce cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Sift together flour and spices.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about one hour. Top with whipped cream.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove chicken from bones; skin and cut into pieces.
Cook noodles in broth; drain and add cheese. Saute peppers and onion in butter. When soft, add Ro-Tel.
Then add this to noodles, cheese and chicken.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli and rice bake
directions: Cook chopped celery and onion in frying pan in melted margarine until golden.
Combine soup, water and cheese.
Thaw broccoli in water in saucepan until just thawed (about 2 minutes).
Cook rice according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients and place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken chow mein noodle casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand 30 minutes to 1 hour. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: miniature cream puffs
directions: Put water and butter in
saucepan
and	bring
to boil, melting butter.
Take pan off stove and add flour and salt and stir until dough forms a ball.
Add
eggs
one at a time until well blended.
Spoon by
heaping
teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet covered with parchment paper.
Bake
at
until puffed up and browned.
Do not underbake,
as they will fall.
Fill with chicken salad, ham salad or pudding.

title: baked meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into balls.
Place in casserole.

title: cheese ring
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix together cheese, nuts, onion and mayonnaise. Place in mold and let chill overnight. Remove from mold and serve with jam and crackers.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: meringue pie
directions: Beat egg whites and baking powder until whites are stiff.
Beat in sugar.
Fold in graham crackers and nuts.
Bake in 9-inch buttered pie pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli in small amount of boiling water; drain. Combine the cottage cheese, cubed Cheddar cheese, broccoli, unbeaten eggs and seasonings.
Sprinkle flour over all and mix together.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Place dish in pan of water and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in crock-pot and cook on low overnight.

title: company chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken breasts.
Salt and pepper it to your own liking.
Wrap it with a slice of bacon.
Line casserole with slices of dried beef.
Place slices over chicken.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup together and spread over chicken.
Bake at 325° for about 3 hours.
Serve with baked potatoes or wild rice.

title: english toffee cookies
directions: Cream together butter with sugar.
Add unbeaten egg yolk.
Add flour and salt.
Spread dough into 9 x 13-inch greased glass pan. Beat egg white until stiff and spread over dough.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut while still warm.

title: rhubarb punch
directions: Boil together the fruit, water, sugar and lemon juice until the fruit is soft, then strain and add the Jell-O while the mixture is still hot.
It may be frozen at this point to serve at a later time.
To Serve:
Mix equal parts of the juice with 7-Up.

title: hamburger-spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
In a casserole (9 x 13-inch), layer hamburger meat, cooked spaghetti, butter and cheese.
Do layers again.
Heat cream of mushroom soup and milk together until smooth.
Pour over casserole.
Cook at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: mock strawberry jam
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 20 minutes.
Add jello.
Put in sterile jars.

title: smothered steak
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Cut round steak into four pieces. Dip each piece in seasoned flour.
Brown in hot oil, add water. Cover and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Add onions, salt and pepper; cover and continue cooking until tender.

title: carrot salad
directions: Slice carrots thin and cook until tender.
Slice onion thin and arrange layers of carrots and onion until used up.

title: dirt(child-approved)
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar. Mix in pudding and milk until blended.
Add Cool Whip.
In blender or food chopper, grind Oreo cookies to a fine dirt-like consistency.
Layer mixture in a clear bowl (or flower pot) starting with cookie, pudding, cookie, pudding and ending with cookie.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Add a plastic flower or gummy worms and serve.
(Many thanks to Dorothy Larkin!)

title: rainbow salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in refrigerator.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Put sugar,
cocoa and milk in a saucepan and bring to a boil over
high heat; lower heat to medium high and boil for 7 minutes. Drop
in
margarine,
don't
stir,
and
cook 5 more minutes. Add
vanilla
and
nuts
and
beat	until set.
Pour quickly into a buttered dish.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: peach salad
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate.

title: banana bread variations
directions: Heat oven to 350° and grease 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.

title: mom's filled cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add milk alternately with flour until have a stiff dough.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs, gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased baking sheet, spacing about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: ground meat main dish
directions: In a bowl, combine meat, crumbs and milk.
Mix well.
Shape into 36 meat balls.
Drain pineapple (keep juice).
In a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish, combine pineapple juice, soy sauce, oil and seasonings.
Add meat balls.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight. Turn once.
Drain meat balls.
Keep marinade.

title: sparkling cranberry cooler
directions: In a glass pitcher, combine all ingredients except soda, stirring to mix. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour or until well chilled. To serve, stir in soda and add ice, if desired. Serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Fry hamburger meat; drain grease. Put in casserole dish and sprinkle onion soup mix. Cook green beans and put them next. Pour mushroom soup over top, then Tater Tots and cover with grated cheese.

title: low-fat banana snack cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 9-inch square baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl, mix banana, egg substitute, buttermilk, 1/2 cup of the brown sugar, applesauce and vanilla extract until blended.
Stir in flour, baking powder and baking soda until smooth.
Scrape into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pour into oblong casserole dish. Slice eggs and place over chicken mixture.
Mix together milk, flour and butter; pour over eggs and chicken mixture.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: incredible melted ice cream cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with vegetable oil spray and dust with flour. Shake out the flour and set aside. Place cake mix, melted ice cream and eggs in a large mixing bowl. Blend with electric mixer on low speed for 1 minute. Stop mixer; scrape down sides and continue beating 2 more minutes. Pour into prepared pan and bake at 350° for 38 to 42 minutes. Place on wire rack; cool for 20 minutes. Run a long, sharp knife around edge and flip cake onto a small rack. Then flip again onto serving plate. Super Duper. You have to try it!

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and molasses and beat well.
Add spices, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Gradually add flour. Dough will become very stiff and may require mixing by hand.
Form 1-inch balls from dough.
Roll in granulated sugar and place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Don't flatten.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
They shouldn't be overly brown when taken out of the oven.
They will be puffed up when taken from oven but will be snappy when cooled.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix cauliflower, broccoli and onion rings in a bowl.
In container with lid, mix the following: mayonnaise, sugar, vegetable oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Shake until mixed.
Pour mixture over vegetables and chill overnight.
Before serving, fry 2 to 3 pieces of bacon, then crumble on top of salad.

title: nachos grande
directions: Place chips on large plate.
Heat chili.
Combine Monterey Jack and Colby cheeses; heat until melted.
Pour immediately over chips.
Pour chili over cheese and chips.
Top with tomatoes, black olives, green olives and sliced peppers to taste.
May add sour cream on top.

title: spiced hot tea
directions: Boil water.
Pour over tea bags and steep.
Place cinnamon sticks and cloves in 1 quart of water and simmer 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil and serve or store in refrigerator in covered jars.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by spoon.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees about 8 - 10 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup of raisins if you want.
For a chewy cookie bake about 8 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour fruit into pan with the melted butter.
If using fresh fruit, sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over the fruit (canned fruits can also be used).
Mix all the ingredients together; pour over fruit.
Crust will rise to the top.
Cook for 30 to 35 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, vanilla, salt, nutmeg and eggs, well beaten.
Add 2 cups hot milk according to the size of your crust.
Stir well. Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Turn oven back to 375° and bake until silver knife comes out clean, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: johnny mazette
directions: Brown beef, sausage, onion and pepper together.
Add celery, mushrooms, tomato juice and tomatoes.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add cooked noodles.
Just before serving, add 3/4 package Velveeta cheese.

title: mexican dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocado with lemon juice; set aside. Combine mayonnaise, taco seasoning mix and sour cream; set aside. Spread bean dip in shallow bowl, 1-inch deep.
Spread sour cream mix over beans.
Layer avocado mix next.
Sprinkle onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with cheese.
Serve at room temperature. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: parm-a-chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cheese, flour and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk.
Coat with cheese mixture. Place in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Pour margarine over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve sprinkled with additional cheese.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: neiman's cookie recipe
directions: Cream butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with dry ingredients.
Add chips, candy and nuts.
Roll into balls.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: meatballs stroganoff
directions: With fork, combine hamburger, milk, bread crumbs, parsley, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Shape into 1 3/4 inch meatballs.
Brown in 2 tablespoons hot oil in 12-inch skillet.
In another pan heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Cook onion and mushrooms with paprika until tender, 5 to 8 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over mixture. While stirring, add beef broth.
Place meatballs in mixture.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and sour cream.
Heat through, careful not to boil.
Serve over hot rice and sprinkle with dill.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute green pepper in margarine until soft.
Mix with mushroom soup, pimentos and mushrooms.
In 9 x 12 x 2-inch casserole dish, layer 1 can green beans, 1/2 soup mixture, 1 can French fried onions and 2 cups cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 450° for about 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken(good over rice)
directions: Put chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Blend soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Combine margarine, crumbs and poppy seed. Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients to taste.
Serve immediately.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: After chopping, drain peppers and onions.
Add sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and salt.
Mix together and bring to a boil, then let simmer for 30 minutes.
Seal in hot, sterile jars.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, then chill for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
When cooked, slip skins off. With electric mixer, whip potatoes, butter, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and enough milk to make potatoes smooth and creamy.
Add coconut, raisins and walnuts.
If desired, add more cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover entire top of casserole with marshmallows.
Push marshmallows 1/4 way into top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until marshmallows are slightly browned.

title: hot stuff
directions: I let these remain in the liquid, but you may tie up the spices in a cheesecloth bag to later remove them.
Add 8 garlic buds to the pickles.
Bring the liquid to a boil, stirring constantly, and pour it cautiously, little by little, to avoid breaking the glass bottle.
Cover and leave at least a week or 10 days.
It is the sugar that makes the pickles so crisp, so don't skimp on the sugar.
You will be delightfully surprised at the results from this recipe.

title: golden coins(marinated carrots)
directions: Cook carrots 10 minutes or just until tender-crisp.
Drain and cool.
Add sliced onion and chopped green pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Chill.
Refrigerate.
Can be kept in the refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: stroganoff meatballs
directions: Combine hamburger, oats, egg, ketchup, onion and salt.
Mix thoroughly and shape into 24 (1-inch) balls.
Place in baking dish and bake at 450° until done.
Cook noodles in boiling water for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Melt butter in same pan; add noodles and parsley.
Toss to coat noodles with parsley butter.
Cover to keep warm.
Combine soup and sour cream in medium saucepan.
Stir in milk and paprika.
Mix well.
Fold in meatballs.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring frequently until hot.
Serve over noodles.

title: grandmother's oatmeal bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add maple syrup.

title: cheese rice spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° in a greased, uncovered, casserole dish for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, until custard is set and not runny.
Good served with meat loaf or as an appetizer.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin together.
Add the other ingredients and mix until blended well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Prebake 9-inch deep dish pie crust until slightly brown.
Mix all ingredients and pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes until center is firm.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs; add melted butter. Mix sugar and vinegar. Add nuts, coconut and raisins. Pour in pie shell. Bake at 300° about 1 hour.

title: dr. woodruff's poppy seed bread (cake)
directions: Mix all the ingredients and spread into a sheet cake pan or two 8-inch pans. Bake at 350° until doneness (according to size pan used).
Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix corn meal, salt and baking powder.
Stir in buttermilk and egg.
When well mixed, add onions.
Drop by teaspoon into hot grease.
Dip spoon in water between each hush puppy.
Serves 4.

title: 1000 springs trout amandine
directions: Clean and bone trout.
Lay flat on lightly oiled sheet of foil on a broiler pan.
Brush the boneless trout lightly with melted butter and sprinkle Summer Savory over it.
Meanwhile, saute 1 tablespoon of sliced almonds in butter until nicely brown.
Add lemon juice.
Broil trout for about 2 minutes under high heat (about 550°).
Remove from broiler.
Spread the sauteed almonds lightly over the trout and return to oven for another 2 minutes at lower heat.
Garnish with lemon slices and parsley and serve immediately.

title: nancy's jello mold
directions: Oil your mold.
Dissolve jello in hot water and add strawberries, pineapple and nuts.
Pour half of mixture in the mold and refrigerate.
When it congeals, about 2 or 3 hours, spread sour cream over it, then pour other half over that.
Let congeal overnight.
I serve on romaine lettuce.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Saute shrimp in oil in large nonstick skillet over medium heat until opaque.
Remove; set aside.
Add garlic to skillet.
Saute 30 seconds.
Add enough water to broth to make 2 cups.
Add tomatoes, broth mixture, salt, thyme and pepper to skillet.
Bring to boil. Add okra.
Lower heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes or until okra is tender.
Remove from heat; stir in rice, ham, shrimp, lemon juice and red pepper.
Cover; let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle green onions on top.
Serves 4.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in double boiler.
Stir in milk; cook over boiling water, stirring until thickened.
Cook for 15 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Beat eggs; stir into cooled mixture gradually.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Line bowl with wafers.
Top with sliced banana.
Pour part of filling over bananas.
Continue layers, ending with wafers crumbled on top.
Chill and serve.

title: six-layer dinner
directions: Season each layer as it is placed in the baking dish with salt and pepper.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Form into ball and wrap in foil.
Chill in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large plastic Ziploc bag, place all ingredients.
Close bag and shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty into shallow roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, stirring occasionally for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish, if desired, with chopped parsley.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Beat eggs and add to sugar and flour mixture with other ingredients.
Bake in an uncooked pie shell at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: company potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, combine potatoes, undiluted soups, sour cream, milk and onion. Stir until well mixed and season with salt, pepper and dill weed. Turn into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and paprika. Bake an additional 1/2 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal and pecans.
Shape in rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill.
Slice thin and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: no peek chicken bake
directions: Place rice in bottom of large greased roaster. Mix soups and milk and pour over chicken and rice. Sprinkle with dry ingredients. Cover tightly with aluminum foil. Bake 3 hours at 325°.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix with mixer 30 seconds.
Beat at high speed for 3 minutes or by hand.
Knead by hand until smooth.
Shape into ball.
Let rise until double the size.
Punch down and divide into 4 parts. Press into pizza pans.
Bake at 500° for 6 to 8 minutes until starts to brown.
Makes 4 crusts.

title: taffy apple pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out cookie dough onto a 14-inch round pan or stone.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Blend peanut butter, cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth. Spread onto cookie.

title: mocha-peanut sundae sauce
directions: Melt all ingredients together in saucepan or in microwave. Stir in vanilla.
Very good served warm over any flavor ice cream.

title: fruit tart
directions: Blend like for a pie crust the flour and Crisco.
Add baking powder and salt.
Combine with milk, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Take away about 1/4 of dough and add more flour to this part for the lattice work.
Press the rest into 13 x 20 x 3/4-inch pan. Fill with 1 1/2 to 2 cans pie filling.
Take the 1/4 of dough that you have saved and crisscross strips of dough to create a lattice work.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
The tart will be done when bubbling and a toothpick inserted at the edge comes out clean.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Pierce potatoes with fork.
Bake at 425° until tender.
Slice potatoes into halves lengthwise.
Scoop pulp into mixer bowl, reserving shells.
Add milk, margarine, salt, pepper and 1 cup cheese to pulp; beat until smooth.
Stir in half the green onions and bacon.

Spoon into reserved shells; place on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; increase oven temperature to 400°. Toss remaining green onions and bacon with 1/2 cup cheese in bowl. Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake for 15 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine ingredients until mixed.

title: french onion soup
directions: Heat deep pot; add oil and butter. Add onions; season with salt, pepper and 1 teaspoon thyme. Cook onions 15 to 18 minutes, stirring frequently, until tender, sweet and caramel colored. Add bay leaf and sherry (optional) to the pot and deglaze the pan drippings. Add beef stock and cover pot to boil soup to quick boil. Arrange 4 small, deep soup bowls or crocks on a cookie sheet. Place broiler on high. Once soup reaches a boil, ladle into bowls. Float toasted bread on soup and cover each bowl with mound of cheese. Sprinkle remaining thyme on cheese and place pan and soup bowls under hot broiler until cheese melts and bubbles.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Put potatoes and onion in 3-quart saucepan; pour water in, just enough to cover potatoes.
Cook on medium heat until potatoes are done.
Add salt.
Mash potatoes by hand.
Add cream of chicken soup and Velveeta.
Turn fire down to low-medium.
When cheese is melted, it's ready.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Allow to set at least 1/2 hour before serving.

title: napa cabbage salad
directions: Cut cabbage lengthwise and cross-wise, and chopped onions to cabbage.
Brown roman noodles in 1 cube oleo. Add nuts and sunflower seeds, brown well. Add to cabbage and onions.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large pot, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender (10 minutes).
Stir in seasoning.
In large bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetable mix. Separate crescent dough and press over bottom and sides of pie dish.
Pour vegetable mix evenly over crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cheesecake (1)
directions: Mix jello and hot water, chill until jelly like.
Mix graham crackers, powdered sugar and melted butter; use as crust and topping in a 9 X 13 pan.
Cream the cream cheese vanilla & sugar. Chill and whip the evaporated milk.
Mix the cream cheese mixture with the jello mixture, fold in the evaporated milk.
Pour on graham cracker crust, sprinkle with remaining crumbs.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Combine butter, garlic, chives, parsley, salt, rosemary and pepper; mix well.
Place on waxed paper.
Pat into 8-inch roll. Freeze until firm.
Place each piece between 2 sheets of waxed paper or plastic wrap; pound with mallet until 1/4 inch thick. Divide butter into 8 portions.
Place one portion in center of each chicken piece.
Tuck in ends; roll up chicken tightly.
Secure with toothpicks.
Combine milk and egg.
Dip chicken pieces in milk mixture.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Place chicken in a single layer in a shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add garlic, tomatoes, sauce, salt, pepper, oregano and mushrooms. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook lasagne noodles in boiling water about 15 minutes. Drain noodles.
Layer a 9 x 13-inch casserole alternately with noodles, Mozzarella cheese, sauce, Parmesan cheese and ending on top with a layer of sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 370° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly the shortening and sugar. Gradually blend in flour.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Spread half of the dough in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover dough with pie filling.
Spoon remaining dough over pie filling (it is not necessary to cover all of the pie filling).
Bake 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken with 40 cloves of garlic
directions: Coat the chicken pieces with olive oil.
Lay the chicken in a casserole with tight fitting lid.
Add the garlic cloves and herbs and all the remaining olive oil.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hrs. without removing lid.
Serve with French bread.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels and reserve drippings.
Saute onion in reserved bacon drippings until tender; set aside.
Combine potatoes, water, salt and pepper in a saucepan; cook over medium heat just until potato is tender.
Stir in clams, milk, butter and onion; simmer 3 minutes or until well heated.
Crumble bacon over each serving.
Yields 2 servings.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine oatmeal, brown sugar, butter, whole-wheat flour and salt. Stir in 2 cups boiling water.

title: green chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Meat: Boil Chicken breast till meat is fully cooked/cool/shred chicken.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: ice cream delight
directions: Crush crackers fine.
Melt butter and mix with crackers and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 gallon vanilla ice cream (softened) and milk.
Add instant pudding.
Pour on top of cracker mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts or crushed Ritz crackers.
Put in freezer at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding according to directions; combine with container of Cool Whip.
Put 1 layer of graham crackers and then 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Then put 1 more layer of graham crackers and remainder of pudding mixture.
Then put 1 final layer of graham crackers. Open container of instant frosting.
Place can in double boiler or a saucepan with some warm water.
Heat until frosting melts.
Pour over the mixture and refrigerate.

title: becky's chocolate icing
directions: If you prefer dark chocolate icing, use semi-sweet chips.
If you prefer mild chocolate icing, use milk chocolate chips.

title: best breakfast gravy
directions: Open the bacon package at one end and cut crosswise the package so that you have small pieces of bacon (about 1 to 1 1/2 cups), depending on how much gravy you want to make.
Brown bacon pieces in skillet.
When browned, dip the pieces out, leaving the drippings; set aside.

title: minnesota hot dish a la garrison
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Combine all ingredients.
Turn into casserole and bake at 300° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cocoa and eggs.
Add flour, sugar and pecans.
Mix well.
Grease and flour a 1 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Spread mixture in pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cake is done when sides pull away from pan.
Remove and while hot, pour 1 small bag of miniature marshmallows over top, then put pan back in oven until marshmallows are soft.
Remove and spread with topping.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Reserve syrup from strawberries. Blend gelatin, sugar and salt in double boiler. Stir in reserved syrup and eggs.

Place over boiling water and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla, lemon peel, juice and food coloring. Beat cream cheese until fluffy and add gelatin mixture to cheese gradually, beating after each addition until smoothly blended. Whip heavy cream until soft peaks form. Fold into cheese mixture. Fold in drained pineapple and strawberries.
Pour mixture over crust in a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Place in refrigerator to chill overnight. Garnish as desired.

title: "tangy" beef barbecue sandwiches
directions: Cut meat in chunks and place in Dutch oven.
Combine remaining ingredients on top of meat.
Heat until boiling.
Simmer in oven at 250° for 6 hours.
Pick apart meat with a fork.
Makes 30 "tangy" sandwiches.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread beans on large platter.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and seasoning.
Spread on beans.
Top with cheese, tomatoes and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix together butter, powdered sugar, Cool Whip, vanilla butter nut flavoring, and candy bars.
Pinch 1/2 of angel food cake into bite size pieces in a bowl or pan with a lid.
Then pour 1/2 of the Cool Whip mixture over it and 1/2 of the candy.
Repeat the order: 1/2 of the cake, Cool Whip mixture, and candy on top.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Grease an 8 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle rice over bottom. Heat the 2 cans of soup with the milk, stirring until blended. Pour over rice.
Put chicken over rice and sprinkle with onion soup mix. Seal pan with foil.
Bake in a slow oven (325°) for at least 2 hours.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; set aside.
Combine sugar and eggs in a large bowl and beat at high speed with mixer until light and fluffy.
Add oil, vanilla and pumpkin until blended. Gradually add flour mixture until blended.
Add flour mixture, beating at low speed.
Pour batter into 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
